37class DBTest2 : public DBTestBase {
38 public:
39 DBTest2() : DBTestBase("db_test2", /*env_do_fsync=*/true) {}
40};
41
42TEST_F(DBTest2, OpenForReadOnly) {
43 DB* db_ptr = nullptr;
44 std::string dbname = test::PerThreadDBPath("db_readonly");
45 Options options = CurrentOptions();
46 options.create_if_missing = true;
47 // OpenForReadOnly should fail but will create <dbname> in the file system
48 ASSERT_NOK(DB::OpenForReadOnly(options, dbname, &db_ptr));
49 // Since <dbname> is created, we should be able to delete the dir
50 // We first get the list files under <dbname>
51 // There should not be any subdirectories -- this is not checked here
52 std::vector<std::string> files;
53 ASSERT_OK(env_->GetChildren(dbname, &files));
54 for (auto& f : files) {
55 ASSERT_OK(env_->DeleteFile(dbname + "/" + f));
56 }
57 // <dbname> should be empty now and we should be able to delete it
58 ASSERT_OK(env_->DeleteDir(dbname));
59 options.create_if_missing = false;
60 // OpenForReadOnly should fail since <dbname> was successfully deleted
61 ASSERT_NOK(DB::OpenForReadOnly(options, dbname, &db_ptr));
62 // With create_if_missing false, there should not be a dir in the file system
63 ASSERT_NOK(env_->FileExists(dbname));
64}
65
66TEST_F(DBTest2, OpenForReadOnlyWithColumnFamilies) {
67 DB* db_ptr = nullptr;
68 std::string dbname = test::PerThreadDBPath("db_readonly");
69 Options options = CurrentOptions();
70 options.create_if_missing = true;
71
72 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options(options);
73 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
74 column_families.emplace_back(kDefaultColumnFamilyName, cf_options);
75 column_families.emplace_back("goku", cf_options);
76 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
77 // OpenForReadOnly should fail but will create <dbname> in the file system
78 ASSERT_NOK(
79 DB::OpenForReadOnly(options, dbname, column_families, &handles, &db_ptr));
80 // Since <dbname> is created, we should be able to delete the dir
81 // We first get the list files under <dbname>
82 // There should not be any subdirectories -- this is not checked here
83 std::vector<std::string> files;
84 ASSERT_OK(env_->GetChildren(dbname, &files));
85 for (auto& f : files) {
86 ASSERT_OK(env_->DeleteFile(dbname + "/" + f));
87 }
88 // <dbname> should be empty now and we should be able to delete it
89 ASSERT_OK(env_->DeleteDir(dbname));
90 options.create_if_missing = false;
91 // OpenForReadOnly should fail since <dbname> was successfully deleted
92 ASSERT_NOK(
93 DB::OpenForReadOnly(options, dbname, column_families, &handles, &db_ptr));
94 // With create_if_missing false, there should not be a dir in the file system
95 ASSERT_NOK(env_->FileExists(dbname));
96}

98class PartitionedIndexTestListener : public EventListener {
99 public:
100 void OnFlushCompleted(DB* /*db*/, const FlushJobInfo& info) override {
101 ASSERT_GT(info.table_properties.index_partitions, 1);
102 ASSERT_EQ(info.table_properties.index_key_is_user_key, 0);
103 }
104};
105
106TEST_F(DBTest2, PartitionedIndexUserToInternalKey) {
107 const int kValueSize = 10500;
108 const int kNumEntriesPerFile = 1000;
109 const int kNumFiles = 3;
110 const int kNumDistinctKeys = 30;
111
112 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
113 Options options = CurrentOptions();
114 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
115 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kTwoLevelIndexSearch;
116 PartitionedIndexTestListener* listener = new PartitionedIndexTestListener();
117 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
118 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
119 std::vector<const Snapshot*> snapshots;
120 Reopen(options);
121 Random rnd(301);
122
123 for (int i = 0; i < kNumFiles; i++) {
124 for (int j = 0; j < kNumEntriesPerFile; j++) {
125 int key_id = (i * kNumEntriesPerFile + j) % kNumDistinctKeys;
126 std::string value = rnd.RandomString(kValueSize);
127 ASSERT_OK(Put("keykey_" + std::to_string(key_id), value));
128 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
129 }
130 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
131 }
132
133 for (auto s : snapshots) {
134 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s);
135 }
136}

139class PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator
140 : public DBTestBase,
141 public ::testing::WithParamInterface<bool> {
142 public:
143 PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator()
144 : DBTestBase("prefix_bloom_reverse", /*env_do_fsync=*/true) {}
145 void SetUp() override { if_cache_filter_ = GetParam(); }
146 bool if_cache_filter_;
147};
148
149TEST_P(PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator,
150 PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator) {
151 Options options = last_options_;
152 options.comparator = ReverseBytewiseComparator();
153 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewCappedPrefixTransform(3));
154 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
155 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
156 if (if_cache_filter_) {
157 bbto.no_block_cache = false;
158 bbto.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
159 bbto.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1);
160 }
161 bbto.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, false));
162 bbto.whole_key_filtering = false;
163 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
164 DestroyAndReopen(options);
165
166 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(WriteOptions(), "bar123", "foo"));
167 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(WriteOptions(), "bar234", "foo2"));
168 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(WriteOptions(), "foo123", "foo3"));
169
170 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Flush(FlushOptions()));
171
172 if (bbto.block_cache) {
173 bbto.block_cache->EraseUnRefEntries();
174 }
175
176 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
177 iter->Seek("bar345");
178 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
179 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
180 ASSERT_EQ("bar234", iter->key().ToString());
181 ASSERT_EQ("foo2", iter->value().ToString());
182 iter->Next();
183 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
184 ASSERT_EQ("bar123", iter->key().ToString());
185 ASSERT_EQ("foo", iter->value().ToString());
186
187 iter->Seek("foo234");
188 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
189 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
190 ASSERT_EQ("foo123", iter->key().ToString());
191 ASSERT_EQ("foo3", iter->value().ToString());
192
193 iter->Seek("bar");
194 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
195 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
196}
197
198INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator,
199 PrefixFullBloomWithReverseComparator, testing::Bool());
200
201TEST_F(DBTest2, IteratorPropertyVersionNumber) {
202 ASSERT_OK(Put("", ""));
203 Iterator* iter1 = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
204 ASSERT_OK(iter1->status());
205 std::string prop_value;
206 ASSERT_OK(
207 iter1->GetProperty("rocksdb.iterator.super-version-number", &prop_value));
208 uint64_t version_number1 =
209 static_cast<uint64_t>(std::atoi(prop_value.c_str()));
210
211 ASSERT_OK(Put("", ""));
212 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
213
214 Iterator* iter2 = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
215 ASSERT_OK(iter2->status());
216 ASSERT_OK(
217 iter2->GetProperty("rocksdb.iterator.super-version-number", &prop_value));
218 uint64_t version_number2 =
219 static_cast<uint64_t>(std::atoi(prop_value.c_str()));
220
221 ASSERT_GT(version_number2, version_number1);
222
223 ASSERT_OK(Put("", ""));
224
225 Iterator* iter3 = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
226 ASSERT_OK(iter3->status());
227 ASSERT_OK(
228 iter3->GetProperty("rocksdb.iterator.super-version-number", &prop_value));
229 uint64_t version_number3 =
230 static_cast<uint64_t>(std::atoi(prop_value.c_str()));
231
232 ASSERT_EQ(version_number2, version_number3);
233
234 iter1->SeekToFirst();
235 ASSERT_OK(
236 iter1->GetProperty("rocksdb.iterator.super-version-number", &prop_value));
237 uint64_t version_number1_new =
238 static_cast<uint64_t>(std::atoi(prop_value.c_str()));
239 ASSERT_EQ(version_number1, version_number1_new);
240
241 delete iter1;
242 delete iter2;
243 delete iter3;
244}

263}

265TEST_F(DBTest2, MaxSuccessiveMergesChangeWithDBRecovery) {
266 Options options = CurrentOptions();
267 options.create_if_missing = true;
268 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
269 options.max_successive_merges = 3;
270 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
271 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
272 DestroyAndReopen(options);
273 ASSERT_OK(Put("poi", "Finch"));
274 ASSERT_OK(db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), "poi", "Reese"));
275 ASSERT_OK(db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), "poi", "Shaw"));
276 ASSERT_OK(db_->Merge(WriteOptions(), "poi", "Root"));
277 options.max_successive_merges = 2;
278 Reopen(options);
279}

281class DBTestSharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs
282 : public DBTestBase,
283 public testing::WithParamInterface<std::tuple<bool, bool>> {
284 public:
285 DBTestSharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs()
286 : DBTestBase("db_test_shared_write_buffer", /*env_do_fsync=*/true) {}
287 void SetUp() override {
288 use_old_interface_ = std::get<0>(GetParam());
289 cost_cache_ = std::get<1>(GetParam());
290 }
291 bool use_old_interface_;
292 bool cost_cache_;
293};
294
295TEST_P(DBTestSharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs, SharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs) {
296 Options options = CurrentOptions();
297 options.arena_block_size = 4096;
298 auto flush_listener = std::make_shared<FlushCounterListener>();
299 options.listeners.push_back(flush_listener);
300 // Don't trip the listener at shutdown.
301 options.avoid_flush_during_shutdown = true;
302
303 // Avoid undeterministic value by malloc_usable_size();
304 // Force arena block size to 1
305 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
306 "Arena::Arena:0", [&](void* arg) {
307 size_t* block_size = static_cast<size_t*>(arg);
308 *block_size = 1;
309 });
310
311 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
312 "Arena::AllocateNewBlock:0", [&](void* arg) {
313 std::pair<size_t*, size_t*>* pair =
314 static_cast<std::pair<size_t*, size_t*>*>(arg);
315 *std::get<0>(*pair) = *std::get<1>(*pair);
316 });
317 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
318
319 // The total soft write buffer size is about 105000
320 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache = NewLRUCache(4 * 1024 * 1024, 2);
321 ASSERT_LT(cache->GetUsage(), 256 * 1024);
322
323 if (use_old_interface_) {
324 options.db_write_buffer_size = 120000; // this is the real limit
325 } else if (!cost_cache_) {
326 options.write_buffer_manager.reset(new WriteBufferManager(114285));
327 } else {
328 options.write_buffer_manager.reset(new WriteBufferManager(114285, cache));
329 }
330 options.write_buffer_size = 500000; // this is never hit
331 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu", "dobrynia", "nikitich"}, options);
332
333 WriteOptions wo;
334 wo.disableWAL = true;
335
336 std::function<void()> wait_flush = [&]() {
337 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[0]));
338 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[1]));
339 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[2]));
340 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[3]));
341 // Ensure background work is fully finished including listener callbacks
342 // before accessing listener state.
343 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForBackgroundWork());
344 };
345
346 // Create some data and flush "default" and "nikitich" so that they
347 // are newer CFs created.
348 flush_listener->expected_flush_reason = FlushReason::kManualFlush;
349 ASSERT_OK(Put(3, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
350 ASSERT_OK(Flush(3));
351 ASSERT_OK(Put(3, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
352 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
353 ASSERT_OK(Flush(0));
354 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
355 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
356 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
357 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
358
359 flush_listener->expected_flush_reason = FlushReason::kWriteBufferManager;
360 ASSERT_OK(Put(3, Key(1), DummyString(30000), wo));
361 if (cost_cache_) {
362 ASSERT_GE(cache->GetUsage(), 256 * 1024);
363 ASSERT_LE(cache->GetUsage(), 2 * 256 * 1024);
364 }
365 wait_flush();
366 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(60000), wo));
367 if (cost_cache_) {
368 ASSERT_GE(cache->GetUsage(), 256 * 1024);
369 ASSERT_LE(cache->GetUsage(), 2 * 256 * 1024);
370 }
371 wait_flush();
372 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
373 // No flush should trigger
374 wait_flush();
375 {
376 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
377 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
378 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "pikachu"),
379 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
380 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "dobrynia"),
381 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
382 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
383 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
384 }
385
386 // Trigger a flush. Flushing "nikitich".
387 ASSERT_OK(Put(3, Key(2), DummyString(30000), wo));
388 wait_flush();
389 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
390 wait_flush();
391 {
392 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
393 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
394 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "pikachu"),
395 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
396 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "dobrynia"),
397 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
398 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
399 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
400 }
401
402 // Without hitting the threshold, no flush should trigger.
403 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(30000), wo));
404 wait_flush();
405 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
406 wait_flush();
407 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
408 wait_flush();
409 {
410 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
411 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
412 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "pikachu"),
413 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
414 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "dobrynia"),
415 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
416 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
417 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
418 }
419
420 // Hit the write buffer limit again. "default"
421 // will have been flushed.
422 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(2), DummyString(10000), wo));
423 wait_flush();
424 ASSERT_OK(Put(3, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
425 wait_flush();
426 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
427 wait_flush();
428 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
429 wait_flush();
430 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
431 wait_flush();
432 {
433 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
434 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
435 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "pikachu"),
436 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
437 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "dobrynia"),
438 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
439 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
440 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
441 }
442
443 // Trigger another flush. This time "dobrynia". "pikachu" should not
444 // be flushed, althrough it was never flushed.
445 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
446 wait_flush();
447 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(80000), wo));
448 wait_flush();
449 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
450 wait_flush();
451 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
452 wait_flush();
453
454 {
455 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
456 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
457 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "pikachu"),
458 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
459 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "dobrynia"),
460 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
461 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "nikitich"),
462 static_cast<uint64_t>(2));
463 }
464 if (cost_cache_) {
465 ASSERT_GE(cache->GetUsage(), 256 * 1024);
466 Close();
467 options.write_buffer_manager.reset();
468 last_options_.write_buffer_manager.reset();
469 ASSERT_LT(cache->GetUsage(), 256 * 1024);
470 }
471 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
472}
473
474INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(DBTestSharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs,
475 DBTestSharedWriteBufferAcrossCFs,
476 ::testing::Values(std::make_tuple(true, false),
477 std::make_tuple(false, false),
478 std::make_tuple(false, true)));
479
480TEST_F(DBTest2, SharedWriteBufferLimitAcrossDB) {
481 std::string dbname2 = test::PerThreadDBPath("db_shared_wb_db2");
482 Options options = CurrentOptions();
483 options.arena_block_size = 4096;
484 auto flush_listener = std::make_shared<FlushCounterListener>();
485 options.listeners.push_back(flush_listener);
486 // Don't trip the listener at shutdown.
487 options.avoid_flush_during_shutdown = true;
488 // Avoid undeterministic value by malloc_usable_size();
489 // Force arena block size to 1
490 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
491 "Arena::Arena:0", [&](void* arg) {
492 size_t* block_size = static_cast<size_t*>(arg);
493 *block_size = 1;
494 });
495
496 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
497 "Arena::AllocateNewBlock:0", [&](void* arg) {
498 std::pair<size_t*, size_t*>* pair =
499 static_cast<std::pair<size_t*, size_t*>*>(arg);
500 *std::get<0>(*pair) = *std::get<1>(*pair);
501 });
502 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
503
504 options.write_buffer_size = 500000; // this is never hit
505 // Use a write buffer total size so that the soft limit is about
506 // 105000.
507 options.write_buffer_manager.reset(new WriteBufferManager(120000));
508 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"cf1", "cf2"}, options);
509
510 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
511 DB* db2 = nullptr;
512 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname2, &db2));
513
514 WriteOptions wo;
515 wo.disableWAL = true;
516
517 std::function<void()> wait_flush = [&]() {
518 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[0]));
519 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[1]));
520 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[2]));
521 ASSERT_OK(static_cast<DBImpl*>(db2)->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
522 // Ensure background work is fully finished including listener callbacks
523 // before accessing listener state.
524 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForBackgroundWork());
525 ASSERT_OK(
526 static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db2)->TEST_WaitForBackgroundWork());
527 };
528
529 // Trigger a flush on cf2
530 flush_listener->expected_flush_reason = FlushReason::kWriteBufferManager;
531 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(70000), wo));
532 wait_flush();
533 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, Key(1), DummyString(20000), wo));
534 wait_flush();
535
536 // Insert to DB2
537 ASSERT_OK(db2->Put(wo, Key(2), DummyString(20000)));
538 wait_flush();
539
540 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
541 wait_flush();
542 ASSERT_OK(static_cast<DBImpl*>(db2)->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
543 {
544 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default") +
545 GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf1") +
546 GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf2"),
547 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
548 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db2, "default"),
549 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
550 }
551
552 // Triggering to flush another CF in DB1
553 ASSERT_OK(db2->Put(wo, Key(2), DummyString(70000)));
554 wait_flush();
555 ASSERT_OK(Put(2, Key(1), DummyString(1), wo));
556 wait_flush();
557 {
558 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
559 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
560 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf1"),
561 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
562 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf2"),
563 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
564 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db2, "default"),
565 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
566 }
567
568 // Triggering flush in DB2.
569 ASSERT_OK(db2->Put(wo, Key(3), DummyString(40000)));
570 wait_flush();
571 ASSERT_OK(db2->Put(wo, Key(1), DummyString(1)));
572 wait_flush();
573 ASSERT_OK(static_cast<DBImpl*>(db2)->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
574 {
575 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "default"),
576 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
577 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf1"),
578 static_cast<uint64_t>(0));
579 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db_, "cf2"),
580 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
581 ASSERT_EQ(GetNumberOfSstFilesForColumnFamily(db2, "default"),
582 static_cast<uint64_t>(1));
583 }
584
585 delete db2;
586 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
587
588 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
589}

591TEST_F(DBTest2, TestWriteBufferNoLimitWithCache) {
592 Options options = CurrentOptions();
593 options.arena_block_size = 4096;
594 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache = NewLRUCache(LRUCacheOptions(
595 10000000 /* capacity */, 1 /* num_shard_bits */,
596 false /* strict_capacity_limit */, 0.0 /* high_pri_pool_ratio */,
597 nullptr /* memory_allocator */, kDefaultToAdaptiveMutex,
598 kDontChargeCacheMetadata));
599
600 options.write_buffer_size = 50000; // this is never hit
601 // Use a write buffer total size so that the soft limit is about
602 // 105000.
603 options.write_buffer_manager.reset(new WriteBufferManager(0, cache));
604 Reopen(options);
605
606 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
607 // One dummy entry is 256KB.
608 ASSERT_GT(cache->GetUsage(), 128000);
609}

611namespace {
612void ValidateKeyExistence(DB* db, const std::vector<Slice>& keys_must_exist,
613 const std::vector<Slice>& keys_must_not_exist) {
614 // Ensure that expected keys exist
615 std::vector<std::string> values;
616 if (keys_must_exist.size() > 0) {
617 std::vector<Status> status_list =
618 db->MultiGet(ReadOptions(), keys_must_exist, &values);
619 for (size_t i = 0; i < keys_must_exist.size(); i++) {
620 ASSERT_OK(status_list[i]);
621 }
622 }
623
624 // Ensure that given keys don't exist
625 if (keys_must_not_exist.size() > 0) {
626 std::vector<Status> status_list =
627 db->MultiGet(ReadOptions(), keys_must_not_exist, &values);
628 for (size_t i = 0; i < keys_must_not_exist.size(); i++) {
629 ASSERT_TRUE(status_list[i].IsNotFound());
630 }
631 }
632}

634} // anonymous namespace

636TEST_F(DBTest2, WalFilterTest) {
637 class TestWalFilter : public WalFilter {
638 private:
639 // Processing option that is requested to be applied at the given index
640 WalFilter::WalProcessingOption wal_processing_option_;
641 // Index at which to apply wal_processing_option_
642 // At other indexes default wal_processing_option::kContinueProcessing is
643 // returned.
644 size_t apply_option_at_record_index_;
645 // Current record index, incremented with each record encountered.
646 size_t current_record_index_;
647
648 public:
649 TestWalFilter(WalFilter::WalProcessingOption wal_processing_option,
650 size_t apply_option_for_record_index)
651 : wal_processing_option_(wal_processing_option),
652 apply_option_at_record_index_(apply_option_for_record_index),
653 current_record_index_(0) {}
654
655 WalProcessingOption LogRecord(const WriteBatch& /*batch*/,
656 WriteBatch* /*new_batch*/,
657 bool* /*batch_changed*/) const override {
658 WalFilter::WalProcessingOption option_to_return;
659
660 if (current_record_index_ == apply_option_at_record_index_) {
661 option_to_return = wal_processing_option_;
662 } else {
663 option_to_return = WalProcessingOption::kContinueProcessing;
664 }
665
666 // Filter is passed as a const object for RocksDB to not modify the
667 // object, however we modify it for our own purpose here and hence
668 // cast the constness away.
669 (const_cast<TestWalFilter*>(this)->current_record_index_)++;
670
671 return option_to_return;
672 }
673
674 const char* Name() const override { return "TestWalFilter"; }
675 };
676
677 // Create 3 batches with two keys each
678 std::vector<std::vector<std::string>> batch_keys(3);
679
680 batch_keys[0].push_back("key1");
681 batch_keys[0].push_back("key2");
682 batch_keys[1].push_back("key3");
683 batch_keys[1].push_back("key4");
684 batch_keys[2].push_back("key5");
685 batch_keys[2].push_back("key6");
686
687 // Test with all WAL processing options
688 for (int option = 0;
689 option < static_cast<int>(
690 WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kWalProcessingOptionMax);
691 option++) {
692 Options options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
693 DestroyAndReopen(options);
694 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
695
696 // Write given keys in given batches
697 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
698 WriteBatch batch;
699 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
700 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[0], batch_keys[i][j], DummyString(1024)));
701 }
702 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Write(WriteOptions(), &batch));
703 }
704
705 WalFilter::WalProcessingOption wal_processing_option =
706 static_cast<WalFilter::WalProcessingOption>(option);
707
708 // Create a test filter that would apply wal_processing_option at the first
709 // record
710 size_t apply_option_for_record_index = 1;
711 TestWalFilter test_wal_filter(wal_processing_option,
712 apply_option_for_record_index);
713
714 // Reopen database with option to use WAL filter
715 options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
716 options.wal_filter = &test_wal_filter;
717 Status status =
718 TryReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
719 if (wal_processing_option ==
720 WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kCorruptedRecord) {
721 ASSERT_NOK(status);
722 // In case of corruption we can turn off paranoid_checks to reopen
723 // databse
724 options.paranoid_checks = false;
725 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
726 } else {
727 ASSERT_OK(status);
728 }
729
730 // Compute which keys we expect to be found
731 // and which we expect not to be found after recovery.
732 std::vector<Slice> keys_must_exist;
733 std::vector<Slice> keys_must_not_exist;
734 switch (wal_processing_option) {
735 case WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kCorruptedRecord:
736 case WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kContinueProcessing: {
737 fprintf(stderr, "Testing with complete WAL processing\n");
738 // we expect all records to be processed
739 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
740 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
741 keys_must_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
742 }
743 }
744 break;
745 }
746 case WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kIgnoreCurrentRecord: {
747 fprintf(stderr,
748 "Testing with ignoring record %" ROCKSDB_PRIszt " only\n",
749 apply_option_for_record_index);
750 // We expect the record with apply_option_for_record_index to be not
751 // found.
752 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
753 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
754 if (i == apply_option_for_record_index) {
755 keys_must_not_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
756 } else {
757 keys_must_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
758 }
759 }
760 }
761 break;
762 }
763 case WalFilter::WalProcessingOption::kStopReplay: {
764 fprintf(stderr,
765 "Testing with stopping replay from record %" ROCKSDB_PRIszt
766 "\n",
767 apply_option_for_record_index);
768 // We expect records beyond apply_option_for_record_index to be not
769 // found.
770 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
771 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
772 if (i >= apply_option_for_record_index) {
773 keys_must_not_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
774 } else {
775 keys_must_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
776 }
777 }
778 }
779 break;
780 }
781 default:
782 FAIL(); // unhandled case
783 }
784
785 bool checked_after_reopen = false;
786
787 while (true) {
788 // Ensure that expected keys exists
789 // and not expected keys don't exist after recovery
790 ValidateKeyExistence(db_, keys_must_exist, keys_must_not_exist);
791
792 if (checked_after_reopen) {
793 break;
794 }
795
796 // reopen database again to make sure previous log(s) are not used
797 //(even if they were skipped)
798 // reopn database with option to use WAL filter
799 options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
800 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
801
802 checked_after_reopen = true;
803 }
804 }
805}

807TEST_F(DBTest2, WalFilterTestWithChangeBatch) {
808 class ChangeBatchHandler : public WriteBatch::Handler {
809 private:
810 // Batch to insert keys in
811 WriteBatch* new_write_batch_;
812 // Number of keys to add in the new batch
813 size_t num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_;
814 // Number of keys added to new batch
815 size_t num_keys_added_;
816
817 public:
818 ChangeBatchHandler(WriteBatch* new_write_batch,
819 size_t num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch)
820 : new_write_batch_(new_write_batch),
821 num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_(num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch),
822 num_keys_added_(0) {}
823 void Put(const Slice& key, const Slice& value) override {
824 if (num_keys_added_ < num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_) {
825 ASSERT_OK(new_write_batch_->Put(key, value));
826 ++num_keys_added_;
827 }
828 }
829 };
830
831 class TestWalFilterWithChangeBatch : public WalFilter {
832 private:
833 // Index at which to start changing records
834 size_t change_records_from_index_;
835 // Number of keys to add in the new batch
836 size_t num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_;
837 // Current record index, incremented with each record encountered.
838 size_t current_record_index_;
839
840 public:
841 TestWalFilterWithChangeBatch(size_t change_records_from_index,
842 size_t num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch)
843 : change_records_from_index_(change_records_from_index),
844 num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_(num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch),
845 current_record_index_(0) {}
846
847 WalProcessingOption LogRecord(const WriteBatch& batch,
848 WriteBatch* new_batch,
849 bool* batch_changed) const override {
850 if (current_record_index_ >= change_records_from_index_) {
851 ChangeBatchHandler handler(new_batch, num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch_);
852 Status s = batch.Iterate(&handler);
853 if (s.ok()) {
854 *batch_changed = true;
855 } else {
856 assert(false);
857 }
858 }
859
860 // Filter is passed as a const object for RocksDB to not modify the
861 // object, however we modify it for our own purpose here and hence
862 // cast the constness away.
863 (const_cast<TestWalFilterWithChangeBatch*>(this)
864 ->current_record_index_)++;
865
866 return WalProcessingOption::kContinueProcessing;
867 }
868
869 const char* Name() const override { return "TestWalFilterWithChangeBatch"; }
870 };
871
872 std::vector<std::vector<std::string>> batch_keys(3);
873
874 batch_keys[0].push_back("key1");
875 batch_keys[0].push_back("key2");
876 batch_keys[1].push_back("key3");
877 batch_keys[1].push_back("key4");
878 batch_keys[2].push_back("key5");
879 batch_keys[2].push_back("key6");
880
881 Options options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
882 DestroyAndReopen(options);
883 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
884
885 // Write given keys in given batches
886 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
887 WriteBatch batch;
888 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
889 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[0], batch_keys[i][j], DummyString(1024)));
890 }
891 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Write(WriteOptions(), &batch));
892 }
893
894 // Create a test filter that would apply wal_processing_option at the first
895 // record
896 size_t change_records_from_index = 1;
897 size_t num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch = 1;
898 TestWalFilterWithChangeBatch test_wal_filter_with_change_batch(
899 change_records_from_index, num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch);
900
901 // Reopen database with option to use WAL filter
902 options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
903 options.wal_filter = &test_wal_filter_with_change_batch;
904 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
905
906 // Ensure that all keys exist before change_records_from_index_
907 // And after that index only single key exists
908 // as our filter adds only single key for each batch
909 std::vector<Slice> keys_must_exist;
910 std::vector<Slice> keys_must_not_exist;
911
912 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys.size(); i++) {
913 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys[i].size(); j++) {
914 if (i >= change_records_from_index && j >= num_keys_to_add_in_new_batch) {
915 keys_must_not_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
916 } else {
917 keys_must_exist.emplace_back(batch_keys[i][j]);
918 }
919 }
920 }
921
922 bool checked_after_reopen = false;
923
924 while (true) {
925 // Ensure that expected keys exists
926 // and not expected keys don't exist after recovery
927 ValidateKeyExistence(db_, keys_must_exist, keys_must_not_exist);
928
929 if (checked_after_reopen) {
930 break;
931 }
932
933 // reopen database again to make sure previous log(s) are not used
934 //(even if they were skipped)
935 // reopn database with option to use WAL filter
936 options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
937 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
938
939 checked_after_reopen = true;
940 }
941}

1012TEST_F(DBTest2, WalFilterTestWithColumnFamilies) {
1013 class TestWalFilterWithColumnFamilies : public WalFilter {
1014 private:
1015 // column_family_id -> log_number map (provided to WALFilter)
1016 std::map<uint32_t, uint64_t> cf_log_number_map_;
1017 // column_family_name -> column_family_id map (provided to WALFilter)
1018 std::map<std::string, uint32_t> cf_name_id_map_;
1019 // column_family_name -> keys_found_in_wal map
1020 // We store keys that are applicable to the column_family
1021 // during recovery (i.e. aren't already flushed to SST file(s))
1022 // for verification against the keys we expect.
1023 std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<std::string>> cf_wal_keys_;
1024
1025 public:
1026 void ColumnFamilyLogNumberMap(
1027 const std::map<uint32_t, uint64_t>& cf_lognumber_map,
1028 const std::map<std::string, uint32_t>& cf_name_id_map) override {
1029 cf_log_number_map_ = cf_lognumber_map;
1030 cf_name_id_map_ = cf_name_id_map;
1031 }
1032
1033 WalProcessingOption LogRecordFound(unsigned long long log_number,
1034 const std::string& /*log_file_name*/,
1035 const WriteBatch& batch,
1036 WriteBatch* /*new_batch*/,
1037 bool* /*batch_changed*/) override {
1038 class LogRecordBatchHandler : public WriteBatch::Handler {
1039 private:
1040 const std::map<uint32_t, uint64_t>& cf_log_number_map_;
1041 std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<std::string>>& cf_wal_keys_;
1042 unsigned long long log_number_;
1043
1044 public:
1045 LogRecordBatchHandler(
1046 unsigned long long current_log_number,
1047 const std::map<uint32_t, uint64_t>& cf_log_number_map,
1048 std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<std::string>>& cf_wal_keys)
1049 : cf_log_number_map_(cf_log_number_map),
1050 cf_wal_keys_(cf_wal_keys),
1051 log_number_(current_log_number) {}
1052
1053 Status PutCF(uint32_t column_family_id, const Slice& key,
1054 const Slice& /*value*/) override {
1055 auto it = cf_log_number_map_.find(column_family_id);
1056 assert(it != cf_log_number_map_.end());
1057 unsigned long long log_number_for_cf = it->second;
1058 // If the current record is applicable for column_family_id
1059 // (i.e. isn't flushed to SST file(s) for column_family_id)
1060 // add it to the cf_wal_keys_ map for verification.
1061 if (log_number_ >= log_number_for_cf) {
1062 cf_wal_keys_[column_family_id].push_back(
1063 std::string(key.data(), key.size()));
1064 }
1065 return Status::OK();
1066 }
1067 } handler(log_number, cf_log_number_map_, cf_wal_keys_);
1068
1069 Status s = batch.Iterate(&handler);
1070 if (!s.ok()) {
1071 // TODO(AR) is this ok?
1072 return WalProcessingOption::kCorruptedRecord;
1073 }
1074
1075 return WalProcessingOption::kContinueProcessing;
1076 }
1077
1078 const char* Name() const override {
1079 return "WalFilterTestWithColumnFamilies";
1080 }
1081
1082 const std::map<uint32_t, std::vector<std::string>>& GetColumnFamilyKeys() {
1083 return cf_wal_keys_;
1084 }
1085
1086 const std::map<std::string, uint32_t>& GetColumnFamilyNameIdMap() {
1087 return cf_name_id_map_;
1088 }
1089 };
1090
1091 std::vector<std::vector<std::string>> batch_keys_pre_flush(3);
1092
1093 batch_keys_pre_flush[0].push_back("key1");
1094 batch_keys_pre_flush[0].push_back("key2");
1095 batch_keys_pre_flush[1].push_back("key3");
1096 batch_keys_pre_flush[1].push_back("key4");
1097 batch_keys_pre_flush[2].push_back("key5");
1098 batch_keys_pre_flush[2].push_back("key6");
1099
1100 Options options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
1101 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1102 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
1103
1104 // Write given keys in given batches
1105 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys_pre_flush.size(); i++) {
1106 WriteBatch batch;
1107 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys_pre_flush[i].size(); j++) {
1108 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[0], batch_keys_pre_flush[i][j],
1109 DummyString(1024)));
1110 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[1], batch_keys_pre_flush[i][j],
1111 DummyString(1024)));
1112 }
1113 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Write(WriteOptions(), &batch));
1114 }
1115
1116 // Flush default column-family
1117 ASSERT_OK(db_->Flush(FlushOptions(), handles_[0]));
1118
1119 // Do some more writes
1120 std::vector<std::vector<std::string>> batch_keys_post_flush(3);
1121
1122 batch_keys_post_flush[0].push_back("key7");
1123 batch_keys_post_flush[0].push_back("key8");
1124 batch_keys_post_flush[1].push_back("key9");
1125 batch_keys_post_flush[1].push_back("key10");
1126 batch_keys_post_flush[2].push_back("key11");
1127 batch_keys_post_flush[2].push_back("key12");
1128
1129 // Write given keys in given batches
1130 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys_post_flush.size(); i++) {
1131 WriteBatch batch;
1132 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys_post_flush[i].size(); j++) {
1133 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[0], batch_keys_post_flush[i][j],
1134 DummyString(1024)));
1135 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(handles_[1], batch_keys_post_flush[i][j],
1136 DummyString(1024)));
1137 }
1138 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Write(WriteOptions(), &batch));
1139 }
1140
1141 // On Recovery we should only find the second batch applicable to default CF
1142 // But both batches applicable to pikachu CF
1143
1144 // Create a test filter that would add extra keys
1145 TestWalFilterWithColumnFamilies test_wal_filter_column_families;
1146
1147 // Reopen database with option to use WAL filter
1148 options = OptionsForLogIterTest();
1149 options.wal_filter = &test_wal_filter_column_families;
1150 Status status = TryReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options);
1151 ASSERT_TRUE(status.ok());
1152
1153 // verify that handles_[0] only has post_flush keys
1154 // while handles_[1] has pre and post flush keys
1155 auto cf_wal_keys = test_wal_filter_column_families.GetColumnFamilyKeys();
1156 auto name_id_map = test_wal_filter_column_families.GetColumnFamilyNameIdMap();
1157 size_t index = 0;
1158 auto keys_cf = cf_wal_keys[name_id_map[kDefaultColumnFamilyName]];
1159 // default column-family, only post_flush keys are expected
1160 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys_post_flush.size(); i++) {
1161 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys_post_flush[i].size(); j++) {
1162 Slice key_from_the_log(keys_cf[index++]);
1163 Slice batch_key(batch_keys_post_flush[i][j]);
1164 ASSERT_EQ(key_from_the_log.compare(batch_key), 0);
1165 }
1166 }
1167 ASSERT_EQ(index, keys_cf.size());
1168
1169 index = 0;
1170 keys_cf = cf_wal_keys[name_id_map["pikachu"]];
1171 // pikachu column-family, all keys are expected
1172 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys_pre_flush.size(); i++) {
1173 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys_pre_flush[i].size(); j++) {
1174 Slice key_from_the_log(keys_cf[index++]);
1175 Slice batch_key(batch_keys_pre_flush[i][j]);
1176 ASSERT_EQ(key_from_the_log.compare(batch_key), 0);
1177 }
1178 }
1179
1180 for (size_t i = 0; i < batch_keys_post_flush.size(); i++) {
1181 for (size_t j = 0; j < batch_keys_post_flush[i].size(); j++) {
1182 Slice key_from_the_log(keys_cf[index++]);
1183 Slice batch_key(batch_keys_post_flush[i][j]);
1184 ASSERT_EQ(key_from_the_log.compare(batch_key), 0);
1185 }
1186 }
1187 ASSERT_EQ(index, keys_cf.size());
1188}
1189
1190TEST_F(DBTest2, PresetCompressionDict) {
1191 // Verifies that compression ratio improves when dictionary is enabled, and
1192 // improves even further when the dictionary is trained by ZSTD.
1193 const size_t kBlockSizeBytes = 4 << 10;
1194 const size_t kL0FileBytes = 128 << 10;
1195 const size_t kApproxPerBlockOverheadBytes = 50;
1196 const int kNumL0Files = 5;
1197
1198 Options options;
1199 // Make sure to use any custom env that the test is configured with.
1200 options.env = CurrentOptions().env;
1201 options.allow_concurrent_memtable_write = false;
1202 options.arena_block_size = kBlockSizeBytes;
1203 options.create_if_missing = true;
1204 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
1205 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = kNumL0Files;
1206 options.memtable_factory.reset(
1207 test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kL0FileBytes / kBlockSizeBytes));
1208 options.num_levels = 2;
1209 options.target_file_size_base = kL0FileBytes;
1210 options.target_file_size_multiplier = 2;
1211 options.write_buffer_size = kL0FileBytes;
1212 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
1213 table_options.block_size = kBlockSizeBytes;
1214 std::vector<CompressionType> compression_types;
1215 if (Zlib_Supported()) {
1216 compression_types.push_back(kZlibCompression);
1217 }
1218#if LZ4_VERSION_NUMBER >= 10400 // r124+
1219 compression_types.push_back(kLZ4Compression);
1220 compression_types.push_back(kLZ4HCCompression);
1221#endif // LZ4_VERSION_NUMBER >= 10400
1222 if (ZSTD_Supported()) {
1223 compression_types.push_back(kZSTD);
1224 }
1225
1226 enum DictionaryTypes : int {
1227 kWithoutDict,
1228 kWithDict,
1229 kWithZSTDfinalizeDict,
1230 kWithZSTDTrainedDict,
1231 kDictEnd,
1232 };
1233
1234 for (auto compression_type : compression_types) {
1235 options.compression = compression_type;
1236 size_t bytes_without_dict = 0;
1237 size_t bytes_with_dict = 0;
1238 size_t bytes_with_zstd_finalize_dict = 0;
1239 size_t bytes_with_zstd_trained_dict = 0;
1240 for (int i = kWithoutDict; i < kDictEnd; i++) {
1241 // First iteration: compress without preset dictionary
1242 // Second iteration: compress with preset dictionary
1243 // Third iteration (zstd only): compress with zstd-trained dictionary
1244 //
1245 // To make sure the compression dictionary has the intended effect, we
1246 // verify the compressed size is smaller in successive iterations. Also in
1247 // the non-first iterations, verify the data we get out is the same data
1248 // we put in.
1249 switch (i) {
1250 case kWithoutDict:
1251 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = 0;
1252 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = 0;
1253 break;
1254 case kWithDict:
1255 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kBlockSizeBytes;
1256 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = 0;
1257 break;
1258 case kWithZSTDfinalizeDict:
1259 if (compression_type != kZSTD ||
1260 !ZSTD_FinalizeDictionarySupported()) {
1261 continue;
1262 }
1263 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kBlockSizeBytes;
1264 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = kL0FileBytes;
1265 options.compression_opts.use_zstd_dict_trainer = false;
1266 break;
1267 case kWithZSTDTrainedDict:
1268 if (compression_type != kZSTD || !ZSTD_TrainDictionarySupported()) {
1269 continue;
1270 }
1271 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kBlockSizeBytes;
1272 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = kL0FileBytes;
1273 options.compression_opts.use_zstd_dict_trainer = true;
1274 break;
1275 default:
1276 assert(false);
1277 }
1278
1279 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
1280 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1281 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
1282 Random rnd(301);
1283 std::string seq_datas[10];
1284 for (int j = 0; j < 10; ++j) {
1285 seq_datas[j] =
1286 rnd.RandomString(kBlockSizeBytes - kApproxPerBlockOverheadBytes);
1287 }
1288
1289 ASSERT_EQ(0, NumTableFilesAtLevel(0, 1));
1290 for (int j = 0; j < kNumL0Files; ++j) {
1291 for (size_t k = 0; k < kL0FileBytes / kBlockSizeBytes + 1; ++k) {
1292 auto key_num = j * (kL0FileBytes / kBlockSizeBytes) + k;
1293 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, Key(static_cast<int>(key_num)),
1294 seq_datas[(key_num / 10) % 10]));
1295 }
1296 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable(handles_[1]));
1297 ASSERT_EQ(j + 1, NumTableFilesAtLevel(0, 1));
1298 }
1299 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_CompactRange(0, nullptr, nullptr, handles_[1],
1300 true /* disallow_trivial_move */));
1301 ASSERT_EQ(0, NumTableFilesAtLevel(0, 1));
1302 ASSERT_GT(NumTableFilesAtLevel(1, 1), 0);
1303
1304 // Get the live sst files size
1305 size_t total_sst_bytes = TotalSize(1);
1306 if (i == kWithoutDict) {
1307 bytes_without_dict = total_sst_bytes;
1308 } else if (i == kWithDict) {
1309 bytes_with_dict = total_sst_bytes;
1310 } else if (i == kWithZSTDfinalizeDict) {
1311 bytes_with_zstd_finalize_dict = total_sst_bytes;
1312 } else if (i == kWithZSTDTrainedDict) {
1313 bytes_with_zstd_trained_dict = total_sst_bytes;
1314 }
1315
1316 for (size_t j = 0; j < kNumL0Files * (kL0FileBytes / kBlockSizeBytes);
1317 j++) {
1318 ASSERT_EQ(seq_datas[(j / 10) % 10], Get(1, Key(static_cast<int>(j))));
1319 }
1320 if (i == kWithDict) {
1321 ASSERT_GT(bytes_without_dict, bytes_with_dict);
1322 } else if (i == kWithZSTDTrainedDict) {
1323 // In zstd compression, it is sometimes possible that using a finalized
1324 // dictionary does not get as good a compression ratio as raw content
1325 // dictionary. But using a dictionary should always get better
1326 // compression ratio than not using one.
1327 ASSERT_TRUE(bytes_with_dict > bytes_with_zstd_finalize_dict ||
1328 bytes_without_dict > bytes_with_zstd_finalize_dict);
1329 } else if (i == kWithZSTDTrainedDict) {
1330 // In zstd compression, it is sometimes possible that using a trained
1331 // dictionary does not get as good a compression ratio as without
1332 // training.
1333 // But using a dictionary (with or without training) should always get
1334 // better compression ratio than not using one.
1335 ASSERT_TRUE(bytes_with_dict > bytes_with_zstd_trained_dict ||
1336 bytes_without_dict > bytes_with_zstd_trained_dict);
1337 }
1338
1339 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1340 }
1341 }
1342}
1343
1344TEST_F(DBTest2, PresetCompressionDictLocality) {
1345 if (!ZSTD_Supported()) {
1346 return;
1347 }
1348 // Verifies that compression dictionary is generated from local data. The
1349 // verification simply checks all output SSTs have different compression
1350 // dictionaries. We do not verify effectiveness as that'd likely be flaky in
1351 // the future.
1352 const int kNumEntriesPerFile = 1 << 10; // 1KB
1353 const int kNumBytesPerEntry = 1 << 10; // 1KB
1354 const int kNumFiles = 4;
1355 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1356 options.compression = kZSTD;
1357 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = 1 << 14; // 16KB
1358 options.compression_opts.zstd_max_train_bytes = 1 << 18; // 256KB
1359 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
1360 options.target_file_size_base = kNumEntriesPerFile * kNumBytesPerEntry;
1361 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
1362 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
1363 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1364 Reopen(options);
1365
1366 Random rnd(301);
1367 for (int i = 0; i < kNumFiles; ++i) {
1368 for (int j = 0; j < kNumEntriesPerFile; ++j) {
1369 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * kNumEntriesPerFile + j),
1370 rnd.RandomString(kNumBytesPerEntry)));
1371 }
1372 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1373 MoveFilesToLevel(1);
1374 ASSERT_EQ(NumTableFilesAtLevel(1), i + 1);
1375 }
1376
1377 // Store all the dictionaries generated during a full compaction.
1378 std::vector<std::string> compression_dicts;
1379 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1380 "BlockBasedTableBuilder::WriteCompressionDictBlock:RawDict",
1381 [&](void* arg) {
1382 compression_dicts.emplace_back(static_cast<Slice*>(arg)->ToString());
1383 });
1384 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1385 CompactRangeOptions compact_range_opts;
1386 compact_range_opts.bottommost_level_compaction =
1387 BottommostLevelCompaction::kForceOptimized;
1388 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(compact_range_opts, nullptr, nullptr));
1389
1390 // Dictionary compression should not be so good as to compress four totally
1391 // random files into one. If it does then there's probably something wrong
1392 // with the test.
1393 ASSERT_GT(NumTableFilesAtLevel(1), 1);
1394
1395 // Furthermore, there should be one compression dictionary generated per file.
1396 // And they should all be different from each other.
1397 ASSERT_EQ(NumTableFilesAtLevel(1),
1398 static_cast<int>(compression_dicts.size()));
1399 for (size_t i = 1; i < compression_dicts.size(); ++i) {
1400 std::string& a = compression_dicts[i - 1];
1401 std::string& b = compression_dicts[i];
1402 size_t alen = a.size();
1403 size_t blen = b.size();
1404 ASSERT_TRUE(alen != blen || memcmp(a.data(), b.data(), alen) != 0);
1405 }
1406}
1407
1408class PresetCompressionDictTest
1409 : public DBTestBase,
1410 public testing::WithParamInterface<std::tuple<CompressionType, bool>> {
1411 public:
1412 PresetCompressionDictTest()
1413 : DBTestBase("db_test2", false /* env_do_fsync */),
1414 compression_type_(std::get<0>(GetParam())),
1415 bottommost_(std::get<1>(GetParam())) {}
1416
1417 protected:
1418 const CompressionType compression_type_;
1419 const bool bottommost_;
1420};
1421
1422INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(
1423 DBTest2, PresetCompressionDictTest,
1424 ::testing::Combine(::testing::ValuesIn(GetSupportedDictCompressions()),
1425 ::testing::Bool()));
1426
1427TEST_P(PresetCompressionDictTest, Flush) {
1428 // Verifies that dictionary is generated and written during flush only when
1429 // `ColumnFamilyOptions::compression` enables dictionary. Also verifies the
1430 // size of the dictionary is within expectations according to the limit on
1431 // buffering set by `CompressionOptions::max_dict_buffer_bytes`.
1432 const size_t kValueLen = 256;
1433 const size_t kKeysPerFile = 1 << 10;
1434 const size_t kDictLen = 16 << 10;
1435 const size_t kBlockLen = 4 << 10;
1436
1437 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1438 if (bottommost_) {
1439 options.bottommost_compression = compression_type_;
1440 options.bottommost_compression_opts.enabled = true;
1441 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1442 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1443 } else {
1444 options.compression = compression_type_;
1445 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1446 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1447 }
1448 options.memtable_factory.reset(test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kKeysPerFile));
1449 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
1450 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
1451 bbto.block_size = kBlockLen;
1452 bbto.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
1453 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
1454 Reopen(options);
1455
1456 Random rnd(301);
1457 for (size_t i = 0; i <= kKeysPerFile; ++i) {
1458 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(static_cast<int>(i)), rnd.RandomString(kValueLen)));
1459 }
1460 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
1461
1462 // We can use `BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT` to detect whether a
1463 // compression dictionary exists since dictionaries would be preloaded when
1464 // the flush finishes.
1465 if (bottommost_) {
1466 // Flush is never considered bottommost. This should change in the future
1467 // since flushed files may have nothing underneath them, like the one in
1468 // this test case.
1469 ASSERT_EQ(
1470 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1471 0);
1472 } else {
1473 ASSERT_GT(
1474 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1475 0);
1476 // TODO(ajkr): fix the below assertion to work with ZSTD. The expectation on
1477 // number of bytes needs to be adjusted in case the cached block is in
1478 // ZSTD's digested dictionary format.
1479 if (compression_type_ != kZSTD &&
1480 compression_type_ != kZSTDNotFinalCompression) {
1481 // Although we limited buffering to `kBlockLen`, there may be up to two
1482 // blocks of data included in the dictionary since we only check limit
1483 // after each block is built.
1484 ASSERT_LE(TestGetTickerCount(options,
1485 BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1486 2 * kBlockLen);
1487 }
1488 }
1489}
1490
1491TEST_P(PresetCompressionDictTest, CompactNonBottommost) {
1492 // Verifies that dictionary is generated and written during compaction to
1493 // non-bottommost level only when `ColumnFamilyOptions::compression` enables
1494 // dictionary. Also verifies the size of the dictionary is within expectations
1495 // according to the limit on buffering set by
1496 // `CompressionOptions::max_dict_buffer_bytes`.
1497 const size_t kValueLen = 256;
1498 const size_t kKeysPerFile = 1 << 10;
1499 const size_t kDictLen = 16 << 10;
1500 const size_t kBlockLen = 4 << 10;
1501
1502 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1503 if (bottommost_) {
1504 options.bottommost_compression = compression_type_;
1505 options.bottommost_compression_opts.enabled = true;
1506 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1507 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1508 } else {
1509 options.compression = compression_type_;
1510 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1511 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1512 }
1513 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
1514 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
1515 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
1516 bbto.block_size = kBlockLen;
1517 bbto.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
1518 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
1519 Reopen(options);
1520
1521 Random rnd(301);
1522 for (size_t j = 0; j <= kKeysPerFile; ++j) {
1523 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(static_cast<int>(j)), rnd.RandomString(kValueLen)));
1524 }
1525 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1526 MoveFilesToLevel(2);
1527
1528 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
1529 for (size_t j = 0; j <= kKeysPerFile; ++j) {
1530 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(static_cast<int>(j)), rnd.RandomString(kValueLen)));
1531 }
1532 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1533 }
1534 ASSERT_EQ("2,0,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
1535
1536 uint64_t prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted =
1537 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT);
1538 // This L0->L1 compaction merges the two L0 files into L1. The produced L1
1539 // file is not bottommost due to the existing L2 file covering the same key-
1540 // range.
1541 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_CompactRange(0, nullptr, nullptr));
1542 ASSERT_EQ("0,1,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
1543 // We can use `BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT` to detect whether a
1544 // compression dictionary exists since dictionaries would be preloaded when
1545 // the compaction finishes.
1546 if (bottommost_) {
1547 ASSERT_EQ(
1548 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1549 prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted);
1550 } else {
1551 ASSERT_GT(
1552 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1553 prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted);
1554 // TODO(ajkr): fix the below assertion to work with ZSTD. The expectation on
1555 // number of bytes needs to be adjusted in case the cached block is in
1556 // ZSTD's digested dictionary format.
1557 if (compression_type_ != kZSTD &&
1558 compression_type_ != kZSTDNotFinalCompression) {
1559 // Although we limited buffering to `kBlockLen`, there may be up to two
1560 // blocks of data included in the dictionary since we only check limit
1561 // after each block is built.
1562 ASSERT_LE(TestGetTickerCount(options,
1563 BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1564 prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted + 2 * kBlockLen);
1565 }
1566 }
1567}

1569TEST_P(PresetCompressionDictTest, CompactBottommost) {
1570 // Verifies that dictionary is generated and written during compaction to
1571 // non-bottommost level only when either `ColumnFamilyOptions::compression` or
1572 // `ColumnFamilyOptions::bottommost_compression` enables dictionary. Also
1573 // verifies the size of the dictionary is within expectations according to the
1574 // limit on buffering set by `CompressionOptions::max_dict_buffer_bytes`.
1575 const size_t kValueLen = 256;
1576 const size_t kKeysPerFile = 1 << 10;
1577 const size_t kDictLen = 16 << 10;
1578 const size_t kBlockLen = 4 << 10;
1579
1580 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1581 if (bottommost_) {
1582 options.bottommost_compression = compression_type_;
1583 options.bottommost_compression_opts.enabled = true;
1584 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1585 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1586 } else {
1587 options.compression = compression_type_;
1588 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kDictLen;
1589 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kBlockLen;
1590 }
1591 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
1592 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
1593 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
1594 bbto.block_size = kBlockLen;
1595 bbto.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
1596 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
1597 Reopen(options);
1598
1599 Random rnd(301);
1600 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
1601 for (size_t j = 0; j <= kKeysPerFile; ++j) {
1602 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(static_cast<int>(j)), rnd.RandomString(kValueLen)));
1603 }
1604 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1605 }
1606 ASSERT_EQ("2", FilesPerLevel(0));
1607
1608 uint64_t prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted =
1609 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT);
1610 CompactRangeOptions cro;
1611 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
1612 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
1613 ASSERT_GT(
1614 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1615 prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted);
1616 // TODO(ajkr): fix the below assertion to work with ZSTD. The expectation on
1617 // number of bytes needs to be adjusted in case the cached block is in ZSTD's
1618 // digested dictionary format.
1619 if (compression_type_ != kZSTD &&
1620 compression_type_ != kZSTDNotFinalCompression) {
1621 // Although we limited buffering to `kBlockLen`, there may be up to two
1622 // blocks of data included in the dictionary since we only check limit after
1623 // each block is built.
1624 ASSERT_LE(
1625 TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_COMPRESSION_DICT_BYTES_INSERT),
1626 prev_compression_dict_bytes_inserted + 2 * kBlockLen);
1627 }
1628}
1629
1630class CompactionCompressionListener : public EventListener {
1631 public:
1632 explicit CompactionCompressionListener(Options* db_options)
1633 : db_options_(db_options) {}
1634
1635 void OnCompactionCompleted(DB* db, const CompactionJobInfo& ci) override {
1636 // Figure out last level with files
1637 int bottommost_level = 0;
1638 for (int level = 0; level < db->NumberLevels(); level++) {
1639 std::string files_at_level;
1640 ASSERT_TRUE(
1641 db->GetProperty("rocksdb.num-files-at-level" + std::to_string(level),
1642 &files_at_level));
1643 if (files_at_level != "0") {
1644 bottommost_level = level;
1645 }
1646 }
1647
1648 if (db_options_->bottommost_compression != kDisableCompressionOption &&
1649 ci.output_level == bottommost_level) {
1650 ASSERT_EQ(ci.compression, db_options_->bottommost_compression);
1651 } else if (db_options_->compression_per_level.size() != 0) {
1652 ASSERT_EQ(ci.compression,
1653 db_options_->compression_per_level[ci.output_level]);
1654 } else {
1655 ASSERT_EQ(ci.compression, db_options_->compression);
1656 }
1657 max_level_checked = std::max(max_level_checked, ci.output_level);
1658 }
1659
1660 int max_level_checked = 0;
1661 const Options* db_options_;
1662};
1663
1664enum CompressionFailureType {
1665 kTestCompressionFail,
1666 kTestDecompressionFail,
1667 kTestDecompressionCorruption
1668};
1669
1670class CompressionFailuresTest
1671 : public DBTest2,
1672 public testing::WithParamInterface<std::tuple<
1673 CompressionFailureType, CompressionType, uint32_t, uint32_t>> {
1674 public:
1675 CompressionFailuresTest() {
1676 std::tie(compression_failure_type_, compression_type_,
1677 compression_max_dict_bytes_, compression_parallel_threads_) =
1678 GetParam();
1679 }
1680
1681 CompressionFailureType compression_failure_type_ = kTestCompressionFail;
1682 CompressionType compression_type_ = kNoCompression;
1683 uint32_t compression_max_dict_bytes_ = 0;
1684 uint32_t compression_parallel_threads_ = 0;
1685};
1686
1687INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(
1688 DBTest2, CompressionFailuresTest,
1689 ::testing::Combine(::testing::Values(kTestCompressionFail,
1690 kTestDecompressionFail,
1691 kTestDecompressionCorruption),
1692 ::testing::ValuesIn(GetSupportedCompressions()),
1693 ::testing::Values(0, 10), ::testing::Values(1, 4)));
1694
1695TEST_P(CompressionFailuresTest, CompressionFailures) {
1696 if (compression_type_ == kNoCompression) {
1697 return;
1698 }
1699
1700 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1701 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
1702 options.max_bytes_for_level_base = 1024;
1703 options.max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 2;
1704 options.num_levels = 7;
1705 options.max_background_compactions = 1;
1706 options.target_file_size_base = 512;
1707
1708 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
1709 table_options.block_size = 512;
1710 table_options.verify_compression = true;
1711 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1712
1713 options.compression = compression_type_;
1714 options.compression_opts.parallel_threads = compression_parallel_threads_;
1715 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = compression_max_dict_bytes_;
1716 options.bottommost_compression_opts.parallel_threads =
1717 compression_parallel_threads_;
1718 options.bottommost_compression_opts.max_dict_bytes =
1719 compression_max_dict_bytes_;
1720
1721 if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestCompressionFail) {
1722 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1723 "CompressData:TamperWithReturnValue", [](void* arg) {
1724 bool* ret = static_cast<bool*>(arg);
1725 *ret = false;
1726 });
1727 } else if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestDecompressionFail) {
1728 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1729 "UncompressBlockData:TamperWithReturnValue", [](void* arg) {
1730 Status* ret = static_cast<Status*>(arg);
1731 ASSERT_OK(*ret);
1732 *ret = Status::Corruption("kTestDecompressionFail");
1733 });
1734 } else if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestDecompressionCorruption) {
1735 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1736 "UncompressBlockData:"
1737 "TamperWithDecompressionOutput",
1738 [](void* arg) {
1739 BlockContents* contents = static_cast<BlockContents*>(arg);
1740 // Ensure uncompressed data != original data
1741 const size_t len = contents->data.size() + 1;
1742 std::unique_ptr<char[]> fake_data(new char[len]());
1743 *contents = BlockContents(std::move(fake_data), len);
1744 });
1745 }
1746
1747 std::map<std::string, std::string> key_value_written;
1748
1749 const int kKeySize = 5;
1750 const int kValUnitSize = 16;
1751 const int kValSize = 256;
1752 Random rnd(405);
1753
1754 Status s = Status::OK();
1755
1756 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1757 // Write 10 random files
1758 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
1759 for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
1760 std::string key = rnd.RandomString(kKeySize);
1761 // Ensure good compression ratio
1762 std::string valueUnit = rnd.RandomString(kValUnitSize);
1763 std::string value;
1764 for (int k = 0; k < kValSize; k += kValUnitSize) {
1765 value += valueUnit;
1766 }
1767 s = Put(key, value);
1768 if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestCompressionFail) {
1769 key_value_written[key] = value;
1770 ASSERT_OK(s);
1771 }
1772 }
1773 s = Flush();
1774 if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestCompressionFail) {
1775 ASSERT_OK(s);
1776 }
1777 s = dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact();
1778 if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestCompressionFail) {
1779 ASSERT_OK(s);
1780 }
1781 if (i == 4) {
1782 // Make compression fail at the mid of table building
1783 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1784 }
1785 }
1786 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
1787
1788 if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestCompressionFail) {
1789 // Should be kNoCompression, check content consistency
1790 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> db_iter(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
1791 for (db_iter->SeekToFirst(); db_iter->Valid(); db_iter->Next()) {
1792 std::string key = db_iter->key().ToString();
1793 std::string value = db_iter->value().ToString();
1794 ASSERT_NE(key_value_written.find(key), key_value_written.end());
1795 ASSERT_EQ(key_value_written[key], value);
1796 key_value_written.erase(key);
1797 }
1798 ASSERT_OK(db_iter->status());
1799 ASSERT_EQ(0, key_value_written.size());
1800 } else if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestDecompressionFail) {
1801 ASSERT_EQ(std::string(s.getState()),
1802 "Could not decompress: kTestDecompressionFail");
1803 } else if (compression_failure_type_ == kTestDecompressionCorruption) {
1804 ASSERT_EQ(std::string(s.getState()),
1805 "Decompressed block did not match pre-compression block");
1806 }
1807}
1808
1809TEST_F(DBTest2, CompressionOptions) {
1810 if (!Zlib_Supported() || !Snappy_Supported()) {
1811 return;
1812 }
1813
1814 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1815 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
1816 options.max_bytes_for_level_base = 100;
1817 options.max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 2;
1818 options.num_levels = 7;
1819 options.max_background_compactions = 1;
1820
1821 CompactionCompressionListener* listener =
1822 new CompactionCompressionListener(&options);
1823 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
1824
1825 const int kKeySize = 5;
1826 const int kValSize = 20;
1827 Random rnd(301);
1828
1829 std::vector<uint32_t> compression_parallel_threads = {1, 4};
1830
1831 std::map<std::string, std::string> key_value_written;
1832
1833 for (int iter = 0; iter <= 2; iter++) {
1834 listener->max_level_checked = 0;
1835
1836 if (iter == 0) {
1837 // Use different compression algorithms for different levels but
1838 // always use Zlib for bottommost level
1839 options.compression_per_level = {kNoCompression, kNoCompression,
1840 kNoCompression, kSnappyCompression,
1841 kSnappyCompression, kSnappyCompression,
1842 kZlibCompression};
1843 options.compression = kNoCompression;
1844 options.bottommost_compression = kZlibCompression;
1845 } else if (iter == 1) {
1846 // Use Snappy except for bottommost level use ZLib
1847 options.compression_per_level = {};
1848 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
1849 options.bottommost_compression = kZlibCompression;
1850 } else if (iter == 2) {
1851 // Use Snappy everywhere
1852 options.compression_per_level = {};
1853 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
1854 options.bottommost_compression = kDisableCompressionOption;
1855 }
1856
1857 for (auto num_threads : compression_parallel_threads) {
1858 options.compression_opts.parallel_threads = num_threads;
1859 options.bottommost_compression_opts.parallel_threads = num_threads;
1860
1861 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1862 // Write 10 random files
1863 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
1864 for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
1865 std::string key = rnd.RandomString(kKeySize);
1866 std::string value = rnd.RandomString(kValSize);
1867 key_value_written[key] = value;
1868 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, value));
1869 }
1870 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1871 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
1872 }
1873
1874 // Make sure that we wrote enough to check all 7 levels
1875 ASSERT_EQ(listener->max_level_checked, 6);
1876
1877 // Make sure database content is the same as key_value_written
1878 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> db_iter(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
1879 for (db_iter->SeekToFirst(); db_iter->Valid(); db_iter->Next()) {
1880 std::string key = db_iter->key().ToString();
1881 std::string value = db_iter->value().ToString();
1882 ASSERT_NE(key_value_written.find(key), key_value_written.end());
1883 ASSERT_EQ(key_value_written[key], value);
1884 key_value_written.erase(key);
1885 }
1886 ASSERT_OK(db_iter->status());
1887 ASSERT_EQ(0, key_value_written.size());
1888 }
1889 }
1890}

1892class CompactionStallTestListener : public EventListener {
1893 public:
1894 CompactionStallTestListener()
1895 : compacting_files_cnt_(0), compacted_files_cnt_(0) {}
1896
1897 void OnCompactionBegin(DB* /*db*/, const CompactionJobInfo& ci) override {
1898 ASSERT_EQ(ci.cf_name, "default");
1899 ASSERT_EQ(ci.base_input_level, 0);
1900 ASSERT_EQ(ci.compaction_reason, CompactionReason::kLevelL0FilesNum);
1901 compacting_files_cnt_ += ci.input_files.size();
1902 }
1903
1904 void OnCompactionCompleted(DB* /*db*/, const CompactionJobInfo& ci) override {
1905 ASSERT_EQ(ci.cf_name, "default");
1906 ASSERT_EQ(ci.base_input_level, 0);
1907 ASSERT_EQ(ci.compaction_reason, CompactionReason::kLevelL0FilesNum);
1908 compacted_files_cnt_ += ci.input_files.size();
1909 }
1910
1911 std::atomic<size_t> compacting_files_cnt_;
1912 std::atomic<size_t> compacted_files_cnt_;
1913};

1915TEST_F(DBTest2, CompactionStall) {
1916 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
1917 {{"DBImpl::BGWorkCompaction", "DBTest2::CompactionStall:0"},
1918 {"DBImpl::BGWorkCompaction", "DBTest2::CompactionStall:1"},
1919 {"DBTest2::CompactionStall:2",
1920 "DBImpl::NotifyOnCompactionBegin::UnlockMutex"},
1921 {"DBTest2::CompactionStall:3",
1922 "DBImpl::NotifyOnCompactionCompleted::UnlockMutex"}});
1923 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1924
1925 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1926 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 4;
1927 options.max_background_compactions = 40;
1928 CompactionStallTestListener* listener = new CompactionStallTestListener();
1929 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
1930 DestroyAndReopen(options);
1931 // make sure all background compaction jobs can be scheduled
1932 auto stop_token =
1933 dbfull()->TEST_write_controler().GetCompactionPressureToken();
1934
1935 Random rnd(301);
1936
1937 // 4 Files in L0
1938 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1939 for (int j = 0; j < 10; j++) {
1940 ASSERT_OK(Put(rnd.RandomString(10), rnd.RandomString(10)));
1941 }
1942 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1943 }
1944
1945 // Wait for compaction to be triggered
1946 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::CompactionStall:0");
1947
1948 // Clear "DBImpl::BGWorkCompaction" SYNC_POINT since we want to hold it again
1949 // at DBTest2::CompactionStall::1
1950 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearTrace();
1951
1952 // Another 6 L0 files to trigger compaction again
1953 for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
1954 for (int j = 0; j < 10; j++) {
1955 ASSERT_OK(Put(rnd.RandomString(10), rnd.RandomString(10)));
1956 }
1957 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1958 }
1959
1960 // Wait for another compaction to be triggered
1961 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::CompactionStall:1");
1962
1963 // Hold NotifyOnCompactionBegin in the unlock mutex section
1964 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::CompactionStall:2");
1965
1966 // Hold NotifyOnCompactionCompleted in the unlock mutex section
1967 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::CompactionStall:3");
1968
1969 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
1970 ASSERT_LT(NumTableFilesAtLevel(0),
1971 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger);
1972 ASSERT_GT(listener->compacted_files_cnt_.load(),
1973 10 - options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger);
1974 ASSERT_EQ(listener->compacting_files_cnt_.load(),
1975 listener->compacted_files_cnt_.load());
1976
1977 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
1978}

1996TEST_F(DBTest2, DuplicateSnapshot) {
1997 Options options;
1998 options = CurrentOptions(options);
1999 std::vector<const Snapshot*> snapshots;
2000 DBImpl* dbi = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db_);
2001 SequenceNumber oldest_ww_snap, first_ww_snap;
2002
2003 ASSERT_OK(Put("k", "v")); // inc seq
2004 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
2005 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
2006 ASSERT_OK(Put("k", "v")); // inc seq
2007 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
2008 snapshots.push_back(dbi->GetSnapshotForWriteConflictBoundary());
2009 first_ww_snap = snapshots.back()->GetSequenceNumber();
2010 ASSERT_OK(Put("k", "v")); // inc seq
2011 snapshots.push_back(dbi->GetSnapshotForWriteConflictBoundary());
2012 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
2013 ASSERT_OK(Put("k", "v")); // inc seq
2014 snapshots.push_back(db_->GetSnapshot());
2015
2016 {
2017 InstrumentedMutexLock l(dbi->mutex());
2018 auto seqs = dbi->snapshots().GetAll(&oldest_ww_snap);
2019 ASSERT_EQ(seqs.size(), 4); // duplicates are not counted
2020 ASSERT_EQ(oldest_ww_snap, first_ww_snap);
2021 }
2022
2023 for (auto s : snapshots) {
2024 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s);
2025 }
2026}
