2028class PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest
2029 : public DBTestBase,
2030 public testing::WithParamInterface<std::tuple<bool, bool>> {
2031 public:
2032 PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest()
2033 : DBTestBase("db_pin_l0_index_bloom_test", /*env_do_fsync=*/true) {}
2034 void SetUp() override {
2035 infinite_max_files_ = std::get<0>(GetParam());
2036 disallow_preload_ = std::get<1>(GetParam());
2037 }
2038
2039 void CreateTwoLevels(Options* options, bool close_afterwards) {
2040 if (infinite_max_files_) {
2041 options->max_open_files = -1;
2042 }
2043 options->create_if_missing = true;
2044 options->statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2045 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
2046 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
2047 table_options.pin_l0_filter_and_index_blocks_in_cache = true;
2048 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(20));
2049 options->table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2050 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, *options);
2051
2052 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "a", "begin"));
2053 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "z", "end"));
2054 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
2055 // move this table to L1
2056 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_CompactRange(0, nullptr, nullptr, handles_[1]));
2057 ASSERT_EQ(1, NumTableFilesAtLevel(1, 1));
2058
2059 // reset block cache
2060 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(64 * 1024);
2061 options->table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2062 ASSERT_OK(TryReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, *options));
2063 // create new table at L0
2064 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "a2", "begin2"));
2065 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "z2", "end2"));
2066 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
2067
2068 if (close_afterwards) {
2069 Close(); // This ensures that there is no ref to block cache entries
2070 }
2071 table_options.block_cache->EraseUnRefEntries();
2072 }
2073
2074 bool infinite_max_files_;
2075 bool disallow_preload_;
2076};
2077
2078TEST_P(PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest,
2079 IndexAndFilterBlocksOfNewTableAddedToCacheWithPinning) {
2080 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2081 if (infinite_max_files_) {
2082 options.max_open_files = -1;
2083 }
2084 options.create_if_missing = true;
2085 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2086 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
2087 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
2088 table_options.pin_l0_filter_and_index_blocks_in_cache = true;
2089 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(20));
2090 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2091 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
2092
2093 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "key", "val"));
2094 // Create a new table.
2095 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
2096
2097 // index/filter blocks added to block cache right after table creation.
2098 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2099 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2100 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2101 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2102
2103 // only index/filter were added
2104 ASSERT_EQ(2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_ADD));
2105 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2106
2107 // Miss and hit count should remain the same, they're all pinned.
2108 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->KeyMayExist(ReadOptions(), handles_[1], "key", nullptr));
2109 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2110 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2111 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2112 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2113
2114 // Miss and hit count should remain the same, they're all pinned.
2115 std::string value = Get(1, "key");
2116 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2117 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2118 ASSERT_EQ(1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2119 ASSERT_EQ(0, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2120}
2121
2122TEST_P(PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest,
2123 MultiLevelIndexAndFilterBlocksCachedWithPinning) {
2124 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2125 PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest::CreateTwoLevels(&options, false);
2126 // get base cache values
2127 uint64_t fm = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS);
2128 uint64_t fh = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT);
2129 uint64_t im = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS);
2130 uint64_t ih = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT);
2131
2132 std::string value;
2133 // this should be read from L0
2134 // so cache values don't change
2135 value = Get(1, "a2");
2136 ASSERT_EQ(fm, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2137 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2138 ASSERT_EQ(im, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2139 ASSERT_EQ(ih, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2140
2141 // this should be read from L1
2142 // the file is opened, prefetching results in a cache filter miss
2143 // the block is loaded and added to the cache,
2144 // then the get results in a cache hit for L1
2145 // When we have inifinite max_files, there is still cache miss because we have
2146 // reset the block cache
2147 value = Get(1, "a");
2148 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2149 ASSERT_EQ(im + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2150}
2151
2152TEST_P(PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest, DisablePrefetchingNonL0IndexAndFilter) {
2153 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2154 // This ensures that db does not ref anything in the block cache, so
2155 // EraseUnRefEntries could clear them up.
2156 bool close_afterwards = true;
2157 PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest::CreateTwoLevels(&options, close_afterwards);
2158
2159 // Get base cache values
2160 uint64_t fm = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS);
2161 uint64_t fh = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT);
2162 uint64_t im = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS);
2163 uint64_t ih = TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT);
2164
2165 if (disallow_preload_) {
2166 // Now we have two files. We narrow the max open files to allow 3 entries
2167 // so that preloading SST files won't happen.
2168 options.max_open_files = 13;
2169 // RocksDB sanitize max open files to at least 20. Modify it back.
2170 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2171 "SanitizeOptions::AfterChangeMaxOpenFiles", [&](void* arg) {
2172 int* max_open_files = static_cast<int*>(arg);
2173 *max_open_files = 13;
2174 });
2175 }
2176 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2177
2178 // Reopen database. If max_open_files is set as -1, table readers will be
2179 // preloaded. This will trigger a BlockBasedTable::Open() and prefetch
2180 // L0 index and filter. Level 1's prefetching is disabled in DB::Open()
2181 ASSERT_OK(TryReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "pikachu"}, options));
2182
2183 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2184
2185 if (!disallow_preload_) {
2186 // After reopen, cache miss are increased by one because we read (and only
2187 // read) filter and index on L0
2188 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2189 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2190 ASSERT_EQ(im + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2191 ASSERT_EQ(ih, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2192 } else {
2193 // If max_open_files is not -1, we do not preload table readers, so there is
2194 // no change.
2195 ASSERT_EQ(fm, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2196 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2197 ASSERT_EQ(im, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2198 ASSERT_EQ(ih, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2199 }
2200 std::string value;
2201 // this should be read from L0
2202 value = Get(1, "a2");
2203 // If max_open_files is -1, we have pinned index and filter in Rep, so there
2204 // will not be changes in index and filter misses or hits. If max_open_files
2205 // is not -1, Get() will open a TableReader and prefetch index and filter.
2206 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2207 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2208 ASSERT_EQ(im + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2209 ASSERT_EQ(ih, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2210
2211 // this should be read from L1
2212 value = Get(1, "a");
2213 if (!disallow_preload_) {
2214 // In infinite max files case, there's a cache miss in executing Get()
2215 // because index and filter are not prefetched before.
2216 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2217 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2218 ASSERT_EQ(im + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2219 ASSERT_EQ(ih, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2220 } else {
2221 // In this case, cache miss will be increased by one in
2222 // BlockBasedTable::Open() because this is not in DB::Open() code path so we
2223 // will prefetch L1's index and filter. Cache hit will also be increased by
2224 // one because Get() will read index and filter from the block cache
2225 // prefetched in previous Open() call.
2226 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2227 ASSERT_EQ(fh + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2228 ASSERT_EQ(im + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2229 ASSERT_EQ(ih + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2230 }
2231
2232 // Force a full compaction to one single file. There will be a block
2233 // cache read for both of index and filter. If prefetch doesn't explicitly
2234 // happen, it will happen when verifying the file.
2235 Compact(1, "a", "zzzzz");
2236 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
2237
2238 if (!disallow_preload_) {
2239 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2240 ASSERT_EQ(fh, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2241 ASSERT_EQ(im + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2242 ASSERT_EQ(ih + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2243 } else {
2244 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2245 ASSERT_EQ(fh + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2246 ASSERT_EQ(im + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2247 ASSERT_EQ(ih + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2248 }
2249
2250 // Bloom and index hit will happen when a Get() happens.
2251 value = Get(1, "a");
2252 if (!disallow_preload_) {
2253 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2254 ASSERT_EQ(fh + 1, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2255 ASSERT_EQ(im + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2256 ASSERT_EQ(ih + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2257 } else {
2258 ASSERT_EQ(fm + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS));
2259 ASSERT_EQ(fh + 2, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT));
2260 ASSERT_EQ(im + 3, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS));
2261 ASSERT_EQ(ih + 4, TestGetTickerCount(options, BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT));
2262 }
2263}
2264
2265INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest,
2266 PinL0IndexAndFilterBlocksTest,
2267 ::testing::Values(std::make_tuple(true, false),
2268 std::make_tuple(false, false),
2269 std::make_tuple(false, true)));
2270
2271TEST_F(DBTest2, MaxCompactionBytesTest) {
2272 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2273 options.memtable_factory.reset(test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(
2274 DBTestBase::kNumKeysByGenerateNewRandomFile));
2275 options.compaction_style = kCompactionStyleLevel;
2276 options.write_buffer_size = 200 << 10;
2277 options.arena_block_size = 4 << 10;
2278 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 4;
2279 options.num_levels = 4;
2280 options.compression = kNoCompression;
2281 options.max_bytes_for_level_base = 450 << 10;
2282 options.target_file_size_base = 100 << 10;
2283 // Infinite for full compaction.
2284 options.max_compaction_bytes = options.target_file_size_base * 100;
2285
2286 Reopen(options);
2287
2288 Random rnd(301);
2289
2290 for (int num = 0; num < 8; num++) {
2291 GenerateNewRandomFile(&rnd);
2292 }
2293 CompactRangeOptions cro;
2294 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForce;
2295 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
2296 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,8", FilesPerLevel(0));
2297
2298 // When compact from Ln -> Ln+1, cut a file if the file overlaps with
2299 // more than three files in Ln+1.
2300 options.max_compaction_bytes = options.target_file_size_base * 3;
2301 Reopen(options);
2302
2303 GenerateNewRandomFile(&rnd);
2304 // Add three more small files that overlap with the previous file
2305 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
2306 ASSERT_OK(Put("a", "z"));
2307 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2308 }
2309 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
2310
2311 // Output files to L1 are cut to 4 pieces, according to
2312 // options.max_compaction_bytes (300K)
2313 // There are 8 files on L2 (grandparents level), each one is 100K. The first
2314 // file overlaps with a, b which max_compaction_bytes is less than 300K, the
2315 // second one overlaps with d, e, which is also less than 300K. Including any
2316 // extra grandparent file will make the future compaction larger than 300K.
2317 // L1: [ 1 ] [ 2 ] [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
2318 // L2: [a] [b] [c] [d] [e] [f] [g] [h]
2319 ASSERT_EQ("0,4,8", FilesPerLevel(0));
2320}
2321
2322static void UniqueIdCallback(void* arg) {
2323 int* result = static_cast<int*>(arg);
2324 if (*result == -1) {
2325 *result = 0;
2326 }
2327
2328 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearTrace();
2329 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2330 "GetUniqueIdFromFile:FS_IOC_GETVERSION", UniqueIdCallback);
2331}
2332
2333class MockPersistentCache : public PersistentCache {
2334 public:
2335 explicit MockPersistentCache(const bool is_compressed, const size_t max_size)
2336 : is_compressed_(is_compressed), max_size_(max_size) {
2337 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2338 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2339 "GetUniqueIdFromFile:FS_IOC_GETVERSION", UniqueIdCallback);
2340 }
2341
2342 ~MockPersistentCache() override = default;
2343
2344 PersistentCache::StatsType Stats() override {
2345 return PersistentCache::StatsType();
2346 }
2347
2348 uint64_t NewId() override {
2349 return last_id_.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_relaxed);
2350 }
2351
2352 Status Insert(const Slice& page_key, const char* data,
2353 const size_t size) override {
2354 MutexLock _(&lock_);
2355
2356 if (size_ > max_size_) {
2357 size_ -= data_.begin()->second.size();
2358 data_.erase(data_.begin());
2359 }
2360
2361 data_.insert(std::make_pair(page_key.ToString(), std::string(data, size)));
2362 size_ += size;
2363 return Status::OK();
2364 }
2365
2366 Status Lookup(const Slice& page_key, std::unique_ptr<char[]>* data,
2367 size_t* size) override {
2368 MutexLock _(&lock_);
2369 auto it = data_.find(page_key.ToString());
2370 if (it == data_.end()) {
2371 return Status::NotFound();
2372 }
2373
2374 assert(page_key.ToString() == it->first);
2375 data->reset(new char[it->second.size()]);
2376 memcpy(data->get(), it->second.c_str(), it->second.size());
2377 *size = it->second.size();
2378 return Status::OK();
2379 }
2380
2381 bool IsCompressed() override { return is_compressed_; }
2382
2383 std::string GetPrintableOptions() const override {
2384 return "MockPersistentCache";
2385 }
2386
2387 port::Mutex lock_;
2388 std::map<std::string, std::string> data_;
2389 const bool is_compressed_ = true;
2390 size_t size_ = 0;
2391 const size_t max_size_ = 10 * 1024; // 10KiB
2392 std::atomic<uint64_t> last_id_{1};
2393};

2434TEST_F(DBTest2, TestPerfContextIterCpuTime) {
2435 DestroyAndReopen(CurrentOptions());
2436 // force resizing table cache so table handle is not preloaded so that
2437 // we can measure find_table_nanos during iteration
2438 dbfull()->TEST_table_cache()->SetCapacity(0);
2439
2440 const size_t kNumEntries = 10;
2441 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumEntries; ++i) {
2442 ASSERT_OK(Put("k" + std::to_string(i), "v" + std::to_string(i)));
2443 }
2444 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2445 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumEntries; ++i) {
2446 ASSERT_EQ("v" + std::to_string(i), Get("k" + std::to_string(i)));
2447 }
2448 std::string last_key = "k" + std::to_string(kNumEntries - 1);
2449 std::string last_value = "v" + std::to_string(kNumEntries - 1);
2450 env_->now_cpu_count_.store(0);
2451 env_->SetMockSleep();
2452
2453 // NOTE: Presumed unnecessary and removed: resetting mock time in env
2454
2455 // CPU timing is not enabled with kEnableTimeExceptForMutex
2456 SetPerfLevel(PerfLevel::kEnableTimeExceptForMutex);
2457 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
2458 iter->Seek("k0");
2459 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2460 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2461 iter->SeekForPrev(last_key);
2462 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2463 iter->SeekToLast();
2464 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2465 ASSERT_EQ(last_value, iter->value().ToString());
2466 iter->SeekToFirst();
2467 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2468 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2469 ASSERT_EQ(0, get_perf_context()->iter_seek_cpu_nanos);
2470 iter->Next();
2471 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2472 ASSERT_EQ("v1", iter->value().ToString());
2473 ASSERT_EQ(0, get_perf_context()->iter_next_cpu_nanos);
2474 iter->Prev();
2475 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2476 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2477 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2478 ASSERT_EQ(0, get_perf_context()->iter_prev_cpu_nanos);
2479 ASSERT_EQ(0, env_->now_cpu_count_.load());
2480 delete iter;
2481
2482 constexpr uint64_t kDummyAddonSeconds = uint64_t{1000000};
2483 constexpr uint64_t kDummyAddonNanos = 1000000000U * kDummyAddonSeconds;
2484
2485 // Add time to NowNanos() reading.
2486 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2487 "TableCache::FindTable:0",
2488 [&](void* /*arg*/) { env_->MockSleepForSeconds(kDummyAddonSeconds); });
2489 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2490
2491 SetPerfLevel(PerfLevel::kEnableTimeAndCPUTimeExceptForMutex);
2492 iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
2493 iter->Seek("k0");
2494 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2495 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2496 iter->SeekForPrev(last_key);
2497 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2498 iter->SeekToLast();
2499 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2500 ASSERT_EQ(last_value, iter->value().ToString());
2501 iter->SeekToFirst();
2502 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2503 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2504 ASSERT_GT(get_perf_context()->iter_seek_cpu_nanos, 0);
2505 ASSERT_LT(get_perf_context()->iter_seek_cpu_nanos, kDummyAddonNanos);
2506 iter->Next();
2507 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2508 ASSERT_EQ("v1", iter->value().ToString());
2509 ASSERT_GT(get_perf_context()->iter_next_cpu_nanos, 0);
2510 ASSERT_LT(get_perf_context()->iter_next_cpu_nanos, kDummyAddonNanos);
2511 iter->Prev();
2512 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2513 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2514 ASSERT_EQ("v0", iter->value().ToString());
2515 ASSERT_GT(get_perf_context()->iter_prev_cpu_nanos, 0);
2516 ASSERT_LT(get_perf_context()->iter_prev_cpu_nanos, kDummyAddonNanos);
2517 ASSERT_GE(env_->now_cpu_count_.load(), 12);
2518 ASSERT_GT(get_perf_context()->find_table_nanos, kDummyAddonNanos);
2519
2520 SetPerfLevel(PerfLevel::kDisable);
2521 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2522 delete iter;
2523}

2527TEST_F(DBTest2, PersistentCache) {
2528 int num_iter = 80;
2529
2530 Options options;
2531 options.write_buffer_size = 64 * 1024; // small write buffer
2532 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2533 options = CurrentOptions(options);
2534
2535 auto bsizes = {/*no block cache*/ 0, /*1M*/ 1 * 1024 * 1024};
2536 auto types = {/*compressed*/ 1, /*uncompressed*/ 0};
2537 for (auto bsize : bsizes) {
2538 for (auto type : types) {
2539 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
2540 table_options.persistent_cache.reset(
2541 new MockPersistentCache(type, 10 * 1024));
2542 table_options.no_block_cache = true;
2543 table_options.block_cache = bsize ? NewLRUCache(bsize) : nullptr;
2544 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2545
2546 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2547 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
2548 // default column family doesn't have block cache
2549 Options no_block_cache_opts;
2550 no_block_cache_opts.statistics = options.statistics;
2551 no_block_cache_opts = CurrentOptions(no_block_cache_opts);
2552 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options_no_bc;
2553 table_options_no_bc.no_block_cache = true;
2554 no_block_cache_opts.table_factory.reset(
2555 NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options_no_bc));
2556 ReopenWithColumnFamilies(
2557 {"default", "pikachu"},
2558 std::vector<Options>({no_block_cache_opts, options}));
2559
2560 Random rnd(301);
2561
2562 // Write 8MB (80 values, each 100K)
2563 ASSERT_EQ(NumTableFilesAtLevel(0, 1), 0);
2564 std::vector<std::string> values;
2565 std::string str;
2566 for (int i = 0; i < num_iter; i++) {
2567 if (i % 4 == 0) { // high compression ratio
2568 str = rnd.RandomString(1000);
2569 }
2570 values.push_back(str);
2571 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, Key(i), values[i]));
2572 }
2573
2574 // flush all data from memtable so that reads are from block cache
2575 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
2576
2577 for (int i = 0; i < num_iter; i++) {
2578 ASSERT_EQ(Get(1, Key(i)), values[i]);
2579 }
2580
2581 auto hit = options.statistics->getTickerCount(PERSISTENT_CACHE_HIT);
2582 auto miss = options.statistics->getTickerCount(PERSISTENT_CACHE_MISS);
2583
2584 ASSERT_GT(hit, 0);
2585 ASSERT_GT(miss, 0);
2586 }
2587 }
2588}

2597TEST_F(DBTest2, SyncPointMarker) {
2598 std::atomic<int> sync_point_called(0);
2599 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2600 "DBTest2::MarkedPoint",
2601 [&](void* /*arg*/) { sync_point_called.fetch_add(1); });
2602
2603 // The first dependency enforces Marker can be loaded before MarkedPoint.
2604 // The second checks that thread 1's MarkedPoint should be disabled here.
2605 // Execution order:
2606 // | Thread 1 | Thread 2 |
2607 // | | Marker |
2608 // | MarkedPoint | |
2609 // | Thread1First | |
2610 // | | MarkedPoint |
2611 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependencyAndMarkers(
2612 {{"DBTest2::SyncPointMarker:Thread1First", "DBTest2::MarkedPoint"}},
2613 {{"DBTest2::SyncPointMarker:Marker", "DBTest2::MarkedPoint"}});
2614
2615 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2616
2617 std::function<void()> func1 = [&]() {
2618 CountSyncPoint();
2619 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::SyncPointMarker:Thread1First");
2620 };
2621
2622 std::function<void()> func2 = [&]() {
2623 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::SyncPointMarker:Marker");
2624 CountSyncPoint();
2625 };
2626
2627 auto thread1 = port::Thread(func1);
2628 auto thread2 = port::Thread(func2);
2629 thread1.join();
2630 thread2.join();
2631
2632 // Callback is only executed once
2633 ASSERT_EQ(sync_point_called.load(), 1);
2634 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2635}
2636
2637size_t GetEncodedEntrySize(size_t key_size, size_t value_size) {
2638 std::string buffer;
2639
2640 PutVarint32(&buffer, static_cast<uint32_t>(0));
2641 PutVarint32(&buffer, static_cast<uint32_t>(key_size));
2642 PutVarint32(&buffer, static_cast<uint32_t>(value_size));
2643
2644 return buffer.size() + key_size + value_size;
2645}
2646
2647TEST_F(DBTest2, ReadAmpBitmap) {
2648 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2649 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
2650 uint32_t bytes_per_bit[2] = {1, 16};
2651 for (size_t k = 0; k < 2; k++) {
2652 // Disable delta encoding to make it easier to calculate read amplification
2653 bbto.use_delta_encoding = false;
2654 // Huge block cache to make it easier to calculate read amplification
2655 bbto.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024 * 1024);
2656 bbto.read_amp_bytes_per_bit = bytes_per_bit[k];
2657 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
2658 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2659 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2660
2661 const size_t kNumEntries = 10000;
2662
2663 Random rnd(301);
2664 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumEntries; i++) {
2665 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(static_cast<int>(i)), rnd.RandomString(100)));
2666 }
2667 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2668
2669 Close();
2670 Reopen(options);
2671
2672 // Read keys/values randomly and verify that reported read amp error
2673 // is less than 2%
2674 uint64_t total_useful_bytes = 0;
2675 std::set<int> read_keys;
2676 std::string value;
2677 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumEntries * 5; i++) {
2678 int key_idx = rnd.Next() % kNumEntries;
2679 std::string key = Key(key_idx);
2680 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ReadOptions(), key, &value));
2681
2682 if (read_keys.find(key_idx) == read_keys.end()) {
2683 auto internal_key = InternalKey(key, 0, ValueType::kTypeValue);
2684 total_useful_bytes +=
2685 GetEncodedEntrySize(internal_key.size(), value.size());
2686 read_keys.insert(key_idx);
2687 }
2688
2689 double expected_read_amp =
2690 static_cast<double>(total_useful_bytes) /
2691 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES);
2692
2693 double read_amp =
2694 static_cast<double>(options.statistics->getTickerCount(
2695 READ_AMP_ESTIMATE_USEFUL_BYTES)) /
2696 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES);
2697
2698 double error_pct = fabs(expected_read_amp - read_amp) * 100;
2699 // Error between reported read amp and real read amp should be less than
2700 // 2%
2701 EXPECT_LE(error_pct, 2);
2702 }
2703
2704 // Make sure we read every thing in the DB (which is smaller than our cache)
2705 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
2706 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
2707 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), Get(iter->key().ToString()));
2708 }
2709 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2710 delete iter;
2711
2712 // Read amp is on average 100% since we read all what we loaded in memory
2713 if (k == 0) {
2714 ASSERT_EQ(
2715 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_ESTIMATE_USEFUL_BYTES),
2716 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES));
2717 } else {
2718 ASSERT_NEAR(
2719 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_ESTIMATE_USEFUL_BYTES) *
2720 1.0f /
2721 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES),
2722 1, .01);
2723 }
2724 }
2725}
2726
2727#ifndef OS_SOLARIS // GetUniqueIdFromFile is not implemented
2728TEST_F(DBTest2, ReadAmpBitmapLiveInCacheAfterDBClose) {
2729 {
2730 const int kIdBufLen = 100;
2731 char id_buf[kIdBufLen];
2732 Status s = Status::NotSupported();
2733#ifndef OS_WIN
2734 // You can't open a directory on windows using random access file
2735 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFile> file;
2736 s = env_->NewRandomAccessFile(dbname_, &file, EnvOptions());
2737 if (s.ok()) {
2738 if (file->GetUniqueId(id_buf, kIdBufLen) == 0) {
2739 // fs holding db directory doesn't support getting a unique file id,
2740 // this means that running this test will fail because lru_cache will
2741 // load the blocks again regardless of them being already in the cache
2742 return;
2743 }
2744 }
2745#endif
2746 if (!s.ok()) {
2747 std::unique_ptr<Directory> dir;
2748 ASSERT_OK(env_->NewDirectory(dbname_, &dir));
2749 if (dir->GetUniqueId(id_buf, kIdBufLen) == 0) {
2750 // fs holding db directory doesn't support getting a unique file id,
2751 // this means that running this test will fail because lru_cache will
2752 // load the blocks again regardless of them being already in the cache
2753 return;
2754 }
2755 }
2756 }
2757 uint32_t bytes_per_bit[2] = {1, 16};
2758 for (size_t k = 0; k < 2; k++) {
2759 std::shared_ptr<Cache> lru_cache = NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024 * 1024);
2760 std::shared_ptr<Statistics> stats = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2761
2762 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2763 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
2764 // Disable delta encoding to make it easier to calculate read amplification
2765 bbto.use_delta_encoding = false;
2766 // Huge block cache to make it easier to calculate read amplification
2767 bbto.block_cache = lru_cache;
2768 bbto.read_amp_bytes_per_bit = bytes_per_bit[k];
2769 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
2770 options.statistics = stats;
2771 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2772
2773 const int kNumEntries = 10000;
2774
2775 Random rnd(301);
2776 for (int i = 0; i < kNumEntries; i++) {
2777 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i), rnd.RandomString(100)));
2778 }
2779 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2780
2781 Close();
2782 Reopen(options);
2783
2784 std::set<int> read_keys;
2785 std::string value;
2786 // Iter1: Read half the DB, Read even keys
2787 // Key(0), Key(2), Key(4), Key(6), Key(8), ...
2788 for (int i = 0; i < kNumEntries; i += 2) {
2789 std::string key = Key(i);
2790 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ReadOptions(), key, &value));
2791
2792 if (read_keys.find(i) == read_keys.end()) {
2793 auto internal_key = InternalKey(key, 0, ValueType::kTypeValue);
2794 read_keys.insert(i);
2795 }
2796 }
2797
2798 size_t total_useful_bytes_iter1 =
2799 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_ESTIMATE_USEFUL_BYTES);
2800 size_t total_loaded_bytes_iter1 =
2801 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES);
2802
2803 Close();
2804 std::shared_ptr<Statistics> new_statistics =
2805 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
2806 // Destroy old statistics obj that the blocks in lru_cache are pointing to
2807 options.statistics.reset();
2808 // Use the statistics object that we just created
2809 options.statistics = new_statistics;
2810 Reopen(options);
2811
2812 // Iter2: Read half the DB, Read odd keys
2813 // Key(1), Key(3), Key(5), Key(7), Key(9), ...
2814 for (int i = 1; i < kNumEntries; i += 2) {
2815 std::string key = Key(i);
2816 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ReadOptions(), key, &value));
2817
2818 if (read_keys.find(i) == read_keys.end()) {
2819 auto internal_key = InternalKey(key, 0, ValueType::kTypeValue);
2820 read_keys.insert(i);
2821 }
2822 }
2823
2824 size_t total_useful_bytes_iter2 =
2825 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_ESTIMATE_USEFUL_BYTES);
2826 size_t total_loaded_bytes_iter2 =
2827 options.statistics->getTickerCount(READ_AMP_TOTAL_READ_BYTES);
2828
2829 // Read amp is on average 100% since we read all what we loaded in memory
2830 if (k == 0) {
2831 ASSERT_EQ(total_useful_bytes_iter1 + total_useful_bytes_iter2,
2832 total_loaded_bytes_iter1 + total_loaded_bytes_iter2);
2833 } else {
2834 ASSERT_NEAR((total_useful_bytes_iter1 + total_useful_bytes_iter2) * 1.0f /
2835 (total_loaded_bytes_iter1 + total_loaded_bytes_iter2),
2836 1, .01);
2837 }
2838 }
2839}

2842TEST_F(DBTest2, AutomaticCompactionOverlapManualCompaction) {
2843 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2844 options.num_levels = 3;
2845 options.IncreaseParallelism(20);
2846 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2847
2848 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(0), "a"));
2849 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(5), "a"));
2850 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2851
2852 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(10), "a"));
2853 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(15), "a"));
2854 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2855
2856 CompactRangeOptions cro;
2857 cro.change_level = true;
2858 cro.target_level = 2;
2859 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
2860
2861 auto get_stat = [](std::string level_str, LevelStatType type,
2862 std::map<std::string, std::string> props) {
2863 auto prop_str =
2864 "compaction." + level_str + "." +
2865 InternalStats::compaction_level_stats.at(type).property_name.c_str();
2866 auto prop_item = props.find(prop_str);
2867 return prop_item == props.end() ? 0 : std::stod(prop_item->second);
2868 };
2869
2870 // Trivial move 2 files to L2
2871 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,2", FilesPerLevel());
2872 // Also test that the stats GetMapProperty API reporting the same result
2873 {
2874 std::map<std::string, std::string> prop;
2875 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()->GetMapProperty("rocksdb.cfstats", &prop));
2876 ASSERT_EQ(0, get_stat("L0", LevelStatType::NUM_FILES, prop));
2877 ASSERT_EQ(0, get_stat("L1", LevelStatType::NUM_FILES, prop));
2878 ASSERT_EQ(2, get_stat("L2", LevelStatType::NUM_FILES, prop));
2879 ASSERT_EQ(2, get_stat("Sum", LevelStatType::NUM_FILES, prop));
2880 }
2881
2882 // While the compaction is running, we will create 2 new files that
2883 // can fit in L2, these 2 files will be moved to L2 and overlap with
2884 // the running compaction and break the LSM consistency.
2885 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2886 "CompactionJob::Run():Start", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
2887 ASSERT_OK(
2888 dbfull()->SetOptions({{"level0_file_num_compaction_trigger", "2"},
2889 {"max_bytes_for_level_base", "1"}}));
2890 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(6), "a"));
2891 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(7), "a"));
2892 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2893
2894 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(8), "a"));
2895 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(9), "a"));
2896 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2897 });
2898 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2899
2900 // Run a manual compaction that will compact the 2 files in L2
2901 // into 1 file in L2
2902 cro.exclusive_manual_compaction = false;
2903 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForceOptimized;
2904 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
2905
2906 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2907
2908 // Test that the stats GetMapProperty API reporting 1 file in L2
2909 {
2910 std::map<std::string, std::string> prop;
2911 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()->GetMapProperty("rocksdb.cfstats", &prop));
2912 ASSERT_EQ(1, get_stat("L2", LevelStatType::NUM_FILES, prop));
2913 }
2914}

2916TEST_F(DBTest2, ManualCompactionOverlapManualCompaction) {
2917 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2918 options.num_levels = 2;
2919 options.IncreaseParallelism(20);
2920 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
2921 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2922
2923 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(0), "a"));
2924 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(5), "a"));
2925 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2926
2927 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(10), "a"));
2928 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(15), "a"));
2929 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2930
2931 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
2932
2933 // Trivial move 2 files to L1
2934 ASSERT_EQ("0,2", FilesPerLevel());
2935
2936 std::function<void()> bg_manual_compact = [&]() {
2937 std::string k1 = Key(6);
2938 std::string k2 = Key(9);
2939 Slice k1s(k1);
2940 Slice k2s(k2);
2941 CompactRangeOptions cro;
2942 cro.exclusive_manual_compaction = false;
2943 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, &k1s, &k2s));
2944 };
2945 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::port::Thread bg_thread;
2946
2947 // While the compaction is running, we will create 2 new files that
2948 // can fit in L1, these 2 files will be moved to L1 and overlap with
2949 // the running compaction and break the LSM consistency.
2950 std::atomic<bool> flag(false);
2951 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2952 "CompactionJob::Run():Start", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
2953 if (flag.exchange(true)) {
2954 // We want to make sure to call this callback only once
2955 return;
2956 }
2957 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(6), "a"));
2958 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(7), "a"));
2959 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2960
2961 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(8), "a"));
2962 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(9), "a"));
2963 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2964
2965 // Start a non-exclusive manual compaction in a bg thread
2966 bg_thread = port::Thread(bg_manual_compact);
2967 // This manual compaction conflict with the other manual compaction
2968 // so it should wait until the first compaction finish
2969 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(1000000);
2970 });
2971 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2972
2973 // Run a manual compaction that will compact the 2 files in L1
2974 // into 1 file in L1
2975 CompactRangeOptions cro;
2976 cro.exclusive_manual_compaction = false;
2977 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kForceOptimized;
2978 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
2979 bg_thread.join();
2980
2981 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2982}

2984TEST_F(DBTest2, PausingManualCompaction1) {
2985 Options options = CurrentOptions();
2986 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
2987 options.num_levels = 7;
2988
2989 DestroyAndReopen(options);
2990 Random rnd(301);
2991 // Generate a file containing 10 keys.
2992 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
2993 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i), rnd.RandomString(50)));
2994 }
2995 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
2996
2997 // Generate another file containing same keys
2998 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
2999 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i), rnd.RandomString(50)));
3000 }
3001 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3002
3003 int manual_compactions_paused = 0;
3004 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3005 "CompactionJob::Run():PausingManualCompaction:1", [&](void* arg) {
3006 auto canceled = static_cast<std::atomic<bool>*>(arg);
3007 // CompactRange triggers manual compaction and cancel the compaction
3008 // by set *canceled as true
3009 if (canceled != nullptr) {
3010 canceled->store(true, std::memory_order_release);
3011 }
3012 manual_compactions_paused += 1;
3013 });
3014 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3015 "TestCompactFiles:PausingManualCompaction:3", [&](void* arg) {
3016 auto paused = static_cast<std::atomic<int>*>(arg);
3017 // CompactFiles() relies on manual_compactions_paused to
3018 // determine if thie compaction should be paused or not
3019 ASSERT_EQ(0, paused->load(std::memory_order_acquire));
3020 paused->fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_release);
3021 });
3022 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3023
3024 std::vector<std::string> files_before_compact, files_after_compact;
3025 // Remember file name before compaction is triggered
3026 std::vector<LiveFileMetaData> files_meta;
3027 dbfull()->GetLiveFilesMetaData(&files_meta);
3028 for (const auto& file : files_meta) {
3029 files_before_compact.push_back(file.name);
3030 }
3031
3032 // OK, now trigger a manual compaction
3033 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3034 ->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr)
3035 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3036
3037 // Wait for compactions to get scheduled and stopped
3038 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3039
3040 // Get file names after compaction is stopped
3041 files_meta.clear();
3042 dbfull()->GetLiveFilesMetaData(&files_meta);
3043 for (const auto& file : files_meta) {
3044 files_after_compact.push_back(file.name);
3045 }
3046
3047 // Like nothing happened
3048 ASSERT_EQ(files_before_compact, files_after_compact);
3049 ASSERT_EQ(manual_compactions_paused, 1);
3050
3051 manual_compactions_paused = 0;
3052 // Now make sure CompactFiles also not run
3053 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3054 ->CompactFiles(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CompactionOptions(),
3055 files_before_compact, 0)
3056 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3057 // Wait for manual compaction to get scheduled and finish
3058 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3059
3060 files_meta.clear();
3061 files_after_compact.clear();
3062 dbfull()->GetLiveFilesMetaData(&files_meta);
3063 for (const auto& file : files_meta) {
3064 files_after_compact.push_back(file.name);
3065 }
3066
3067 ASSERT_EQ(files_before_compact, files_after_compact);
3068 // CompactFiles returns at entry point
3069 ASSERT_EQ(manual_compactions_paused, 0);
3070
3071 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3072}

3210TEST_F(DBTest2, CancelManualCompaction1) {
3211 CompactRangeOptions compact_options;
3212 auto canceledPtr =
3213 std::unique_ptr<std::atomic<bool>>(new std::atomic<bool>{true});
3214 compact_options.canceled = canceledPtr.get();
3215
3216 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3217 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
3218 options.num_levels = 7;
3219
3220 Random rnd(301);
3221 auto generate_files = [&]() {
3222 for (int i = 0; i < options.num_levels; i++) {
3223 for (int j = 0; j < options.num_levels - i + 1; j++) {
3224 for (int k = 0; k < 1000; k++) {
3225 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(k + j * 1000), rnd.RandomString(50)));
3226 }
3227 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3228 }
3229
3230 for (int l = 1; l < options.num_levels - i; l++) {
3231 MoveFilesToLevel(l);
3232 }
3233 }
3234 };
3235
3236 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3237 generate_files();
3238 ASSERT_EQ("2,3,4,5,6,7,8", FilesPerLevel());
3239
3240 int run_manual_compactions = 0;
3241 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3242 "CompactionJob::Run():PausingManualCompaction:1",
3243 [&](void* /*arg*/) { run_manual_compactions++; });
3244 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3245
3246 // Setup a callback to disable compactions after a couple of levels are
3247 // compacted
3248 int compactions_run = 0;
3249 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3250 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1",
3251 [&](void* /*arg*/) { ++compactions_run; });
3252
3253 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3254 ->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr)
3255 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3256 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3257
3258 // Since compactions are disabled, we shouldn't start compacting.
3259 // E.g. we should call the compaction function exactly one time.
3260 ASSERT_EQ(compactions_run, 0);
3261 ASSERT_EQ(run_manual_compactions, 0);
3262 ASSERT_EQ("2,3,4,5,6,7,8", FilesPerLevel());
3263
3264 compactions_run = 0;
3265 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3266 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1");
3267 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3268 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3269 ++compactions_run;
3270 // After 3 compactions disable
3271 if (compactions_run == 3) {
3272 compact_options.canceled->store(true, std::memory_order_release);
3273 }
3274 });
3275
3276 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_release);
3277 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3278 ->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr)
3279 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3280 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3281
3282 ASSERT_EQ(compactions_run, 3);
3283
3284 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3285 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1");
3286 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3287 "CompactionJob::Run():PausingManualCompaction:1");
3288
3289 // Compactions should work again if we re-enable them..
3290 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_relaxed);
3291 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr));
3292 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3293 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,0,0,0,0,2", FilesPerLevel());
3294
3295 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3296}

3298TEST_F(DBTest2, CancelManualCompaction2) {
3299 CompactRangeOptions compact_options;
3300 auto canceledPtr =
3301 std::unique_ptr<std::atomic<bool>>(new std::atomic<bool>{true});
3302 compact_options.canceled = canceledPtr.get();
3303 compact_options.max_subcompactions = 1;
3304
3305 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3306 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
3307 options.num_levels = 7;
3308
3309 Random rnd(301);
3310 auto generate_files = [&]() {
3311 for (int i = 0; i < options.num_levels; i++) {
3312 for (int j = 0; j < options.num_levels - i + 1; j++) {
3313 for (int k = 0; k < 1000; k++) {
3314 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(k + j * 1000), rnd.RandomString(50)));
3315 }
3316 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3317 }
3318
3319 for (int l = 1; l < options.num_levels - i; l++) {
3320 MoveFilesToLevel(l);
3321 }
3322 }
3323 };
3324
3325 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3326 generate_files();
3327 ASSERT_EQ("2,3,4,5,6,7,8", FilesPerLevel());
3328
3329 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3330
3331 int compactions_run = 0;
3332 std::atomic<int> kv_compactions{0};
3333 int compactions_stopped_at = 0;
3334 int kv_compactions_stopped_at = 0;
3335 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3336 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3337 ++compactions_run;
3338 // After 3 compactions disable
3339 });
3340
3341 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3342 "CompactionIterator:ProcessKV", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3343 int kv_compactions_run =
3344 kv_compactions.fetch_add(1, std::memory_order_release);
3345 if (kv_compactions_run == 5) {
3346 compact_options.canceled->store(true, std::memory_order_release);
3347 kv_compactions_stopped_at = kv_compactions_run;
3348 compactions_stopped_at = compactions_run;
3349 }
3350 });
3351
3352 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_release);
3353 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3354 ->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr)
3355 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3356 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3357
3358 // NOTE: as we set compact_options.max_subcompacitons = 1, and store true to
3359 // the canceled variable from the single compacting thread (via callback),
3360 // this value is deterministically kv_compactions_stopped_at + 1.
3361 ASSERT_EQ(kv_compactions, kv_compactions_stopped_at + 1);
3362 ASSERT_EQ(compactions_run, compactions_stopped_at);
3363
3364 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3365 "CompactionIterator::ProcessKV");
3366 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3367 "DBImpl::RunManualCompaction()::1");
3368 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3369 "CompactionJob::Run():PausingManualCompaction:1");
3370
3371 // Compactions should work again if we re-enable them..
3372 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_relaxed);
3373 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr));
3374 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3375 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,0,0,0,0,2", FilesPerLevel());
3376
3377 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3378}
3379
3380class CancelCompactionListener : public EventListener {
3381 public:
3382 CancelCompactionListener()
3383 : num_compaction_started_(0), num_compaction_ended_(0) {}
3384
3385 void OnCompactionBegin(DB* /*db*/, const CompactionJobInfo& ci) override {
3386 ASSERT_EQ(ci.cf_name, "default");
3387 ASSERT_EQ(ci.base_input_level, 0);
3388 num_compaction_started_++;
3389 }
3390
3391 void OnCompactionCompleted(DB* /*db*/, const CompactionJobInfo& ci) override {
3392 ASSERT_EQ(ci.cf_name, "default");
3393 ASSERT_EQ(ci.base_input_level, 0);
3394 ASSERT_EQ(ci.status.code(), code_);
3395 ASSERT_EQ(ci.status.subcode(), subcode_);
3396 num_compaction_ended_++;
3397 }
3398
3399 std::atomic<size_t> num_compaction_started_;
3400 std::atomic<size_t> num_compaction_ended_;
3401 Status::Code code_;
3402 Status::SubCode subcode_;
3403};
3404
3405TEST_F(DBTest2, CancelManualCompactionWithListener) {
3406 CompactRangeOptions compact_options;
3407 auto canceledPtr =
3408 std::unique_ptr<std::atomic<bool>>(new std::atomic<bool>{true});
3409 compact_options.canceled = canceledPtr.get();
3410 compact_options.max_subcompactions = 1;
3411
3412 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3413 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
3414 CancelCompactionListener* listener = new CancelCompactionListener();
3415 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
3416
3417 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3418
3419 Random rnd(301);
3420 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
3421 for (int j = 0; j < 10; j++) {
3422 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i + j * 10), rnd.RandomString(50)));
3423 }
3424 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3425 }
3426
3427 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3428
3429 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3430 "CompactionIterator:ProcessKV", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3431 compact_options.canceled->store(true, std::memory_order_release);
3432 });
3433
3434 int running_compaction = 0;
3435 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3436 "CompactionJob::FinishCompactionOutputFile1",
3437 [&](void* /*arg*/) { running_compaction++; });
3438
3439 // Case I: 1 Notify begin compaction, 2 Set *canceled as true to disable
3440 // manual compaction in the callback function, 3 Compaction not run,
3441 // 4 Notify compaction end.
3442 listener->code_ = Status::kIncomplete;
3443 listener->subcode_ = Status::SubCode::kManualCompactionPaused;
3444
3445 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_release);
3446 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3447 ->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr)
3448 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3449 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3450
3451 ASSERT_GT(listener->num_compaction_started_, 0);
3452 ASSERT_EQ(listener->num_compaction_started_, listener->num_compaction_ended_);
3453 ASSERT_EQ(running_compaction, 0);
3454
3455 listener->num_compaction_started_ = 0;
3456 listener->num_compaction_ended_ = 0;
3457
3458 // Case II: 1 Set *canceled as true in the callback function to disable manual
3459 // compaction, 2 Notify begin compaction (return without notifying), 3 Notify
3460 // compaction end (return without notifying).
3461 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()
3462 ->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr)
3463 .IsManualCompactionPaused());
3464 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3465
3466 ASSERT_EQ(listener->num_compaction_started_, 0);
3467 ASSERT_EQ(listener->num_compaction_started_, listener->num_compaction_ended_);
3468 ASSERT_EQ(running_compaction, 0);
3469
3470 // Case III: 1 Notify begin compaction, 2 Compaction in between
3471 // 3. Set *canceled as true in the callback function to disable manual
3472 // compaction, 4 Notify compaction end.
3473 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearCallBack(
3474 "CompactionIterator:ProcessKV");
3475
3476 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3477 "CompactionJob::Run:BeforeVerify", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
3478 compact_options.canceled->store(true, std::memory_order_release);
3479 });
3480
3481 listener->code_ = Status::kOk;
3482 listener->subcode_ = Status::SubCode::kNone;
3483
3484 compact_options.canceled->store(false, std::memory_order_release);
3485 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr));
3486 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3487
3488 ASSERT_GT(listener->num_compaction_started_, 0);
3489 ASSERT_EQ(listener->num_compaction_started_, listener->num_compaction_ended_);
3490
3491 // Compaction job will succeed.
3492 ASSERT_GT(running_compaction, 0);
3493
3494 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3495 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3496}

3498TEST_F(DBTest2, CompactionOnBottomPriorityWithListener) {
3499 int num_levels = 3;
3500 const int kNumFilesTrigger = 4;
3501
3502 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3503 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(0, Env::Priority::HIGH);
3504 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(0, Env::Priority::LOW);
3505 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(1, Env::Priority::BOTTOM);
3506 options.env = env_;
3507 options.compaction_style = kCompactionStyleUniversal;
3508 options.num_levels = num_levels;
3509 options.write_buffer_size = 100 << 10; // 100KB
3510 options.target_file_size_base = 32 << 10; // 32KB
3511 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = kNumFilesTrigger;
3512 // Trigger compaction if size amplification exceeds 110%
3513 options.compaction_options_universal.max_size_amplification_percent = 110;
3514
3515 CancelCompactionListener* listener = new CancelCompactionListener();
3516 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
3517
3518 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3519
3520 int num_bottom_thread_compaction_scheduled = 0;
3521 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3522
3523 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3524 "DBImpl::BackgroundCompaction:ForwardToBottomPriPool",
3525 [&](void* /*arg*/) { num_bottom_thread_compaction_scheduled++; });
3526
3527 int num_compaction_jobs = 0;
3528 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3529 "CompactionJob::Run():End",
3530 [&](void* /*arg*/) { num_compaction_jobs++; });
3531
3532 listener->code_ = Status::kOk;
3533 listener->subcode_ = Status::SubCode::kNone;
3534
3535 Random rnd(301);
3536 for (int i = 0; i < 1; ++i) {
3537 for (int num = 0; num < kNumFilesTrigger; num++) {
3538 int key_idx = 0;
3539 GenerateNewFile(&rnd, &key_idx, true /* no_wait */);
3540 // use no_wait above because that one waits for flush and compaction. We
3541 // don't want to wait for compaction because the full compaction is
3542 // intentionally blocked while more files are flushed.
3543 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
3544 }
3545 }
3546 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3547 ASSERT_GT(num_bottom_thread_compaction_scheduled, 0);
3548 ASSERT_EQ(num_compaction_jobs, 1);
3549 ASSERT_GT(listener->num_compaction_started_, 0);
3550 ASSERT_EQ(listener->num_compaction_started_, listener->num_compaction_ended_);
3551
3552 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3553 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3554}

3568TEST_F(DBTest2, OptimizeForSmallDB) {
3569 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3570 Close();
3571 options.OptimizeForSmallDb();
3572
3573 // Find the cache object
3574 ASSERT_TRUE(options.table_factory->IsInstanceOf(
3575 TableFactory::kBlockBasedTableName()));
3576 auto table_options =
3577 options.table_factory->GetOptions<BlockBasedTableOptions>();
3578
3579 ASSERT_TRUE(table_options != nullptr);
3580 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache = table_options->block_cache;
3581
3582 ASSERT_EQ(0, cache->GetUsage());
3583 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname_, &db_));
3584 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "v1"));
3585
3586 // memtable size is costed to the block cache
3587 ASSERT_NE(0, cache->GetUsage());
3588
3589 ASSERT_EQ("v1", Get("foo"));
3590 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3591
3592 size_t prev_size = cache->GetUsage();
3593 // Remember block cache size, so that we can find that
3594 // it is filled after Get().
3595 // Use pinnable slice so that it can ping the block so that
3596 // when we check the size it is not evicted.
3597 PinnableSlice value;
3598 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ReadOptions(), db_->DefaultColumnFamily(), "foo", &value));
3599 ASSERT_GT(cache->GetUsage(), prev_size);
3600 value.Reset();
3601}

3767TEST_F(DBTest2, MemtableOnlyIterator) {
3768 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3769 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
3770
3771 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "first"));
3772 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "bar", "second"));
3773
3774 ReadOptions ropt;
3775 ropt.read_tier = kMemtableTier;
3776 std::string value;
3777 Iterator* it = nullptr;
3778
3779 // Before flushing
3780 // point lookups
3781 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ropt, handles_[1], "foo", &value));
3782 ASSERT_EQ("first", value);
3783 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ropt, handles_[1], "bar", &value));
3784 ASSERT_EQ("second", value);
3785
3786 // Memtable-only iterator (read_tier=kMemtableTier); data not flushed yet.
3787 it = db_->NewIterator(ropt, handles_[1]);
3788 int count = 0;
3789 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next()) {
3790 ASSERT_TRUE(it->Valid());
3791 count++;
3792 }
3793 ASSERT_TRUE(!it->Valid());
3794 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3795 ASSERT_EQ(2, count);
3796 delete it;
3797
3798 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
3799
3800 // After flushing
3801 // point lookups
3802 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ropt, handles_[1], "foo", &value));
3803 ASSERT_EQ("first", value);
3804 ASSERT_OK(db_->Get(ropt, handles_[1], "bar", &value));
3805 ASSERT_EQ("second", value);
3806 // nothing should be returned using memtable-only iterator after flushing.
3807 it = db_->NewIterator(ropt, handles_[1]);
3808 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3809 count = 0;
3810 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next()) {
3811 ASSERT_TRUE(it->Valid());
3812 count++;
3813 }
3814 ASSERT_TRUE(!it->Valid());
3815 ASSERT_EQ(0, count);
3816 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3817 delete it;
3818
3819 // Add a key to memtable
3820 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foobar", "third"));
3821 it = db_->NewIterator(ropt, handles_[1]);
3822 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3823 count = 0;
3824 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next()) {
3825 ASSERT_TRUE(it->Valid());
3826 ASSERT_EQ("foobar", it->key().ToString());
3827 ASSERT_EQ("third", it->value().ToString());
3828 count++;
3829 }
3830 ASSERT_TRUE(!it->Valid());
3831 ASSERT_EQ(1, count);
3832 ASSERT_OK(it->status());
3833 delete it;
3834}

3836TEST_F(DBTest2, LowPriWrite) {
3837 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3838 // Compaction pressure should trigger since 6 files
3839 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 4;
3840 options.level0_slowdown_writes_trigger = 12;
3841 options.level0_stop_writes_trigger = 30;
3842 options.delayed_write_rate = 8 * 1024 * 1024;
3843 Reopen(options);
3844
3845 std::atomic<int> rate_limit_count(0);
3846
3847 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3848 "GenericRateLimiter::Request:1", [&](void* arg) {
3849 rate_limit_count.fetch_add(1);
3850 int64_t* rate_bytes_per_sec = static_cast<int64_t*>(arg);
3851 ASSERT_EQ(1024 * 1024, *rate_bytes_per_sec);
3852 });
3853
3854 // Make a trivial L5 for L0 to compact into. L6 will be large so debt ratio
3855 // will not cause compaction pressure.
3856 Random rnd(301);
3857 ASSERT_OK(Put("", rnd.RandomString(102400)));
3858 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3859 MoveFilesToLevel(6);
3860 ASSERT_OK(Put("", ""));
3861 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3862 MoveFilesToLevel(5);
3863
3864 // Block compaction
3865 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
3866 {"DBTest.LowPriWrite:0", "DBImpl::BGWorkCompaction"},
3867 });
3868 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3869 WriteOptions wo;
3870 for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
3871 wo.low_pri = false;
3872 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3873 wo.low_pri = true;
3874 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3875 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
3876 }
3877 ASSERT_EQ(0, rate_limit_count.load());
3878 wo.low_pri = true;
3879 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3880 ASSERT_EQ(1, rate_limit_count.load());
3881 wo.low_pri = false;
3882 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3883 ASSERT_EQ(1, rate_limit_count.load());
3884
3885 wo.low_pri = true;
3886 std::string big_value = std::string(1 * 1024 * 1024, 'x');
3887 ASSERT_OK(Put("", big_value, wo));
3888 ASSERT_LT(1, rate_limit_count.load());
3889 // Reset
3890 rate_limit_count = 0;
3891 wo.low_pri = false;
3892 ASSERT_OK(Put("", big_value, wo));
3893 ASSERT_EQ(0, rate_limit_count.load());
3894
3895 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest.LowPriWrite:0");
3896 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3897
3898 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3899 wo.low_pri = true;
3900 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3901 ASSERT_EQ(0, rate_limit_count.load());
3902 wo.low_pri = false;
3903 ASSERT_OK(Put("", "", wo));
3904 ASSERT_EQ(0, rate_limit_count.load());
3905}
3906
3907TEST_F(DBTest2, RateLimitedCompactionReads) {
3908 // compaction input has 512KB data
3909 const int kNumKeysPerFile = 128;
3910 const int kBytesPerKey = 1024;
3911 const int kNumL0Files = 4;
3912
3913 for (int compaction_readahead_size : {0, 32 << 10}) {
3914 for (auto use_direct_io : {false, true}) {
3915 if (use_direct_io && !IsDirectIOSupported()) {
3916 continue;
3917 }
3918 Options options = CurrentOptions();
3919 options.compaction_readahead_size = compaction_readahead_size;
3920 options.compression = kNoCompression;
3921 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = kNumL0Files;
3922 options.memtable_factory.reset(
3923 test::NewSpecialSkipListFactory(kNumKeysPerFile));
3924 // takes roughly one second, split into 100 x 10ms intervals. Each
3925 // interval permits 5.12KB, which is smaller than the block size, so this
3926 // test exercises the code for chunking reads.
3927 options.rate_limiter.reset(NewGenericRateLimiter(
3928 static_cast<int64_t>(kNumL0Files * kNumKeysPerFile *
3929 kBytesPerKey) /* rate_bytes_per_sec */,
3930 10 * 1000 /* refill_period_us */, 10 /* fairness */,
3931 RateLimiter::Mode::kReadsOnly));
3932 options.use_direct_reads =
3933 options.use_direct_io_for_flush_and_compaction = use_direct_io;
3934 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
3935 bbto.block_size = 16384;
3936 bbto.no_block_cache = true;
3937 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
3938 DestroyAndReopen(options);
3939
3940 // To precisely control when to start bg compaction for excluding previous
3941 // rate-limited bytes of flush read for table verification
3942 std::shared_ptr<test::SleepingBackgroundTask> sleeping_task(
3943 new test::SleepingBackgroundTask());
3944 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(1, Env::LOW);
3945 env_->Schedule(&test::SleepingBackgroundTask::DoSleepTask,
3946 sleeping_task.get(), Env::Priority::LOW);
3947 sleeping_task->WaitUntilSleeping();
3948
3949 for (int i = 0; i < kNumL0Files; ++i) {
3950 for (int j = 0; j <= kNumKeysPerFile; ++j) {
3951 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(j), DummyString(kBytesPerKey)));
3952 }
3953 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForFlushMemTable());
3954 if (i + 1 < kNumL0Files) {
3955 ASSERT_EQ(i + 1, NumTableFilesAtLevel(0));
3956 }
3957 }
3958
3959 size_t rate_limited_bytes_start_bytes =
3960 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_TOTAL);
3961
3962 sleeping_task->WakeUp();
3963 sleeping_task->WaitUntilDone();
3964 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
3965 ASSERT_EQ(0, NumTableFilesAtLevel(0));
3966 // should be slightly above 512KB due to non-data blocks read. Arbitrarily
3967 // chose 1MB as the upper bound on the total bytes read.
3968 size_t rate_limited_bytes =
3969 static_cast<size_t>(
3970 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_TOTAL)) -
3971 rate_limited_bytes_start_bytes;
3972 // The charges can exist for `IO_LOW` and `IO_USER` priorities.
3973 size_t rate_limited_bytes_by_pri =
3974 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_LOW) +
3975 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_USER);
3976 ASSERT_EQ(rate_limited_bytes,
3977 static_cast<size_t>(rate_limited_bytes_by_pri));
3978 // Include the explicit prefetch of the footer in direct I/O case.
3979 size_t direct_io_extra = use_direct_io ? 512 * 1024 : 0;
3980 ASSERT_GE(
3981 rate_limited_bytes,
3982 static_cast<size_t>(kNumKeysPerFile * kBytesPerKey * kNumL0Files));
3983 ASSERT_LT(
3984 rate_limited_bytes,
3985 static_cast<size_t>(2 * kNumKeysPerFile * kBytesPerKey * kNumL0Files +
3986 direct_io_extra));
3987
3988 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
3989 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3990 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
3991 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), DummyString(kBytesPerKey));
3992 }
3993 delete iter;
3994 // bytes read for user iterator shouldn't count against the rate limit.
3995 rate_limited_bytes_by_pri =
3996 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_LOW) +
3997 options.rate_limiter->GetTotalBytesThrough(Env::IO_USER);
3998 ASSERT_EQ(rate_limited_bytes,
3999 static_cast<size_t>(rate_limited_bytes_by_pri));
4000 }
4001 }
4002}
4003
4004// Make sure DB can be reopen with reduced number of levels, given no file
4005// is on levels higher than the new num_levels.
4006TEST_F(DBTest2, ReduceLevel) {
4007 Options options;
4008 options.env = env_;
4009 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
4010 options.num_levels = 7;
4011 Reopen(options);
4012 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
4013 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4014 MoveFilesToLevel(6);
4015 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,0,0,0,0,1", FilesPerLevel());
4016 CompactRangeOptions compact_options;
4017 compact_options.change_level = true;
4018 compact_options.target_level = 1;
4019 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(compact_options, nullptr, nullptr));
4020 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel());
4021 options.num_levels = 3;
4022 Reopen(options);
4023 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel());
4024}

4026// Test that ReadCallback is actually used in both memtbale and sst tables
4027TEST_F(DBTest2, ReadCallbackTest) {
4028 Options options;
4029 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
4030 options.num_levels = 7;
4031 options.env = env_;
4032 Reopen(options);
4033 std::vector<const Snapshot*> snapshots;
4034 // Try to create a db with multiple layers and a memtable
4035 const std::string key = "foo";
4036 const std::string value = "bar";
4037 // This test assumes that the seq start with 1 and increased by 1 after each
4038 // write batch of size 1. If that behavior changes, the test needs to be
4039 // updated as well.
4040 // TODO(myabandeh): update this test to use the seq number that is returned by
4041 // the DB instead of assuming what seq the DB used.
4042 int i = 1;
4043 for (; i < 10; i++) {
4044 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, value + std::to_string(i)));
4045 // Take a snapshot to avoid the value being removed during compaction
4046 auto snapshot = dbfull()->GetSnapshot();
4047 snapshots.push_back(snapshot);
4048 }
4049 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4050 for (; i < 20; i++) {
4051 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, value + std::to_string(i)));
4052 // Take a snapshot to avoid the value being removed during compaction
4053 auto snapshot = dbfull()->GetSnapshot();
4054 snapshots.push_back(snapshot);
4055 }
4056 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4057 MoveFilesToLevel(6);
4058 ASSERT_EQ("0,0,0,0,0,0,2", FilesPerLevel());
4059 for (; i < 30; i++) {
4060 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, value + std::to_string(i)));
4061 auto snapshot = dbfull()->GetSnapshot();
4062 snapshots.push_back(snapshot);
4063 }
4064 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4065 ASSERT_EQ("1,0,0,0,0,0,2", FilesPerLevel());
4066 // And also add some values to the memtable
4067 for (; i < 40; i++) {
4068 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, value + std::to_string(i)));
4069 auto snapshot = dbfull()->GetSnapshot();
4070 snapshots.push_back(snapshot);
4071 }
4072
4073 class TestReadCallback : public ReadCallback {
4074 public:
4075 explicit TestReadCallback(SequenceNumber snapshot)
4076 : ReadCallback(snapshot), snapshot_(snapshot) {}
4077 bool IsVisibleFullCheck(SequenceNumber seq) override {
4078 return seq <= snapshot_;
4079 }
4080
4081 private:
4082 SequenceNumber snapshot_;
4083 };
4084
4085 for (int seq = 1; seq < i; seq++) {
4086 PinnableSlice pinnable_val;
4087 ReadOptions roptions;
4088 TestReadCallback callback(seq);
4089 bool dont_care = true;
4090 DBImpl::GetImplOptions get_impl_options;
4091 get_impl_options.column_family = dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily();
4092 get_impl_options.value = &pinnable_val;
4093 get_impl_options.value_found = &dont_care;
4094 get_impl_options.callback = &callback;
4095 Status s = dbfull()->GetImpl(roptions, key, get_impl_options);
4096 ASSERT_TRUE(s.ok());
4097 // Assuming that after each Put the DB increased seq by one, the value and
4098 // seq number must be equal since we also inc value by 1 after each Put.
4099 ASSERT_EQ(value + std::to_string(seq), pinnable_val.ToString());
4100 }
4101
4102 for (auto snapshot : snapshots) {
4103 dbfull()->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot);
4104 }
4105}
