4107
4108TEST_F(DBTest2, LiveFilesOmitObsoleteFiles) {
4109 // Regression test for race condition where an obsolete file is returned to
4110 // user as a "live file" but then deleted, all while file deletions are
4111 // disabled.
4112 //
4113 // It happened like this:
4114 //
4115 // 1. [flush thread] Log file "x.log" found by FindObsoleteFiles
4116 // 2. [user thread] DisableFileDeletions, GetSortedWalFiles are called and the
4117 // latter returned "x.log"
4118 // 3. [flush thread] PurgeObsoleteFiles deleted "x.log"
4119 // 4. [user thread] Reading "x.log" failed
4120 //
4121 // Unfortunately the only regression test I can come up with involves sleep.
4122 // We cannot set SyncPoints to repro since, once the fix is applied, the
4123 // SyncPoints would cause a deadlock as the repro's sequence of events is now
4124 // prohibited.
4125 //
4126 // Instead, if we sleep for a second between Find and Purge, and ensure the
4127 // read attempt happens after purge, then the sequence of events will almost
4128 // certainly happen on the old code.
4129 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
4130 {"DBImpl::BackgroundCallFlush:FilesFound",
4131 "DBTest2::LiveFilesOmitObsoleteFiles:FlushTriggered"},
4132 {"DBImpl::PurgeObsoleteFiles:End",
4133 "DBTest2::LiveFilesOmitObsoleteFiles:LiveFilesCaptured"},
4134 });
4135 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
4136 "DBImpl::PurgeObsoleteFiles:Begin",
4137 [&](void* /*arg*/) { env_->SleepForMicroseconds(1000000); });
4138 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
4139
4140 ASSERT_OK(Put("key", "val"));
4141 FlushOptions flush_opts;
4142 flush_opts.wait = false;
4143 ASSERT_OK(db_->Flush(flush_opts));
4144 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::LiveFilesOmitObsoleteFiles:FlushTriggered");
4145
4146 ASSERT_OK(db_->DisableFileDeletions());
4147 VectorWalPtr log_files;
4148 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetSortedWalFiles(log_files));
4149 TEST_SYNC_POINT("DBTest2::LiveFilesOmitObsoleteFiles:LiveFilesCaptured");
4150 for (const auto& log_file : log_files) {
4151 ASSERT_OK(env_->FileExists(LogFileName(dbname_, log_file->LogNumber())));
4152 }
4153
4154 ASSERT_OK(db_->EnableFileDeletions());
4155 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
4156}
4157
4158TEST_F(DBTest2, TestNumPread) {
4159 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4160 bool prefetch_supported =
4161 test::IsPrefetchSupported(env_->GetFileSystem(), dbname_);
4162 // disable block cache
4163 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4164 table_options.no_block_cache = true;
4165 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4166 Reopen(options);
4167 env_->count_random_reads_ = true;
4168 env_->random_file_open_counter_.store(0);
4169 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "foo"));
4170 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
4171 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4172 if (prefetch_supported) {
4173 // After flush, we'll open the file and read footer, meta block,
4174 // property block and index block.
4175 ASSERT_EQ(4, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4176 } else {
4177 // With prefetch not supported, we will do a single read into a buffer
4178 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4179 }
4180 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_file_open_counter_.load());
4181
4182 // One pread per a normal data block read
4183 env_->random_file_open_counter_.store(0);
4184 env_->random_read_counter_.Reset();
4185 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo"));
4186 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4187 // All files are already opened.
4188 ASSERT_EQ(0, env_->random_file_open_counter_.load());
4189
4190 env_->random_file_open_counter_.store(0);
4191 env_->random_read_counter_.Reset();
4192 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar2", "foo2"));
4193 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo2", "bar2"));
4194 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4195 if (prefetch_supported) {
4196 // After flush, we'll open the file and read footer, meta block,
4197 // property block and index block.
4198 ASSERT_EQ(4, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4199 } else {
4200 // With prefetch not supported, we will do a single read into a buffer
4201 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4202 }
4203 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_file_open_counter_.load());
4204
4205 env_->random_file_open_counter_.store(0);
4206 env_->random_read_counter_.Reset();
4207 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
4208 if (prefetch_supported) {
4209 // Compaction needs two input blocks, which requires 2 preads, and
4210 // generate a new SST file which needs 4 preads (footer, meta block,
4211 // property block and index block). In total 6.
4212 ASSERT_EQ(6, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4213 } else {
4214 // With prefetch off, compaction needs two input blocks,
4215 // followed by a single buffered read. In total 3.
4216 ASSERT_EQ(3, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4217 }
4218 // All compaction input files should have already been opened.
4219 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_file_open_counter_.load());
4220
4221 // One pread per a normal data block read
4222 env_->random_file_open_counter_.store(0);
4223 env_->random_read_counter_.Reset();
4224 ASSERT_EQ("foo2", Get("bar2"));
4225 ASSERT_EQ(1, env_->random_read_counter_.Read());
4226 // SST files are already opened.
4227 ASSERT_EQ(0, env_->random_file_open_counter_.load());
4228}
4229
4230class TraceExecutionResultHandler : public TraceRecordResult::Handler {
4231 public:
4232 TraceExecutionResultHandler() = default;
4233 ~TraceExecutionResultHandler() override = default;
4234
4235 Status Handle(const StatusOnlyTraceExecutionResult& result) override {
4236 if (result.GetStartTimestamp() > result.GetEndTimestamp()) {
4237 return Status::InvalidArgument("Invalid timestamps.");
4238 }
4239 result.GetStatus().PermitUncheckedError();
4240 switch (result.GetTraceType()) {
4241 case kTraceWrite: {
4242 total_latency_ += result.GetLatency();
4243 cnt_++;
4244 writes_++;
4245 break;
4246 }
4247 default:
4248 return Status::Corruption("Type mismatch.");
4249 }
4250 return Status::OK();
4251 }
4252
4253 Status Handle(const SingleValueTraceExecutionResult& result) override {
4254 if (result.GetStartTimestamp() > result.GetEndTimestamp()) {
4255 return Status::InvalidArgument("Invalid timestamps.");
4256 }
4257 result.GetStatus().PermitUncheckedError();
4258 switch (result.GetTraceType()) {
4259 case kTraceGet: {
4260 total_latency_ += result.GetLatency();
4261 cnt_++;
4262 gets_++;
4263 break;
4264 }
4265 default:
4266 return Status::Corruption("Type mismatch.");
4267 }
4268 return Status::OK();
4269 }
4270
4271 Status Handle(const MultiValuesTraceExecutionResult& result) override {
4272 if (result.GetStartTimestamp() > result.GetEndTimestamp()) {
4273 return Status::InvalidArgument("Invalid timestamps.");
4274 }
4275 for (const Status& s : result.GetMultiStatus()) {
4276 s.PermitUncheckedError();
4277 }
4278 switch (result.GetTraceType()) {
4279 case kTraceMultiGet: {
4280 total_latency_ += result.GetLatency();
4281 cnt_++;
4282 multigets_++;
4283 break;
4284 }
4285 default:
4286 return Status::Corruption("Type mismatch.");
4287 }
4288 return Status::OK();
4289 }
4290
4291 Status Handle(const IteratorTraceExecutionResult& result) override {
4292 if (result.GetStartTimestamp() > result.GetEndTimestamp()) {
4293 return Status::InvalidArgument("Invalid timestamps.");
4294 }
4295 result.GetStatus().PermitUncheckedError();
4296 switch (result.GetTraceType()) {
4297 case kTraceIteratorSeek:
4298 case kTraceIteratorSeekForPrev: {
4299 total_latency_ += result.GetLatency();
4300 cnt_++;
4301 seeks_++;
4302 break;
4303 }
4304 default:
4305 return Status::Corruption("Type mismatch.");
4306 }
4307 return Status::OK();
4308 }
4309
4310 void Reset() {
4311 total_latency_ = 0;
4312 cnt_ = 0;
4313 writes_ = 0;
4314 gets_ = 0;
4315 seeks_ = 0;
4316 multigets_ = 0;
4317 }
4318
4319 double GetAvgLatency() const {
4320 return cnt_ == 0 ? 0.0 : 1.0 * total_latency_ / cnt_;
4321 }
4322
4323 int GetNumWrites() const { return writes_; }
4324
4325 int GetNumGets() const { return gets_; }
4326
4327 int GetNumIterSeeks() const { return seeks_; }
4328
4329 int GetNumMultiGets() const { return multigets_; }
4330
4331 private:
4332 std::atomic<uint64_t> total_latency_{0};
4333 std::atomic<uint32_t> cnt_{0};
4334 std::atomic<int> writes_{0};
4335 std::atomic<int> gets_{0};
4336 std::atomic<int> seeks_{0};
4337 std::atomic<int> multigets_{0};
4338};
4339
4340TEST_F(DBTest2, TraceAndReplay) {
4341 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4342 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
4343 ReadOptions ro;
4344 WriteOptions wo;
4345 TraceOptions trace_opts;
4346 EnvOptions env_opts;
4347 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
4348 Random rnd(301);
4349 Iterator* single_iter = nullptr;
4350
4351 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->EndTrace().IsIOError());
4352
4353 std::string trace_filename = dbname_ + "/rocksdb.trace";
4354 std::unique_ptr<TraceWriter> trace_writer;
4355 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceWriter(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_writer));
4356 ASSERT_OK(db_->StartTrace(trace_opts, std::move(trace_writer)));
4357
4358 // 5 Writes
4359 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "a", "1"));
4360 ASSERT_OK(Merge(0, "b", "2"));
4361 ASSERT_OK(Delete(0, "c"));
4362 ASSERT_OK(SingleDelete(0, "d"));
4363 ASSERT_OK(db_->DeleteRange(wo, dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily(), "e", "f"));
4364
4365 // 6th Write
4366 WriteBatch batch;
4367 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("f", "11"));
4368 ASSERT_OK(batch.Merge("g", "12"));
4369 ASSERT_OK(batch.Delete("h"));
4370 ASSERT_OK(batch.SingleDelete("i"));
4371 ASSERT_OK(batch.DeleteRange("j", "k"));
4372 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(wo, &batch));
4373
4374 // 2 Seek(ForPrev)s
4375 single_iter = db_->NewIterator(ro);
4376 single_iter->Seek("f"); // Seek 1
4377 single_iter->SeekForPrev("g");
4378 ASSERT_OK(single_iter->status());
4379 delete single_iter;
4380
4381 // 2 Gets
4382 ASSERT_EQ("1", Get(0, "a"));
4383 ASSERT_EQ("12", Get(0, "g"));
4384
4385 // 7th and 8th Write, 3rd Get
4386 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "bar"));
4387 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "rocksdb", "rocks"));
4388 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get(1, "leveldb"));
4389
4390 // Total Write x 8, Get x 3, Seek x 2.
4391 ASSERT_OK(db_->EndTrace());
4392 // These should not get into the trace file as it is after EndTrace.
4393 ASSERT_OK(Put("hello", "world"));
4394 ASSERT_OK(Merge("foo", "bar"));
4395
4396 // Open another db, replay, and verify the data
4397 std::string value;
4398 std::string dbname2 = test::PerThreadDBPath(env_, "/db_replay");
4399 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
4400
4401 // Using a different name than db2, to pacify infer's use-after-lifetime
4402 // warnings (http://fbinfer.com).
4403 DB* db2_init = nullptr;
4404 options.create_if_missing = true;
4405 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname2, &db2_init));
4406 ColumnFamilyHandle* cf;
4407 ASSERT_OK(
4408 db2_init->CreateColumnFamily(ColumnFamilyOptions(), "pikachu", &cf));
4409 delete cf;
4410 delete db2_init;
4411
4412 DB* db2 = nullptr;
4413 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
4414 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options;
4415 cf_options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
4416 column_families.emplace_back("default", cf_options);
4417 column_families.emplace_back("pikachu", ColumnFamilyOptions());
4418 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
4419 DBOptions db_opts;
4420 db_opts.env = env_;
4421 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(db_opts, dbname2, column_families, &handles, &db2));
4422
4423 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(100);
4424 // Verify that the keys don't already exist
4425 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value).IsNotFound());
4426 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value).IsNotFound());
4427
4428 std::unique_ptr<TraceReader> trace_reader;
4429 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceReader(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_reader));
4430 std::unique_ptr<Replayer> replayer;
4431 ASSERT_OK(
4432 db2->NewDefaultReplayer(handles, std::move(trace_reader), &replayer));
4433
4434 TraceExecutionResultHandler res_handler;
4435 std::function<void(Status, std::unique_ptr<TraceRecordResult> &&)> res_cb =
4436 [&res_handler](Status exec_s, std::unique_ptr<TraceRecordResult>&& res) {
4437 ASSERT_TRUE(exec_s.ok() || exec_s.IsNotSupported());
4438 if (res != nullptr) {
4439 ASSERT_OK(res->Accept(&res_handler));
4440 res.reset();
4441 }
4442 };
4443
4444 // Unprepared replay should fail with Status::Incomplete()
4445 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(), nullptr).IsIncomplete());
4446 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
4447 // Ok to repeatedly Prepare().
4448 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
4449 // Replay using 1 thread, 1x speed.
4450 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(1, 1.0), res_cb));
4451 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4452 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 8);
4453 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 3);
4454 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 2);
4455 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4456 res_handler.Reset();
4457
4458 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value));
4459 ASSERT_EQ("1", value);
4460 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value));
4461 ASSERT_EQ("12", value);
4462 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "hello", &value).IsNotFound());
4463 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "world", &value).IsNotFound());
4464
4465 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[1], "foo", &value));
4466 ASSERT_EQ("bar", value);
4467 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[1], "rocksdb", &value));
4468 ASSERT_EQ("rocks", value);
4469
4470 // Re-replay should fail with Status::Incomplete() if Prepare() was not
4471 // called. Currently we don't distinguish between unprepared and trace end.
4472 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(), nullptr).IsIncomplete());
4473
4474 // Re-replay using 2 threads, 2x speed.
4475 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
4476 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(2, 2.0), res_cb));
4477 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4478 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 8);
4479 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 3);
4480 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 2);
4481 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4482 res_handler.Reset();
4483
4484 // Re-replay using 2 threads, 1/2 speed.
4485 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
4486 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(2, 0.5), res_cb));
4487 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4488 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 8);
4489 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 3);
4490 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 2);
4491 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4492 res_handler.Reset();
4493
4494 replayer.reset();
4495
4496 for (auto handle : handles) {
4497 delete handle;
4498 }
4499 delete db2;
4500 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
4501}

4503TEST_F(DBTest2, TraceAndManualReplay) {
4504 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4505 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
4506 ReadOptions ro;
4507 WriteOptions wo;
4508 TraceOptions trace_opts;
4509 EnvOptions env_opts;
4510 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
4511 Random rnd(301);
4512 Iterator* single_iter = nullptr;
4513
4514 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->EndTrace().IsIOError());
4515
4516 std::string trace_filename = dbname_ + "/rocksdb.trace";
4517 std::unique_ptr<TraceWriter> trace_writer;
4518 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceWriter(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_writer));
4519 ASSERT_OK(db_->StartTrace(trace_opts, std::move(trace_writer)));
4520
4521 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "a", "1"));
4522 ASSERT_OK(Merge(0, "b", "2"));
4523 ASSERT_OK(Delete(0, "c"));
4524 ASSERT_OK(SingleDelete(0, "d"));
4525 ASSERT_OK(db_->DeleteRange(wo, dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily(), "e", "f"));
4526
4527 WriteBatch batch;
4528 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("f", "11"));
4529 ASSERT_OK(batch.Merge("g", "12"));
4530 ASSERT_OK(batch.Delete("h"));
4531 ASSERT_OK(batch.SingleDelete("i"));
4532 ASSERT_OK(batch.DeleteRange("j", "k"));
4533 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(wo, &batch));
4534
4535 single_iter = db_->NewIterator(ro);
4536 single_iter->Seek("f");
4537 single_iter->SeekForPrev("g");
4538 ASSERT_OK(single_iter->status());
4539 delete single_iter;
4540
4541 // Write some sequenced keys for testing lower/upper bounds of iterator.
4542 batch.Clear();
4543 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("iter-0", "iter-0"));
4544 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("iter-1", "iter-1"));
4545 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("iter-2", "iter-2"));
4546 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("iter-3", "iter-3"));
4547 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("iter-4", "iter-4"));
4548 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(wo, &batch));
4549
4550 ReadOptions bounded_ro = ro;
4551 Slice lower_bound("iter-1");
4552 Slice upper_bound("iter-3");
4553 bounded_ro.iterate_lower_bound = &lower_bound;
4554 bounded_ro.iterate_upper_bound = &upper_bound;
4555 single_iter = db_->NewIterator(bounded_ro);
4556 single_iter->Seek("iter-0");
4557 ASSERT_EQ(single_iter->key().ToString(), "iter-1");
4558 single_iter->Seek("iter-2");
4559 ASSERT_EQ(single_iter->key().ToString(), "iter-2");
4560 single_iter->Seek("iter-4");
4561 ASSERT_FALSE(single_iter->Valid());
4562 single_iter->SeekForPrev("iter-0");
4563 ASSERT_FALSE(single_iter->Valid());
4564 single_iter->SeekForPrev("iter-2");
4565 ASSERT_EQ(single_iter->key().ToString(), "iter-2");
4566 single_iter->SeekForPrev("iter-4");
4567 ASSERT_EQ(single_iter->key().ToString(), "iter-2");
4568 ASSERT_OK(single_iter->status());
4569 delete single_iter;
4570
4571 ASSERT_EQ("1", Get(0, "a"));
4572 ASSERT_EQ("12", Get(0, "g"));
4573
4574 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "bar"));
4575 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "rocksdb", "rocks"));
4576 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get(1, "leveldb"));
4577
4578 // Same as TraceAndReplay, Write x 8, Get x 3, Seek x 2.
4579 // Plus 1 WriteBatch for iterator with lower/upper bounds, and 6
4580 // Seek(ForPrev)s.
4581 // Total Write x 9, Get x 3, Seek x 8
4582 ASSERT_OK(db_->EndTrace());
4583 // These should not get into the trace file as it is after EndTrace.
4584 ASSERT_OK(Put("hello", "world"));
4585 ASSERT_OK(Merge("foo", "bar"));
4586
4587 // Open another db, replay, and verify the data
4588 std::string value;
4589 std::string dbname2 = test::PerThreadDBPath(env_, "/db_replay");
4590 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
4591
4592 // Using a different name than db2, to pacify infer's use-after-lifetime
4593 // warnings (http://fbinfer.com).
4594 DB* db2_init = nullptr;
4595 options.create_if_missing = true;
4596 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname2, &db2_init));
4597 ColumnFamilyHandle* cf;
4598 ASSERT_OK(
4599 db2_init->CreateColumnFamily(ColumnFamilyOptions(), "pikachu", &cf));
4600 delete cf;
4601 delete db2_init;
4602
4603 DB* db2 = nullptr;
4604 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
4605 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options;
4606 cf_options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
4607 column_families.emplace_back("default", cf_options);
4608 column_families.emplace_back("pikachu", ColumnFamilyOptions());
4609 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
4610 DBOptions db_opts;
4611 db_opts.env = env_;
4612 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(db_opts, dbname2, column_families, &handles, &db2));
4613
4614 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(100);
4615 // Verify that the keys don't already exist
4616 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value).IsNotFound());
4617 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value).IsNotFound());
4618
4619 std::unique_ptr<TraceReader> trace_reader;
4620 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceReader(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_reader));
4621 std::unique_ptr<Replayer> replayer;
4622 ASSERT_OK(
4623 db2->NewDefaultReplayer(handles, std::move(trace_reader), &replayer));
4624
4625 TraceExecutionResultHandler res_handler;
4626
4627 // Manual replay for 2 times. The 2nd checks if the replay can restart.
4628 std::unique_ptr<TraceRecord> record;
4629 std::unique_ptr<TraceRecordResult> result;
4630 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
4631 // Next should fail if unprepared.
4632 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Next(nullptr).IsIncomplete());
4633 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
4634 Status s = Status::OK();
4635 // Looping until trace end.
4636 while (s.ok()) {
4637 s = replayer->Next(&record);
4638 // Skip unsupported operations.
4639 if (s.IsNotSupported()) {
4640 continue;
4641 }
4642 if (s.ok()) {
4643 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4644 if (result != nullptr) {
4645 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler));
4646 if (record->GetTraceType() == kTraceIteratorSeek ||
4647 record->GetTraceType() == kTraceIteratorSeekForPrev) {
4648 IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord* iter_rec =
4649 dynamic_cast<IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord*>(record.get());
4650 IteratorTraceExecutionResult* iter_res =
4651 dynamic_cast<IteratorTraceExecutionResult*>(result.get());
4652 // Check if lower/upper bounds are correctly saved and decoded.
4653 std::string lower_str = iter_rec->GetLowerBound().ToString();
4654 std::string upper_str = iter_rec->GetUpperBound().ToString();
4655 std::string iter_key = iter_res->GetKey().ToString();
4656 std::string iter_value = iter_res->GetValue().ToString();
4657 if (!lower_str.empty() && !upper_str.empty()) {
4658 ASSERT_EQ(lower_str, "iter-1");
4659 ASSERT_EQ(upper_str, "iter-3");
4660 if (iter_res->GetValid()) {
4661 // If iterator is valid, then lower_bound <= key < upper_bound.
4662 ASSERT_GE(iter_key, lower_str);
4663 ASSERT_LT(iter_key, upper_str);
4664 } else {
4665 // If iterator is invalid, then
4666 // key < lower_bound or key >= upper_bound.
4667 ASSERT_TRUE(iter_key < lower_str || iter_key >= upper_str);
4668 }
4669 }
4670 // If iterator is invalid, the key and value should be empty.
4671 if (!iter_res->GetValid()) {
4672 ASSERT_TRUE(iter_key.empty());
4673 ASSERT_TRUE(iter_value.empty());
4674 }
4675 }
4676 result.reset();
4677 }
4678 }
4679 }
4680 // Status::Incomplete() will be returned when manually reading the trace
4681 // end, or Prepare() was not called.
4682 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsIncomplete());
4683 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Next(nullptr).IsIncomplete());
4684 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4685 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 9);
4686 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 3);
4687 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 8);
4688 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4689 res_handler.Reset();
4690 }
4691
4692 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value));
4693 ASSERT_EQ("1", value);
4694 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value));
4695 ASSERT_EQ("12", value);
4696 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "hello", &value).IsNotFound());
4697 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "world", &value).IsNotFound());
4698
4699 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[1], "foo", &value));
4700 ASSERT_EQ("bar", value);
4701 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[1], "rocksdb", &value));
4702 ASSERT_EQ("rocks", value);
4703
4704 // Test execution of artificially created TraceRecords.
4705 uint64_t fake_ts = 1U;
4706 // Write
4707 batch.Clear();
4708 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("trace-record-write1", "write1"));
4709 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("trace-record-write2", "write2"));
4710 record.reset(new WriteQueryTraceRecord(batch.Data(), fake_ts++));
4711 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4712 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4713 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // Write x 1
4714 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "trace-record-write1", &value));
4715 ASSERT_EQ("write1", value);
4716 ASSERT_OK(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "trace-record-write2", &value));
4717 ASSERT_EQ("write2", value);
4718 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4719 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 1);
4720 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 0);
4721 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 0);
4722 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4723 res_handler.Reset();
4724
4725 // Get related
4726 // Get an existing key.
4727 record.reset(new GetQueryTraceRecord(handles[0]->GetID(),
4728 "trace-record-write1", fake_ts++));
4729 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4730 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4731 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // Get x 1
4732 // Get an non-existing key, should still return Status::OK().
4733 record.reset(new GetQueryTraceRecord(handles[0]->GetID(), "trace-record-get",
4734 fake_ts++));
4735 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4736 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4737 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // Get x 2
4738 // Get from an invalid (non-existing) cf_id.
4739 uint32_t invalid_cf_id = handles[1]->GetID() + 1;
4740 record.reset(new GetQueryTraceRecord(invalid_cf_id, "whatever", fake_ts++));
4741 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Execute(record, &result).IsCorruption());
4742 ASSERT_TRUE(result == nullptr);
4743 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4744 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 0);
4745 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 2);
4746 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 0);
4747 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4748 res_handler.Reset();
4749
4750 // Iteration related
4751 for (IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord::SeekType seekType :
4752 {IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord::kSeek,
4753 IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord::kSeekForPrev}) {
4754 // Seek to an existing key.
4755 record.reset(new IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord(
4756 seekType, handles[0]->GetID(), "trace-record-write1", fake_ts++));
4757 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4758 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4759 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // Seek x 1 in one iteration
4760 // Seek to an non-existing key, should still return Status::OK().
4761 record.reset(new IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord(
4762 seekType, handles[0]->GetID(), "trace-record-get", fake_ts++));
4763 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4764 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4765 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // Seek x 2 in one iteration
4766 // Seek from an invalid cf_id.
4767 record.reset(new IteratorSeekQueryTraceRecord(seekType, invalid_cf_id,
4768 "whatever", fake_ts++));
4769 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Execute(record, &result).IsCorruption());
4770 ASSERT_TRUE(result == nullptr);
4771 }
4772 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4773 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 0);
4774 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 0);
4775 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 4); // Seek x 2 in two iterations
4776 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 0);
4777 res_handler.Reset();
4778
4779 // MultiGet related
4780 // Get existing keys.
4781 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4782 std::vector<uint32_t>({handles[0]->GetID(), handles[1]->GetID()}),
4783 std::vector<std::string>({"a", "foo"}), fake_ts++));
4784 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4785 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4786 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // MultiGet x 1
4787 // Get all non-existing keys, should still return Status::OK().
4788 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4789 std::vector<uint32_t>({handles[0]->GetID(), handles[1]->GetID()}),
4790 std::vector<std::string>({"no1", "no2"}), fake_ts++));
4791 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4792 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4793 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // MultiGet x 2
4794 // Get mixed of existing and non-existing keys, should still return
4795 // Status::OK().
4796 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4797 std::vector<uint32_t>({handles[0]->GetID(), handles[1]->GetID()}),
4798 std::vector<std::string>({"a", "no2"}), fake_ts++));
4799 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Execute(record, &result));
4800 ASSERT_TRUE(result != nullptr);
4801 MultiValuesTraceExecutionResult* mvr =
4802 dynamic_cast<MultiValuesTraceExecutionResult*>(result.get());
4803 ASSERT_TRUE(mvr != nullptr);
4804 ASSERT_OK(mvr->GetMultiStatus()[0]);
4805 ASSERT_TRUE(mvr->GetMultiStatus()[1].IsNotFound());
4806 ASSERT_EQ(mvr->GetValues()[0], "1");
4807 ASSERT_EQ(mvr->GetValues()[1], "");
4808 ASSERT_OK(result->Accept(&res_handler)); // MultiGet x 3
4809 // Get from an invalid (non-existing) cf_id.
4810 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4811 std::vector<uint32_t>(
4812 {handles[0]->GetID(), handles[1]->GetID(), invalid_cf_id}),
4813 std::vector<std::string>({"a", "foo", "whatever"}), fake_ts++));
4814 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Execute(record, &result).IsCorruption());
4815 ASSERT_TRUE(result == nullptr);
4816 // Empty MultiGet
4817 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4818 std::vector<uint32_t>(), std::vector<std::string>(), fake_ts++));
4819 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Execute(record, &result).IsInvalidArgument());
4820 ASSERT_TRUE(result == nullptr);
4821 // MultiGet size mismatch
4822 record.reset(new MultiGetQueryTraceRecord(
4823 std::vector<uint32_t>({handles[0]->GetID(), handles[1]->GetID()}),
4824 std::vector<std::string>({"a"}), fake_ts++));
4825 ASSERT_TRUE(replayer->Execute(record, &result).IsInvalidArgument());
4826 ASSERT_TRUE(result == nullptr);
4827 ASSERT_GE(res_handler.GetAvgLatency(), 0.0);
4828 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumWrites(), 0);
4829 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumGets(), 0);
4830 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumIterSeeks(), 0);
4831 ASSERT_EQ(res_handler.GetNumMultiGets(), 3);
4832 res_handler.Reset();
4833
4834 replayer.reset();
4835
4836 for (auto handle : handles) {
4837 delete handle;
4838 }
4839 delete db2;
4840 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
4841}

4992TEST_F(DBTest2, TraceWithFilter) {
4993 Options options = CurrentOptions();
4994 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
4995 ReadOptions ro;
4996 WriteOptions wo;
4997 TraceOptions trace_opts;
4998 EnvOptions env_opts;
4999 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
5000 Random rnd(301);
5001 Iterator* single_iter = nullptr;
5002
5003 trace_opts.filter = TraceFilterType::kTraceFilterWrite;
5004
5005 std::string trace_filename = dbname_ + "/rocksdb.trace";
5006 std::unique_ptr<TraceWriter> trace_writer;
5007 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceWriter(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_writer));
5008 ASSERT_OK(db_->StartTrace(trace_opts, std::move(trace_writer)));
5009
5010 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "a", "1"));
5011 ASSERT_OK(Merge(0, "b", "2"));
5012 ASSERT_OK(Delete(0, "c"));
5013 ASSERT_OK(SingleDelete(0, "d"));
5014 ASSERT_OK(db_->DeleteRange(wo, dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily(), "e", "f"));
5015
5016 WriteBatch batch;
5017 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put("f", "11"));
5018 ASSERT_OK(batch.Merge("g", "12"));
5019 ASSERT_OK(batch.Delete("h"));
5020 ASSERT_OK(batch.SingleDelete("i"));
5021 ASSERT_OK(batch.DeleteRange("j", "k"));
5022 ASSERT_OK(db_->Write(wo, &batch));
5023
5024 single_iter = db_->NewIterator(ro);
5025 single_iter->Seek("f");
5026 single_iter->SeekForPrev("g");
5027 delete single_iter;
5028
5029 ASSERT_EQ("1", Get(0, "a"));
5030 ASSERT_EQ("12", Get(0, "g"));
5031
5032 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "bar"));
5033 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "rocksdb", "rocks"));
5034 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get(1, "leveldb"));
5035
5036 ASSERT_OK(db_->EndTrace());
5037 // These should not get into the trace file as it is after EndTrace.
5038 ASSERT_OK(Put("hello", "world"));
5039 ASSERT_OK(Merge("foo", "bar"));
5040
5041 // Open another db, replay, and verify the data
5042 std::string value;
5043 std::string dbname2 = test::PerThreadDBPath(env_, "db_replay");
5044 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
5045
5046 // Using a different name than db2, to pacify infer's use-after-lifetime
5047 // warnings (http://fbinfer.com).
5048 DB* db2_init = nullptr;
5049 options.create_if_missing = true;
5050 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname2, &db2_init));
5051 ColumnFamilyHandle* cf;
5052 ASSERT_OK(
5053 db2_init->CreateColumnFamily(ColumnFamilyOptions(), "pikachu", &cf));
5054 delete cf;
5055 delete db2_init;
5056
5057 DB* db2 = nullptr;
5058 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
5059 ColumnFamilyOptions cf_options;
5060 cf_options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreatePutOperator();
5061 column_families.emplace_back("default", cf_options);
5062 column_families.emplace_back("pikachu", ColumnFamilyOptions());
5063 std::vector<ColumnFamilyHandle*> handles;
5064 DBOptions db_opts;
5065 db_opts.env = env_;
5066 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(db_opts, dbname2, column_families, &handles, &db2));
5067
5068 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(100);
5069 // Verify that the keys don't already exist
5070 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value).IsNotFound());
5071 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value).IsNotFound());
5072
5073 std::unique_ptr<TraceReader> trace_reader;
5074 ASSERT_OK(NewFileTraceReader(env_, env_opts, trace_filename, &trace_reader));
5075 std::unique_ptr<Replayer> replayer;
5076 ASSERT_OK(
5077 db2->NewDefaultReplayer(handles, std::move(trace_reader), &replayer));
5078 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Prepare());
5079 ASSERT_OK(replayer->Replay(ReplayOptions(), nullptr));
5080 replayer.reset();
5081
5082 // All the key-values should not present since we filter out the WRITE ops.
5083 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value).IsNotFound());
5084 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value).IsNotFound());
5085 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "hello", &value).IsNotFound());
5086 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "world", &value).IsNotFound());
5087 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "foo", &value).IsNotFound());
5088 ASSERT_TRUE(db2->Get(ro, handles[0], "rocksdb", &value).IsNotFound());
5089
5090 for (auto handle : handles) {
5091 delete handle;
5092 }
5093 delete db2;
5094 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname2, options));
5095
5096 // Set up a new db.
5097 std::string dbname3 = test::PerThreadDBPath(env_, "db_not_trace_read");
5098 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname3, options));
5099
5100 DB* db3_init = nullptr;
5101 options.create_if_missing = true;
5102 ColumnFamilyHandle* cf3;
5103 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbname3, &db3_init));
5104 ASSERT_OK(
5105 db3_init->CreateColumnFamily(ColumnFamilyOptions(), "pikachu", &cf3));
5106 delete cf3;
5107 delete db3_init;
5108
5109 column_families.clear();
5110 column_families.emplace_back("default", cf_options);
5111 column_families.emplace_back("pikachu", ColumnFamilyOptions());
5112 handles.clear();
5113
5114 DB* db3 = nullptr;
5115 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(db_opts, dbname3, column_families, &handles, &db3));
5116
5117 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(100);
5118 // Verify that the keys don't already exist
5119 ASSERT_TRUE(db3->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value).IsNotFound());
5120 ASSERT_TRUE(db3->Get(ro, handles[0], "g", &value).IsNotFound());
5121
5122 // The tracer will not record the READ ops.
5123 trace_opts.filter = TraceFilterType::kTraceFilterGet;
5124 std::string trace_filename3 = dbname_ + "/rocksdb.trace_3";
5125 std::unique_ptr<TraceWriter> trace_writer3;
5126 ASSERT_OK(
5127 NewFileTraceWriter(env_, env_opts, trace_filename3, &trace_writer3));
5128 ASSERT_OK(db3->StartTrace(trace_opts, std::move(trace_writer3)));
5129
5130 ASSERT_OK(db3->Put(wo, handles[0], "a", "1"));
5131 ASSERT_OK(db3->Merge(wo, handles[0], "b", "2"));
5132 ASSERT_OK(db3->Delete(wo, handles[0], "c"));
5133 ASSERT_OK(db3->SingleDelete(wo, handles[0], "d"));
5134
5135 ASSERT_OK(db3->Get(ro, handles[0], "a", &value));
5136 ASSERT_EQ(value, "1");
5137 ASSERT_TRUE(db3->Get(ro, handles[0], "c", &value).IsNotFound());
5138
5139 ASSERT_OK(db3->EndTrace());
5140
5141 for (auto handle : handles) {
5142 delete handle;
5143 }
5144 delete db3;
5145 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname3, options));
5146
5147 std::unique_ptr<TraceReader> trace_reader3;
5148 ASSERT_OK(
5149 NewFileTraceReader(env_, env_opts, trace_filename3, &trace_reader3));
5150
5151 // Count the number of records in the trace file;
5152 int count = 0;
5153 std::string data;
5154 Status s;
5155 while (true) {
5156 s = trace_reader3->Read(&data);
5157 if (!s.ok()) {
5158 break;
5159 }
5160 count += 1;
5161 }
5162 // We also need to count the header and footer
5163 // 4 WRITE + HEADER + FOOTER = 6
5164 ASSERT_EQ(count, 6);
5165}

5168TEST_F(DBTest2, PinnableSliceAndMmapReads) {
5169 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5170 options.env = env_;
5171 if (!IsMemoryMappedAccessSupported()) {
5172 ROCKSDB_GTEST_SKIP("Test requires default environment");
5173 return;
5174 }
5175 options.allow_mmap_reads = true;
5176 options.max_open_files = 100;
5177 options.compression = kNoCompression;
5178 Reopen(options);
5179
5180 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
5181 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5182
5183 PinnableSlice pinned_value;
5184 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", &pinned_value), Status::OK());
5185 // It is not safe to pin mmap files as they might disappear by compaction
5186 ASSERT_FALSE(pinned_value.IsPinned());
5187 ASSERT_EQ(pinned_value.ToString(), "bar");
5188
5189 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_CompactRange(
5190 0 /* level */, nullptr /* begin */, nullptr /* end */,
5191 nullptr /* column_family */, true /* disallow_trivial_move */));
5192
5193 // Ensure pinned_value doesn't rely on memory munmap'd by the above
5194 // compaction. It crashes if it does.
5195 ASSERT_EQ(pinned_value.ToString(), "bar");
5196
5197 pinned_value.Reset();
5198 // Unsafe to pin mmap files when they could be kicked out of table cache
5199 Close();
5200 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
5201 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", &pinned_value), Status::OK());
5202 ASSERT_FALSE(pinned_value.IsPinned());
5203 ASSERT_EQ(pinned_value.ToString(), "bar");
5204
5205 pinned_value.Reset();
5206 // In read-only mode with infinite capacity on table cache it should pin the
5207 // value and avoid the memcpy
5208 Close();
5209 options.max_open_files = -1;
5210 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
5211 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", &pinned_value), Status::OK());
5212 ASSERT_TRUE(pinned_value.IsPinned());
5213 ASSERT_EQ(pinned_value.ToString(), "bar");
5214}
5215
5216TEST_F(DBTest2, DISABLED_IteratorPinnedMemory) {
5217 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5218 options.create_if_missing = true;
5219 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
5220 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
5221 bbto.no_block_cache = false;
5222 bbto.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = false;
5223 bbto.block_cache = NewLRUCache(100000);
5224 bbto.block_size = 400; // small block size
5225 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5226 Reopen(options);
5227
5228 Random rnd(301);
5229 std::string v = rnd.RandomString(400);
5230
5231 // Since v is the size of a block, each key should take a block
5232 // of 400+ bytes.
5233 ASSERT_OK(Put("1", v));
5234 ASSERT_OK(Put("3", v));
5235 ASSERT_OK(Put("5", v));
5236 ASSERT_OK(Put("7", v));
5237 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5238
5239 ASSERT_EQ(0, bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage());
5240
5241 // Verify that iterators don't pin more than one data block in block cache
5242 // at each time.
5243 {
5244 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
5245 iter->SeekToFirst();
5246
5247 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5248 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5249 // Block cache should contain exactly one block.
5250 ASSERT_GT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0);
5251 ASSERT_LT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 800);
5252 iter->Next();
5253 }
5254 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
5255
5256 iter->Seek("4");
5257 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5258
5259 ASSERT_GT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0);
5260 ASSERT_LT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 800);
5261
5262 iter->Seek("3");
5263 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5264
5265 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
5266
5267 ASSERT_GT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0);
5268 ASSERT_LT(bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 800);
5269 }
5270 ASSERT_EQ(0, bbto.block_cache->GetPinnedUsage());
5271
5272 // Test compaction case
5273 ASSERT_OK(Put("2", v));
5274 ASSERT_OK(Put("5", v));
5275 ASSERT_OK(Put("6", v));
5276 ASSERT_OK(Put("8", v));
5277 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5278
5279 // Clear existing data in block cache
5280 bbto.block_cache->SetCapacity(0);
5281 bbto.block_cache->SetCapacity(100000);
5282
5283 // Verify compaction input iterators don't hold more than one data blocks at
5284 // one time.
5285 std::atomic<bool> finished(false);
5286 std::atomic<int> block_newed(0);
5287 std::atomic<int> block_destroyed(0);
5288 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5289 "Block::Block:0", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
5290 if (finished) {
5291 return;
5292 }
5293 // Two iterators. At most 2 outstanding blocks.
5294 EXPECT_GE(block_newed.load(), block_destroyed.load());
5295 EXPECT_LE(block_newed.load(), block_destroyed.load() + 1);
5296 block_newed.fetch_add(1);
5297 });
5298 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5299 "Block::~Block", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
5300 if (finished) {
5301 return;
5302 }
5303 // Two iterators. At most 2 outstanding blocks.
5304 EXPECT_GE(block_newed.load(), block_destroyed.load() + 1);
5305 EXPECT_LE(block_newed.load(), block_destroyed.load() + 2);
5306 block_destroyed.fetch_add(1);
5307 });
5308 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5309 "CompactionJob::Run:BeforeVerify",
5310 [&](void* /*arg*/) { finished = true; });
5311 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
5312
5313 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
5314
5315 // Two input files. Each of them has 4 data blocks.
5316 ASSERT_EQ(8, block_newed.load());
5317 ASSERT_EQ(8, block_destroyed.load());
5318
5319 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
5320}

5432TEST_F(DBTest2, MultiDBParallelOpenTest) {
5433 const int kNumDbs = 2;
5434 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5435 std::vector<std::string> dbnames;
5436 for (int i = 0; i < kNumDbs; ++i) {
5437 dbnames.emplace_back(test::PerThreadDBPath(env_, "db" + std::to_string(i)));
5438 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbnames.back(), options));
5439 }
5440
5441 // Verify empty DBs can be created in parallel
5442 std::vector<std::thread> open_threads;
5443 std::vector<DB*> dbs{static_cast<unsigned int>(kNumDbs), nullptr};
5444 options.create_if_missing = true;
5445 for (int i = 0; i < kNumDbs; ++i) {
5446 open_threads.emplace_back(
5447 [&](int dbnum) {
5448 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbnames[dbnum], &dbs[dbnum]));
5449 },
5450 i);
5451 }
5452
5453 // Now add some data and close, so next we can verify non-empty DBs can be
5454 // recovered in parallel
5455 for (int i = 0; i < kNumDbs; ++i) {
5456 open_threads[i].join();
5457 ASSERT_OK(dbs[i]->Put(WriteOptions(), "xi", "gua"));
5458 delete dbs[i];
5459 }
5460
5461 // Verify non-empty DBs can be recovered in parallel
5462 open_threads.clear();
5463 for (int i = 0; i < kNumDbs; ++i) {
5464 open_threads.emplace_back(
5465 [&](int dbnum) {
5466 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, dbnames[dbnum], &dbs[dbnum]));
5467 },
5468 i);
5469 }
5470
5471 // Wait and cleanup
5472 for (int i = 0; i < kNumDbs; ++i) {
5473 open_threads[i].join();
5474 delete dbs[i];
5475 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbnames[i], options));
5476 }
5477}

5539TEST_F(DBTest2, PrefixBloomReseek) {
5540 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5541 options.create_if_missing = true;
5542 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewCappedPrefixTransform(3));
5543 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
5544 bbto.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, false));
5545 bbto.whole_key_filtering = false;
5546 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5547 DestroyAndReopen(options);
5548
5549 // Construct two L1 files with keys:
5550 // f1:[aaa1 ccc1] f2:[ddd0]
5551 ASSERT_OK(Put("aaa1", ""));
5552 ASSERT_OK(Put("ccc1", ""));
5553 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5554 ASSERT_OK(Put("ddd0", ""));
5555 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5556 CompactRangeOptions cro;
5557 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kSkip;
5558 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
5559
5560 ASSERT_OK(Put("bbb1", ""));
5561
5562 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
5563 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
5564
5565 // Seeking into f1, the iterator will check bloom filter which returns the
5566 // file iterator ot be invalidate, and the cursor will put into f2, with
5567 // the next key to be "ddd0".
5568 iter->Seek("bbb1");
5569 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5570 ASSERT_EQ("bbb1", iter->key().ToString());
5571
5572 // Reseek ccc1, the L1 iterator needs to go back to f1 and reseek.
5573 iter->Seek("ccc1");
5574 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5575 ASSERT_EQ("ccc1", iter->key().ToString());
5576
5577 delete iter;
5578}

5580TEST_F(DBTest2, PrefixBloomFilteredOut) {
5581 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5582 options.create_if_missing = true;
5583 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewCappedPrefixTransform(3));
5584 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
5585 bbto.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, false));
5586 bbto.whole_key_filtering = false;
5587 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5588
5589 // This test is also the primary test for prefix_seek_opt_in_only
5590 for (bool opt_in : {false, true}) {
5591 options.prefix_seek_opt_in_only = opt_in;
5592 DestroyAndReopen(options);
5593
5594 // Construct two L1 files with keys:
5595 // f1:[aaa1 ccc1] f2:[ddd0]
5596 ASSERT_OK(Put("aaa1", ""));
5597 ASSERT_OK(Put("ccc1", ""));
5598 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5599 ASSERT_OK(Put("ddd0", ""));
5600 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5601 CompactRangeOptions cro;
5602 cro.bottommost_level_compaction = BottommostLevelCompaction::kSkip;
5603 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(cro, nullptr, nullptr));
5604
5605 ReadOptions ropts;
5606 for (bool same : {false, true}) {
5607 ropts.prefix_same_as_start = same;
5608 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iter(db_->NewIterator(ropts));
5609 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
5610
5611 iter->Seek("bbb1");
5612 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
5613 if (opt_in && !same) {
5614 // Unbounded total order seek
5615 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5616 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), "ccc1");
5617 } else {
5618 // Bloom filter is filterd out by f1. When same == false, this is just
5619 // one valid position following the contract. Postioning to ccc1 or ddd0
5620 // is also valid. This is just to validate the behavior of the current
5621 // implementation. If underlying implementation changes, the test might
5622 // fail here.
5623 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
5624 }
5625 }
5626 }
5627}

5629TEST_F(DBTest2, RowCacheSnapshot) {
5630 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5631 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
5632 options.row_cache = NewLRUCache(8 * 8192);
5633 DestroyAndReopen(options);
5634
5635 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar1"));
5636
5637 const Snapshot* s1 = db_->GetSnapshot();
5638
5639 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar2"));
5640 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5641
5642 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo2", "bar"));
5643 const Snapshot* s2 = db_->GetSnapshot();
5644 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo3", "bar"));
5645 const Snapshot* s3 = db_->GetSnapshot();
5646
5647 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 0);
5648 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 0);
5649 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo"), "bar2");
5650 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 0);
5651 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 1);
5652 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo"), "bar2");
5653 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 1);
5654 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 1);
5655 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", s1), "bar1");
5656 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 1);
5657 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 2);
5658 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", s2), "bar2");
5659 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 2);
5660 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 2);
5661 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", s1), "bar1");
5662 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 3);
5663 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 2);
5664 ASSERT_EQ(Get("foo", s3), "bar2");
5665 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_HIT), 4);
5666 ASSERT_EQ(TestGetTickerCount(options, ROW_CACHE_MISS), 2);
5667
5668 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s1);
5669 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s2);
5670 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s3);
5671}
5672
5673// When DB is reopened with multiple column families, the manifest file
5674// is written after the first CF is flushed, and it is written again
5675// after each flush. If DB crashes between the flushes, the flushed CF
5676// flushed will pass the latest log file, and now we require it not
5677// to be corrupted, and triggering a corruption report.
5678// We need to fix the bug and enable the test.
5679TEST_F(DBTest2, CrashInRecoveryMultipleCF) {
5680 const std::vector<std::string> sync_points = {
5681 "DBImpl::RecoverLogFiles:BeforeFlushFinalMemtable",
5682 "VersionSet::ProcessManifestWrites:BeforeWriteLastVersionEdit:0"};
5683 for (const auto& test_sync_point : sync_points) {
5684 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5685 // First destroy original db to ensure a clean start.
5686 DestroyAndReopen(options);
5687 options.create_if_missing = true;
5688 options.wal_recovery_mode = WALRecoveryMode::kPointInTimeRecovery;
5689 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
5690 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
5691 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5692 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "bar"));
5693 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
5694 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
5695 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "bar"));
5696 // The value is large enough to be divided to two blocks.
5697 std::string large_value(400, ' ');
5698 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo1", large_value));
5699 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo2", large_value));
5700 Close();
5701
5702 // Corrupt the log file in the middle, so that it is not corrupted
5703 // in the tail.
5704 std::vector<std::string> filenames;
5705 ASSERT_OK(env_->GetChildren(dbname_, &filenames));
5706 for (const auto& f : filenames) {
5707 uint64_t number;
5708 FileType type;
5709 if (ParseFileName(f, &number, &type) && type == FileType::kWalFile) {
5710 std::string fname = dbname_ + "/" + f;
5711 std::string file_content;
5712 ASSERT_OK(ReadFileToString(env_, fname, &file_content));
5713 file_content[400] = 'h';
5714 file_content[401] = 'a';
5715 ASSERT_OK(WriteStringToFile(env_, file_content, fname, false));
5716 break;
5717 }
5718 }
5719
5720 // Reopen and freeze the file system after the first manifest write.
5721 FaultInjectionTestEnv fit_env(options.env);
5722 options.env = &fit_env;
5723 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
5724 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5725 test_sync_point,
5726 [&](void* /*arg*/) { fit_env.SetFilesystemActive(false); });
5727 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
5728 ASSERT_NOK(TryReopenWithColumnFamilies(
5729 {kDefaultColumnFamilyName, "pikachu"}, options));
5730 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
5731
5732 fit_env.SetFilesystemActive(true);
5733 // If we continue using failure ingestion Env, it will conplain something
5734 // when renaming current file, which is not expected. Need to investigate
5735 // why.
5736 options.env = env_;
5737 ASSERT_OK(TryReopenWithColumnFamilies({kDefaultColumnFamilyName, "pikachu"},
5738 options));
5739 }
5740}

5776TEST_F(DBTest2, BackgroundPurgeTest) {
5777 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5778 options.write_buffer_manager =
5779 std::make_shared<ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::WriteBufferManager>(1 << 20);
5780 options.avoid_unnecessary_blocking_io = true;
5781 DestroyAndReopen(options);
5782 size_t base_value = options.write_buffer_manager->memory_usage();
5783
5784 ASSERT_OK(Put("a", "a"));
5785 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
5786 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
5787 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5788 size_t value = options.write_buffer_manager->memory_usage();
5789 ASSERT_GT(value, base_value);
5790
5791 db_->GetEnv()->SetBackgroundThreads(1, Env::Priority::HIGH);
5792 test::SleepingBackgroundTask sleeping_task_after;
5793 db_->GetEnv()->Schedule(&test::SleepingBackgroundTask::DoSleepTask,
5794 &sleeping_task_after, Env::Priority::HIGH);
5795 delete iter;
5796
5797 Env::Default()->SleepForMicroseconds(100000);
5798 value = options.write_buffer_manager->memory_usage();
5799 ASSERT_GT(value, base_value);
5800
5801 sleeping_task_after.WakeUp();
5802 sleeping_task_after.WaitUntilDone();
5803
5804 test::SleepingBackgroundTask sleeping_task_after2;
5805 db_->GetEnv()->Schedule(&test::SleepingBackgroundTask::DoSleepTask,
5806 &sleeping_task_after2, Env::Priority::HIGH);
5807 sleeping_task_after2.WakeUp();
5808 sleeping_task_after2.WaitUntilDone();
5809
5810 value = options.write_buffer_manager->memory_usage();
5811 ASSERT_EQ(base_value, value);
5812}

5884TEST_F(DBTest2, BlockBasedTablePrefixIndexSeekForPrev) {
5885 // create a DB with block prefix index
5886 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
5887 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5888 table_options.block_size = 300;
5889 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kHashSearch;
5890 table_options.index_shortening =
5891 BlockBasedTableOptions::IndexShorteningMode::kNoShortening;
5892 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
5893 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(1));
5894
5895 Reopen(options);
5896
5897 Random rnd(301);
5898 std::string large_value = rnd.RandomString(500);
5899
5900 ASSERT_OK(Put("a1", large_value));
5901 ASSERT_OK(Put("x1", large_value));
5902 ASSERT_OK(Put("y1", large_value));
5903 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5904
5905 {
5906 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
5907 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
5908 iterator->SeekForPrev("x3");
5909 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
5910 ASSERT_EQ("x1", iterator->key().ToString());
5911
5912 iterator->SeekForPrev("a3");
5913 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
5914 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
5915
5916 iterator->SeekForPrev("y3");
5917 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
5918 ASSERT_EQ("y1", iterator->key().ToString());
5919
5920 // Query more than one non-existing prefix to cover the case both
5921 // of empty hash bucket and hash bucket conflict.
5922 iterator->SeekForPrev("b1");
5923 // Result should be not valid or "a1".
5924 if (iterator->Valid()) {
5925 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
5926 }
5927
5928 iterator->SeekForPrev("c1");
5929 // Result should be not valid or "a1".
5930 if (iterator->Valid()) {
5931 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
5932 }
5933
5934 iterator->SeekForPrev("d1");
5935 // Result should be not valid or "a1".
5936 if (iterator->Valid()) {
5937 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
5938 }
5939
5940 iterator->SeekForPrev("y3");
5941 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
5942 ASSERT_EQ("y1", iterator->key().ToString());
5943 }
5944}

5949 options.max_open_files = 20;

5986TEST_F(DBTest2, ChangePrefixExtractor) {
5987 for (bool use_partitioned_filter : {true, false}) {
5988 // create a DB with block prefix index
5989 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
5990 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5991 options.prefix_seek_opt_in_only = false; // Use legacy prefix seek
5992
5993 // Sometimes filter is checked based on upper bound. Assert counters
5994 // for that case. Otherwise, only check data correctness.
5995 bool expect_filter_check = !use_partitioned_filter;
5996 table_options.partition_filters = use_partitioned_filter;
5997 if (use_partitioned_filter) {
5998 table_options.index_type =
5999 BlockBasedTableOptions::IndexType::kTwoLevelIndexSearch;
6000 }
6001 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, false));
6002
6003 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6004 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
6005
6006 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(2));
6007 DestroyAndReopen(options);
6008
6009 Random rnd(301);
6010
6011 ASSERT_OK(Put("aa", ""));
6012 ASSERT_OK(Put("xb", ""));
6013 ASSERT_OK(Put("xx1", ""));
6014 ASSERT_OK(Put("xz1", ""));
6015 ASSERT_OK(Put("zz", ""));
6016 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6017
6018 // After reopening DB with prefix size 2 => 1, prefix extractor
6019 // won't take effective unless it won't change results based
6020 // on upper bound and seek key.
6021 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(1));
6022 Reopen(options);
6023
6024 {
6025 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
6026 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6027 iterator->Seek("xa");
6028 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6029 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6030 if (expect_filter_check) {
6031 EXPECT_EQ(0, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6032 }
6033
6034 iterator->Seek("xz");
6035 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6036 ASSERT_EQ("xz1", iterator->key().ToString());
6037 if (expect_filter_check) {
6038 EXPECT_EQ(0, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6039 }
6040 }
6041
6042 std::string ub_str = "xg9";
6043 Slice ub(ub_str);
6044 ReadOptions ro;
6045 ro.iterate_upper_bound = &ub;
6046
6047 {
6048 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ro));
6049 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6050
6051 // SeekForPrev() never uses prefix bloom if it is changed.
6052 iterator->SeekForPrev("xg0");
6053 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6054 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6055 if (expect_filter_check) {
6056 EXPECT_EQ(0, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6057 }
6058 }
6059
6060 ub_str = "xx9";
6061 ub = Slice(ub_str);
6062 {
6063 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ro));
6064 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6065
6066 iterator->Seek("x");
6067 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6068 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6069 if (expect_filter_check) {
6070 EXPECT_EQ(0, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6071 }
6072
6073 iterator->Seek("xx0");
6074 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6075 ASSERT_EQ("xx1", iterator->key().ToString());
6076 if (expect_filter_check) {
6077 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6078 }
6079 }
6080
6081 CompactRangeOptions compact_range_opts;
6082 compact_range_opts.bottommost_level_compaction =
6083 BottommostLevelCompaction::kForce;
6084 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(compact_range_opts, nullptr, nullptr));
6085 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(compact_range_opts, nullptr, nullptr));
6086
6087 // Re-execute similar queries after a full compaction
6088 {
6089 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
6090
6091 iterator->Seek("x");
6092 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6093 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6094 if (expect_filter_check) {
6095 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6096 }
6097
6098 iterator->Seek("xg");
6099 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6100 ASSERT_EQ("xx1", iterator->key().ToString());
6101 if (expect_filter_check) {
6102 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6103 }
6104
6105 iterator->Seek("xz");
6106 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6107 ASSERT_EQ("xz1", iterator->key().ToString());
6108 if (expect_filter_check) {
6109 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6110 }
6111
6112 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6113 }
6114 {
6115 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ro));
6116
6117 iterator->SeekForPrev("xx0");
6118 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6119 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6120 if (expect_filter_check) {
6121 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6122 }
6123
6124 iterator->Seek("xx0");
6125 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6126 ASSERT_EQ("xx1", iterator->key().ToString());
6127 if (expect_filter_check) {
6128 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6129 }
6130
6131 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6132 }
6133
6134 ub_str = "xg9";
6135 ub = Slice(ub_str);
6136 {
6137 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ro));
6138 iterator->SeekForPrev("xg0");
6139 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6140 ASSERT_EQ("xb", iterator->key().ToString());
6141 if (expect_filter_check) {
6142 EXPECT_EQ(1, PopTicker(options, NON_LAST_LEVEL_SEEK_FILTER_MATCH));
6143 }
6144 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6145 }
6146 }
6147}

6342 iterator->Seek("z");
6343 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6344 ASSERT_EQ("y1", iterator->key().ToString());
6345 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6346 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6347
6348 ub = "b1";
6349 iterator->Seek("c");
6350 ASSERT_FALSE(iterator->Valid());
6351 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6352 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6353
6354 ub = "b";
6355 iterator->Seek("c9");
6356 ASSERT_FALSE(iterator->Valid());
6357 // Fails if ReverseBytewiseComparator::IsSameLengthImmediateSuccessor
6358 // is "correctly" implemented.
6359 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6360 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6361
6362 ub = "a";
6363 iterator->Seek("b9");
6364 // Fails if ReverseBytewiseComparator::IsSameLengthImmediateSuccessor
6365 // is "correctly" implemented.
6366 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6367 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
6368 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6369 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6370
6371 ub = "b";
6372 iterator->Seek("a");
6373 ASSERT_FALSE(iterator->Valid());
6374 // Fails if ReverseBytewiseComparator::IsSameLengthImmediateSuccessor
6375 // matches BytewiseComparator::IsSameLengthImmediateSuccessor. Upper
6376 // comparing before seek key prevents a real bug from surfacing.
6377 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6378 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6379
6380 ub = "b1";
6381 iterator->SeekForPrev("b9");
6382 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6383 // Fails if ReverseBytewiseComparator::IsSameLengthImmediateSuccessor
6384 // is "correctly" implemented.
6385 ASSERT_EQ("x1", iterator->key().ToString());
6386 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6387 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6388
6389 ub = "a";
6390 iterator->SeekToLast();
6391 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6392 ASSERT_EQ("a1", iterator->key().ToString());
6393
6394 iterator->SeekToFirst();
6395 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6396 ASSERT_EQ("y1", iterator->key().ToString());
6397 }
6398
6399 // Now something a bit different, related to "short" keys that
6400 // auto_prefix_mode can omit. See "BUG" section of auto_prefix_mode.
6401 options.comparator = BytewiseComparator();
6402 for (const auto config : {"fixed:2", "capped:2"}) {
6403 ASSERT_OK(SliceTransform::CreateFromString(ConfigOptions(), config,
6404 &options.prefix_extractor));
6405
6406 // FIXME: kHashSearch, etc. requires all keys be InDomain
6407 if (StartsWith(config, "fixed") &&
6408 (table_options.index_type == BlockBasedTableOptions::kHashSearch ||
6409 StartsWith(options.memtable_factory->Name(), "Hash"))) {
6410 continue;
6411 }
6412 DestroyAndReopen(options);
6413
6414 const char* a_end_stuff = "a\xffXYZ";
6415 const char* b_begin_stuff = "b\x00XYZ";
6416 ASSERT_OK(Put("a", large_value));
6417 ASSERT_OK(Put("b", large_value));
6418 ASSERT_OK(Put(Slice(b_begin_stuff, 3), large_value));
6419 ASSERT_OK(Put("c", large_value));
6420 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6421
6422 // control showing valid optimization with auto_prefix mode
6423 ub = Slice(a_end_stuff, 4);
6424 ro.iterate_upper_bound = &ub;
6425
6426 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> iterator(db_->NewIterator(ro));
6427 iterator->Seek(Slice(a_end_stuff, 2));
6428 ASSERT_FALSE(iterator->Valid());
6429 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6430 EXPECT_EQ(1, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6431 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6432
6433 // test, cannot be validly optimized with auto_prefix_mode
6434 ub = Slice(b_begin_stuff, 2);
6435 ro.iterate_upper_bound = &ub;
6436
6437 iterator->Seek(Slice(a_end_stuff, 2));
6438 // !!! BUG !!! See "BUG" section of auto_prefix_mode.
6439 ASSERT_FALSE(iterator->Valid());
6440 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6441 EXPECT_EQ(1, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6442 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6443
6444 // To prove that is the wrong result, now use total order seek
6445 ReadOptions tos_ro = ro;
6446 tos_ro.total_order_seek = true;
6447 tos_ro.auto_prefix_mode = false;
6448 iterator.reset(db_->NewIterator(tos_ro));
6449 iterator->Seek(Slice(a_end_stuff, 2));
6450 ASSERT_TRUE(iterator->Valid());
6451 ASSERT_EQ("b", iterator->key().ToString());
6452 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, hit_stat));
6453 EXPECT_EQ(0, TestGetAndResetTickerCount(options, miss_stat));
6454 ASSERT_OK(iterator->status());
6455 }
6456 } while (ChangeOptions(kSkipPlainTable));
6457}

6459class RenameCurrentTest : public DBTestBase,
6460 public testing::WithParamInterface<std::string> {
6461 public:
6462 RenameCurrentTest()
6463 : DBTestBase("rename_current_test", /*env_do_fsync=*/true),
6464 sync_point_(GetParam()) {}
6465
6466 ~RenameCurrentTest() override = default;
6467
6468 void SetUp() override {
6469 env_->no_file_overwrite_.store(true, std::memory_order_release);
6470 }
6471
6472 void TearDown() override {
6473 env_->no_file_overwrite_.store(false, std::memory_order_release);
6474 }
6475
6476 void SetupSyncPoints() {
6477 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
6478 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(sync_point_, [&](void* arg) {
6479 Status* s = static_cast<Status*>(arg);
6480 assert(s);
6481 *s = Status::IOError("Injected IO error.");
6482 });
6483 }
6484
6485 const std::string sync_point_;
6486};
6487
6488INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(DistributedFS, RenameCurrentTest,

6490 "SetCurrentFile:AfterRename"));

6495 options.create_if_missing = true;
6496 SetupSyncPoints();
6497 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
6498 Status s = TryReopen(options);
6499 ASSERT_NOK(s);
6500
6501 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
6502 Reopen(options);
6503}
6504
6505TEST_P(RenameCurrentTest, Flush) {

6517
6518 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
6519 Reopen(options);

6522}
