6551TEST_F(DBTest2, VariousFileTemperatures) {
6552 constexpr size_t kNumberFileTypes = static_cast<size_t>(kBlobFile) + 1U;
6553
6554 struct MyTestFS : public FileTemperatureTestFS {
6555 explicit MyTestFS(const std::shared_ptr<FileSystem>& fs)
6556 : FileTemperatureTestFS(fs) {
6557 Reset();
6558 }
6559
6560 IOStatus NewWritableFile(const std::string& fname, const FileOptions& opts,
6561 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile>* result,
6562 IODebugContext* dbg) override {
6563 IOStatus ios =
6564 FileTemperatureTestFS::NewWritableFile(fname, opts, result, dbg);
6565 if (ios.ok()) {
6566 uint64_t number;
6567 FileType type;
6568 if (ParseFileName(GetFileName(fname), &number, "LOG", &type)) {
6569 if (type == kTableFile) {
6570 // Not checked here
6571 } else if (type == kWalFile) {
6572 if (opts.temperature != expected_wal_temperature) {
6573 std::cerr << "Attempt to open " << fname << " with temperature "
6574 << temperature_to_string[opts.temperature]
6575 << " rather than "
6576 << temperature_to_string[expected_wal_temperature]
6577 << std::endl;
6578 assert(false);
6579 }
6580 } else if (type == kDescriptorFile) {
6581 if (opts.temperature != expected_manifest_temperature) {
6582 std::cerr << "Attempt to open " << fname << " with temperature "
6583 << temperature_to_string[opts.temperature]
6584 << " rather than "
6585 << temperature_to_string[expected_wal_temperature]
6586 << std::endl;
6587 assert(false);
6588 }
6589 } else if (opts.temperature != expected_other_metadata_temperature) {
6590 std::cerr << "Attempt to open " << fname << " with temperature "
6591 << temperature_to_string[opts.temperature]
6592 << " rather than "
6593 << temperature_to_string[expected_wal_temperature]
6594 << std::endl;
6595 assert(false);
6596 }
6597 UpdateCount(type, 1);
6598 }
6599 }
6600 return ios;
6601 }
6602
6603 IOStatus RenameFile(const std::string& src, const std::string& dst,
6604 const IOOptions& options,
6605 IODebugContext* dbg) override {
6606 IOStatus ios = FileTemperatureTestFS::RenameFile(src, dst, options, dbg);
6607 if (ios.ok()) {
6608 uint64_t number;
6609 FileType src_type;
6610 FileType dst_type;
6611 assert(ParseFileName(GetFileName(src), &number, "LOG", &src_type));
6612 assert(ParseFileName(GetFileName(dst), &number, "LOG", &dst_type));
6613
6614 UpdateCount(src_type, -1);
6615 UpdateCount(dst_type, 1);
6616 }
6617 return ios;
6618 }
6619
6620 void UpdateCount(FileType type, int delta) {
6621 size_t i = static_cast<size_t>(type);
6622 assert(i < kNumberFileTypes);
6623 counts[i].FetchAddRelaxed(delta);
6624 }
6625
6626 std::map<FileType, size_t> PopCounts() {
6627 std::map<FileType, size_t> ret;
6628 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumberFileTypes; ++i) {
6629 int c = counts[i].ExchangeRelaxed(0);
6630 if (c > 0) {
6631 ret[static_cast<FileType>(i)] = c;
6632 }
6633 }
6634 return ret;
6635 }
6636
6637 FileOptions OptimizeForLogWrite(
6638 const FileOptions& file_options,
6639 const DBOptions& /*db_options*/) const override {
6640 FileOptions opts = file_options;
6641 if (optimize_wal_temperature != Temperature::kUnknown) {
6642 opts.temperature = optimize_wal_temperature;
6643 }
6644 return opts;
6645 }
6646
6647 FileOptions OptimizeForManifestWrite(
6648 const FileOptions& file_options) const override {
6649 FileOptions opts = file_options;
6650 if (optimize_manifest_temperature != Temperature::kUnknown) {
6651 opts.temperature = optimize_manifest_temperature;
6652 }
6653 return opts;
6654 }
6655
6656 void Reset() {
6657 optimize_manifest_temperature = Temperature::kUnknown;
6658 optimize_wal_temperature = Temperature::kUnknown;
6659 expected_manifest_temperature = Temperature::kUnknown;
6660 expected_other_metadata_temperature = Temperature::kUnknown;
6661 expected_wal_temperature = Temperature::kUnknown;
6662 for (auto& c : counts) {
6663 c.StoreRelaxed(0);
6664 }
6665 }
6666
6667 Temperature optimize_manifest_temperature;
6668 Temperature optimize_wal_temperature;
6669 Temperature expected_manifest_temperature;
6670 Temperature expected_other_metadata_temperature;
6671 Temperature expected_wal_temperature;
6672 std::array<RelaxedAtomic<int>, kNumberFileTypes> counts;
6673 };
6674
6675 // We don't have enough non-unknown temps to confidently distinguish that
6676 // a specific setting caused a specific outcome, in a single run. This is a
6677 // reasonable work-around without blowing up test time. Only returns
6678 // non-unknown temperatures.
6679 auto RandomTemp = [] {
6680 static std::vector<Temperature> temps = {
6681 Temperature::kHot, Temperature::kWarm, Temperature::kCold};
6682 return temps[Random::GetTLSInstance()->Uniform(
6683 static_cast<int>(temps.size()))];
6684 };
6685
6686 auto test_fs = std::make_shared<MyTestFS>(env_->GetFileSystem());
6687 std::unique_ptr<Env> env(new CompositeEnvWrapper(env_, test_fs));
6688 for (bool use_optimize : {false, true}) {
6689 std::cerr << "use_optimize: " << std::to_string(use_optimize) << std::endl;
6690 for (bool use_temp_options : {false, true}) {
6691 std::cerr << "use_temp_options: " << std::to_string(use_temp_options)
6692 << std::endl;
6693
6694 Options options = CurrentOptions();
6695 // Currently require for last level temperature
6696 options.compaction_style = kCompactionStyleUniversal;
6697 options.env = env.get();
6698 test_fs->Reset();
6699 if (use_optimize) {
6700 test_fs->optimize_manifest_temperature = RandomTemp();
6701 test_fs->expected_manifest_temperature =
6702 test_fs->optimize_manifest_temperature;
6703 test_fs->optimize_wal_temperature = RandomTemp();
6704 test_fs->expected_wal_temperature = test_fs->optimize_wal_temperature;
6705 }
6706 if (use_temp_options) {
6707 options.metadata_write_temperature = RandomTemp();
6708 test_fs->expected_manifest_temperature =
6709 options.metadata_write_temperature;
6710 test_fs->expected_other_metadata_temperature =
6711 options.metadata_write_temperature;
6712 options.wal_write_temperature = RandomTemp();
6713 test_fs->expected_wal_temperature = options.wal_write_temperature;
6714 options.last_level_temperature = RandomTemp();
6715 options.default_write_temperature = RandomTemp();
6716 }
6717
6718 DestroyAndReopen(options);
6719 Defer closer([&] { Close(); });
6720
6721 using FTC = std::map<FileType, size_t>;
6722 // Files on DB startup
6723 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->PopCounts(), FTC({{kWalFile, 1},
6724 {kDescriptorFile, 2},
6725 {kCurrentFile, 2},
6726 {kIdentityFile, 1},
6727 {kOptionsFile, 1}}));
6728
6729 // Temperature count map
6730 using TCM = std::map<Temperature, size_t>;
6731 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->CountCurrentSstFilesByTemp(), TCM({}));
6732
6733 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "1"));
6734 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "1"));
6735 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6736 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "2"));
6737 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "2"));
6738 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6739
6740 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->CountCurrentSstFilesByTemp(),
6741 TCM({{options.default_write_temperature, 2}}));
6742
6743 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange({}, nullptr, nullptr));
6744 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForBackgroundWork());
6745
6746 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->CountCurrentSstFilesByTemp(),
6747 TCM({{options.last_level_temperature, 1}}));
6748
6749 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "3"));
6750 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "3"));
6751 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6752
6753 // Just in memtable/WAL
6754 ASSERT_OK(Put("dog", "3"));
6755
6756 {
6757 TCM expected;
6758 expected[options.default_write_temperature] += 1;
6759 expected[options.last_level_temperature] += 1;
6760 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->CountCurrentSstFilesByTemp(), expected);
6761 }
6762
6763 // New files during operation
6764 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->PopCounts(), FTC({{kWalFile, 3}, {kTableFile, 4}}));
6765
6766 Reopen(options);
6767
6768 // New files during re-open/recovery
6769 ASSERT_EQ(test_fs->PopCounts(), FTC({{kWalFile, 1},
6770 {kTableFile, 1},
6771 {kDescriptorFile, 1},
6772 {kCurrentFile, 1},
6773 {kOptionsFile, 1}}));
6774
6775 Destroy(options);
6776 }
6777 }
6778}
6779
6780TEST_F(DBTest2, LastLevelTemperature) {
6781 class TestListener : public EventListener {
6782 public:
6783 void OnFileReadFinish(const FileOperationInfo& info) override {
6784 UpdateFileTemperature(info);
6785 }
6786
6787 void OnFileWriteFinish(const FileOperationInfo& info) override {
6788 UpdateFileTemperature(info);
6789 }
6790
6791 void OnFileFlushFinish(const FileOperationInfo& info) override {
6792 UpdateFileTemperature(info);
6793 }
6794
6795 void OnFileSyncFinish(const FileOperationInfo& info) override {
6796 UpdateFileTemperature(info);
6797 }
6798
6799 void OnFileCloseFinish(const FileOperationInfo& info) override {
6800 UpdateFileTemperature(info);
6801 }
6802
6803 bool ShouldBeNotifiedOnFileIO() override { return true; }
6804
6805 std::unordered_map<uint64_t, Temperature> file_temperatures;
6806
6807 private:
6808 void UpdateFileTemperature(const FileOperationInfo& info) {
6809 auto filename = GetFileName(info.path);
6810 uint64_t number;
6811 FileType type;
6812 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(filename, &number, &type));
6813 if (type == kTableFile) {
6814 MutexLock l(&mutex_);
6815 auto ret = file_temperatures.insert({number, info.temperature});
6816 if (!ret.second) {
6817 // the same file temperature should always be the same for all events
6818 ASSERT_TRUE(ret.first->second == info.temperature);
6819 }
6820 }
6821 }
6822
6823 std::string GetFileName(const std::string& fname) {
6824 auto filename = fname.substr(fname.find_last_of(kFilePathSeparator) + 1);
6825 // workaround only for Windows that the file path could contain both
6826 // Windows FilePathSeparator and '/'
6827 filename = filename.substr(filename.find_last_of('/') + 1);
6828 return filename;
6829 }
6830
6831 port::Mutex mutex_;
6832 };
6833
6834 const int kNumLevels = 7;
6835 const int kLastLevel = kNumLevels - 1;
6836
6837 auto* listener = new TestListener();
6838
6839 Options options = CurrentOptions();
6840 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kWarm;
6841 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
6842 options.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
6843 options.num_levels = kNumLevels;
6844 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
6845 options.listeners.emplace_back(listener);
6846 Reopen(options);
6847
6848 auto size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
6849 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6850 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
6851 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6852 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot);
6853 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6854
6855 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
6856 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
6857 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6858 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
6859 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
6860 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6861 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
6862
6863 get_iostats_context()->Reset();
6864 IOStatsContext* iostats = get_iostats_context();
6865
6866 ColumnFamilyMetaData metadata;
6867 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
6868 ASSERT_EQ(1, metadata.file_count);
6869 SstFileMetaData meta = metadata.levels[kLastLevel].files[0];
6870 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm, meta.temperature);
6871 uint64_t number;
6872 FileType type;
6873 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6874 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6875
6876 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
6877 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6878 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
6879 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
6880 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6881 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_read_count, 0);
6882 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6883 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6884 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6885 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6886
6887 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo"));
6888
6889 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6890 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_read_count, 1);
6891 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6892 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_bytes_read, 0);
6893 ASSERT_GT(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_bytes_read, 0);
6894 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.cold_file_bytes_read, 0);
6895 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6896 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6897 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6898 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6899 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6900 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6901
6902 // non-bottommost file still has unknown temperature
6903 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
6904 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
6905 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
6906 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("bar"));
6907 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6908 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_read_count, 1);
6909 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
6910 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_bytes_read, 0);
6911 ASSERT_GT(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_bytes_read, 0);
6912 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.cold_file_bytes_read, 0);
6913 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6914 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6915 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
6916 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6917 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6918 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
6919
6920 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
6921 ASSERT_EQ(2, metadata.file_count);
6922 meta = metadata.levels[0].files[0];
6923 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown, meta.temperature);
6924 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6925 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6926
6927 meta = metadata.levels[kLastLevel].files[0];
6928 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm, meta.temperature);
6929 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6930 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6931
6932 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
6933 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
6934 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
6935 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
6936
6937 // reopen and check the information is persisted
6938 Reopen(options);
6939 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
6940 ASSERT_EQ(2, metadata.file_count);
6941 meta = metadata.levels[0].files[0];
6942 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown, meta.temperature);
6943 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6944 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6945
6946 meta = metadata.levels[kLastLevel].files[0];
6947 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm, meta.temperature);
6948 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6949 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6950 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
6951 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
6952 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
6953 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
6954
6955 // check other non-exist temperatures
6956 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot);
6957 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6958 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold);
6959 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
6960 std::string prop;
6961 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()->GetProperty(
6962 DB::Properties::kLiveSstFilesSizeAtTemperature + std::to_string(22),
6963 &prop));
6964 ASSERT_EQ(std::atoi(prop.c_str()), 0);
6965
6966 Reopen(options);
6967 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
6968 ASSERT_EQ(2, metadata.file_count);
6969 meta = metadata.levels[0].files[0];
6970 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown, meta.temperature);
6971 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6972 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6973
6974 meta = metadata.levels[kLastLevel].files[0];
6975 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm, meta.temperature);
6976 ASSERT_TRUE(ParseFileName(meta.name, &number, &type));
6977 ASSERT_EQ(listener->file_temperatures.at(number), meta.temperature);
6978}

6980TEST_F(DBTest2, LastLevelTemperatureUniversal) {

6996 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);

7017 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_read_count, 0);
7018 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.cold_file_read_count, 0);
7019 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7020 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7021 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7022 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7023 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7024 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7025 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo"));
7026
7027 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
7028 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_read_count, 0);
7029 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_read_count, 0);
7030 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.hot_file_bytes_read, 0);
7031 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.warm_file_bytes_read, 0);
7032 ASSERT_EQ(iostats->file_io_stats_by_temperature.cold_file_bytes_read, 0);
7033 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7034 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7035 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7036 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7037 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7038 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7039
7040 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
7041 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7042 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7043 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7044 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7045 ASSERT_EQ(2, metadata.file_count);
7046 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown, metadata.levels[0].files[0].temperature);
7047 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7048 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7049 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7050 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7051
7052 // Update last level temperature
7053 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kWarm;
7054 Reopen(options);
7055 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7056 // Should not impact existing ones
7057 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown,
7058 metadata.levels[kBottommostLevel].files[0].temperature);
7059 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7060 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7061 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7062 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7063
7064 // new generated file should have the new settings
7065 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
7066 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7067 ASSERT_EQ(1, metadata.file_count);
7068 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm,
7069 metadata.levels[kBottommostLevel].files[0].temperature);
7070 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7071 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7072 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7073 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7074 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7075 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7076 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES), 0);
7077 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7078 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7079 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT), 0);
7080
7081 // non-bottommost file still has unknown temperature
7082 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
7083 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7084 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7085 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7086 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7087 ASSERT_EQ(2, metadata.file_count);
7088 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kUnknown, metadata.levels[0].files[0].temperature);
7089 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7090 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7091 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7092 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7093
7094 // check other non-exist temperatures
7095 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot);
7096 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7097 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold);
7098 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7099 std::string prop;
7100 ASSERT_TRUE(dbfull()->GetProperty(
7101 DB::Properties::kLiveSstFilesSizeAtTemperature + std::to_string(22),
7102 &prop));
7103 ASSERT_EQ(std::atoi(prop.c_str()), 0);
7104
7105 // Update last level temperature dynamically with SetOptions
7106 auto s = db_->SetOptions({{"last_level_temperature", "kCold"}});
7107 ASSERT_OK(s);
7108 ASSERT_EQ(db_->GetOptions().last_level_temperature, Temperature::kCold);
7109 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7110 // Should not impact the existing files
7111 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kWarm,
7112 metadata.levels[kBottommostLevel].files[0].temperature);
7113 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7114 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7115 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7116 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7117 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold);
7118 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7119
7120 // new generated files should have the new settings
7121 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
7122 db_->GetColumnFamilyMetaData(&metadata);
7123 ASSERT_EQ(1, metadata.file_count);
7124 ASSERT_EQ(Temperature::kCold,
7125 metadata.levels[kBottommostLevel].files[0].temperature);
7126 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown);
7127 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7128 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7129 ASSERT_EQ(size, 0);
7130 size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold);
7131 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7132
7133 // kLastTemperature is an invalid temperature
7134 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kLastTemperature;
7135 s = TryReopen(options);
7136 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsIOError());
7137}

7139TEST_F(DBTest2, LastLevelStatistics) {
7140 for (bool write_time_default : {false, true}) {
7141 SCOPED_TRACE("write time default? " + std::to_string(write_time_default));
7142 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7143 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kWarm;
7144 if (write_time_default) {
7145 options.default_write_temperature = Temperature::kHot;
7146 ASSERT_EQ(options.default_temperature, Temperature::kUnknown);
7147 } else {
7148 options.default_temperature = Temperature::kHot;
7149 ASSERT_EQ(options.default_write_temperature, Temperature::kUnknown);
7150 }
7151 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
7152 options.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
7153 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
7154 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
7155 bbto.no_block_cache = true;
7156 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
7157
7158 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7159
7160 // generate 1 sst on level 0
7161 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo1", "bar"));
7162 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7163 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7164 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("bar"));
7165
7166 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES), 0);
7167 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT), 0);
7168 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7169 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7170 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7171 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7172 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES), 0);
7173 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT), 0);
7174
7175 // 2nd flush to trigger compaction
7176 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo2", "bar"));
7177 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7178 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7179 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7180 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("bar"));
7181
7182 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7183 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7184 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7185 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7186 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7187 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7188 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7189 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7190
7191 auto pre_bytes =
7192 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES);
7193 auto pre_count =
7194 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT);
7195
7196 // 3rd flush to generate 1 sst on level 0
7197 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo3", "bar"));
7198 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7199 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7200 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo1"));
7201 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo2"));
7202 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo3"));
7203 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("bar"));
7204
7205 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7206 pre_bytes);
7207 ASSERT_GT(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7208 pre_count);
7209 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7210 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7211 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7212 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7213 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7214 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7215 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7216 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7217 // Control
7218 ASSERT_NE(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7219 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT));
7220
7221 // Not a realistic setting to make last level kWarm and default temp kCold.
7222 // This is just for testing default temp can be reset on reopen while the
7223 // last level temp is consistent across DB reopen because those file's temp
7224 // are persisted in manifest.
7225 options.default_temperature = Temperature::kCold;
7226 ASSERT_OK(options.statistics->Reset());
7227 Reopen(options);
7228 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo1"));
7229 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo2"));
7230 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("foo3"));
7231 ASSERT_EQ("bar", Get("bar"));
7232
7233 if (write_time_default) {
7234 // Unchanged
7235 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7236 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7237 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7238 options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7239
7240 ASSERT_LT(0, options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7241 ASSERT_EQ(0, options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7242 } else {
7243 // Changed (in how we map kUnknown)
7244 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7245 options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7246 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7247 options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7248
7249 ASSERT_EQ(0, options.statistics->getTickerCount(HOT_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7250 ASSERT_LT(0, options.statistics->getTickerCount(COLD_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7251 }
7252
7253 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_BYTES),
7254 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_BYTES));
7255 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7256 options.statistics->getTickerCount(WARM_FILE_READ_COUNT));
7257 // Control
7258 ASSERT_NE(options.statistics->getTickerCount(LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT),
7259 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NON_LAST_LEVEL_READ_COUNT));
7260 }
7261}

7263TEST_F(DBTest2, CheckpointFileTemperature) {
7264 class NoLinkTestFS : public FileTemperatureTestFS {
7265 using FileTemperatureTestFS::FileTemperatureTestFS;
7266
7267 IOStatus LinkFile(const std::string&, const std::string&, const IOOptions&,
7268 IODebugContext*) override {
7269 // return not supported to force checkpoint copy the file instead of just
7270 // link
7271 return IOStatus::NotSupported();
7272 }
7273 };
7274 auto test_fs = std::make_shared<NoLinkTestFS>(env_->GetFileSystem());
7275 std::unique_ptr<Env> env(new CompositeEnvWrapper(env_, test_fs));
7276 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7277 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kWarm;
7278 // set dynamic_level to true so the compaction would compact the data to the
7279 // last level directly which will have the last_level_temperature
7280 options.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
7281 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
7282 options.env = env.get();
7283 Reopen(options);
7284
7285 // generate a bottommost file and a non-bottommost file
7286 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
7287 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7288 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7289 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
7290 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7291 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7292 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7293 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
7294 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "bar"));
7295 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7296 auto size = GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm);
7297 ASSERT_GT(size, 0);
7298
7299 std::map<uint64_t, Temperature> temperatures;
7300 std::vector<LiveFileStorageInfo> infos;
7301 ASSERT_OK(
7302 dbfull()->GetLiveFilesStorageInfo(LiveFilesStorageInfoOptions(), &infos));
7303 for (const auto& info : infos) {
7304 temperatures.emplace(info.file_number, info.temperature);
7305 }
7306
7307 test_fs->PopRequestedSstFileTemperatures();
7308 Checkpoint* checkpoint;
7309 ASSERT_OK(Checkpoint::Create(db_, &checkpoint));
7310 ASSERT_OK(
7311 checkpoint->CreateCheckpoint(dbname_ + kFilePathSeparator + "tempcp"));
7312
7313 // checking src file src_temperature hints: 2 sst files: 1 sst is kWarm,
7314 // another is kUnknown
7315 std::vector<std::pair<uint64_t, Temperature>> requested_temps;
7316 test_fs->PopRequestedSstFileTemperatures(&requested_temps);
7317 // Two requests
7318 ASSERT_EQ(requested_temps.size(), 2);
7319 std::set<uint64_t> distinct_requests;
7320 for (const auto& requested_temp : requested_temps) {
7321 // Matching manifest temperatures
7322 ASSERT_EQ(temperatures.at(requested_temp.first), requested_temp.second);
7323 distinct_requests.insert(requested_temp.first);
7324 }
7325 // Each request to distinct file
7326 ASSERT_EQ(distinct_requests.size(), requested_temps.size());
7327
7328 delete checkpoint;
7329 Close();
7330}

7332TEST_F(DBTest2, FileTemperatureManifestFixup) {
7333 auto test_fs = std::make_shared<FileTemperatureTestFS>(env_->GetFileSystem());
7334 std::unique_ptr<Env> env(new CompositeEnvWrapper(env_, test_fs));
7335 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7336 options.last_level_temperature = Temperature::kWarm;
7337 // set dynamic_level to true so the compaction would compact the data to the
7338 // last level directly which will have the last_level_temperature
7339 options.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
7340 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 2;
7341 options.env = env.get();
7342 std::vector<std::string> cfs = {/*"default",*/ "test1", "test2"};
7343 CreateAndReopenWithCF(cfs, options);
7344 // Needed for later re-opens (weird)
7345 cfs.insert(cfs.begin(), kDefaultColumnFamilyName);
7346
7347 // Generate a bottommost file in all CFs
7348 for (int cf = 0; cf < 3; ++cf) {
7349 ASSERT_OK(Put(cf, "a", "val"));
7350 ASSERT_OK(Put(cf, "c", "val"));
7351 ASSERT_OK(Flush(cf));
7352 ASSERT_OK(Put(cf, "b", "val"));
7353 ASSERT_OK(Put(cf, "d", "val"));
7354 ASSERT_OK(Flush(cf));
7355 }
7356 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7357
7358 // verify
7359 ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm), 0);
7360 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown), 0);
7361 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold), 0);
7362 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot), 0);
7363
7364 // Generate a non-bottommost file in all CFs
7365 for (int cf = 0; cf < 3; ++cf) {
7366 ASSERT_OK(Put(cf, "e", "val"));
7367 ASSERT_OK(Flush(cf));
7368 }
7369
7370 // re-verify
7371 ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm), 0);
7372 // Not supported: ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown), 0);
7373 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold), 0);
7374 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot), 0);
7375
7376 // Now change FS temperature on bottommost file(s) to kCold
7377 std::map<uint64_t, Temperature> current_temps;
7378 test_fs->CopyCurrentSstFileTemperatures(&current_temps);
7379 for (auto e : current_temps) {
7380 if (e.second == Temperature::kWarm) {
7381 test_fs->OverrideSstFileTemperature(e.first, Temperature::kCold);
7382 }
7383 }
7384 // Metadata not yet updated
7385 ASSERT_EQ(Get("a"), "val");
7386 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold), 0);
7387
7388 // Update with Close and UpdateManifestForFilesState, but first save cf
7389 // descriptors
7390 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
7391 for (size_t i = 0; i < handles_.size(); ++i) {
7392 ColumnFamilyDescriptor cfdescriptor;
7393 handles_[i]->GetDescriptor(&cfdescriptor).PermitUncheckedError();
7394 column_families.push_back(cfdescriptor);
7395 }
7396 Close();
7397 experimental::UpdateManifestForFilesStateOptions update_opts;
7398 update_opts.update_temperatures = true;
7399
7400 ASSERT_OK(experimental::UpdateManifestForFilesState(
7401 options, dbname_, column_families, update_opts));
7402
7403 // Re-open and re-verify after update
7404 ReopenWithColumnFamilies(cfs, options);
7405 ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold), 0);
7406 // Not supported: ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown), 0);
7407 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm), 0);
7408 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot), 0);
7409
7410 // Change kUnknown to kHot
7411 test_fs->CopyCurrentSstFileTemperatures(&current_temps);
7412 for (auto e : current_temps) {
7413 if (e.second == Temperature::kUnknown) {
7414 test_fs->OverrideSstFileTemperature(e.first, Temperature::kHot);
7415 }
7416 }
7417
7418 // Update with Close and UpdateManifestForFilesState
7419 Close();
7420 ASSERT_OK(experimental::UpdateManifestForFilesState(
7421 options, dbname_, column_families, update_opts));
7422
7423 // Re-open and re-verify after update
7424 ReopenWithColumnFamilies(cfs, options);
7425 ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kCold), 0);
7426 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kUnknown), 0);
7427 ASSERT_EQ(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kWarm), 0);
7428 ASSERT_GT(GetSstSizeHelper(Temperature::kHot), 0);
7429
7430 Close();
7431}

7433// WAL recovery mode is WALRecoveryMode::kPointInTimeRecovery.
7434TEST_F(DBTest2, PointInTimeRecoveryWithIOErrorWhileReadingWal) {
7435 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7436 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7437 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "value0"));
7438 Close();
7439 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
7440 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
7441 bool should_inject_error = false;
7442 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7443 "DBImpl::RecoverLogFiles:BeforeReadWal",
7444 [&](void* /*arg*/) { should_inject_error = true; });
7445 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7446 "LogReader::ReadMore:AfterReadFile", [&](void* arg) {
7447 if (should_inject_error) {
7448 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, arg);
7449 *static_cast<Status*>(arg) = Status::IOError("Injected IOError");
7450 }
7451 });
7452 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
7453 options.avoid_flush_during_recovery = true;
7454 options.wal_recovery_mode = WALRecoveryMode::kPointInTimeRecovery;
7455 Status s = TryReopen(options);
7456 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsIOError());
7457}

7487TEST_F(DBTest2, SortL0FilesByEpochNumber) {
7488 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7489 options.num_levels = 1;
7490 options.compaction_style = kCompactionStyleUniversal;
7491 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7492
7493 // Set up L0 files to be sorted by their epoch_number
7494 ASSERT_OK(Put("key1", "seq1"));
7495
7496 SstFileWriter sst_file_writer{EnvOptions(), options};
7497 std::string external_file1 = dbname_ + "/test_files1.sst";
7498 std::string external_file2 = dbname_ + "/test_files2.sst";
7499 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Open(external_file1));
7500 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Put("key2", "seq0"));
7501 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Finish());
7502 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Open(external_file2));
7503 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Put("key3", "seq0"));
7504 ASSERT_OK(sst_file_writer.Finish());
7505
7506 ASSERT_OK(Put("key4", "seq2"));
7507 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7508
7509 auto* handle = db_->DefaultColumnFamily();
7510 ASSERT_OK(db_->IngestExternalFile(handle, {external_file1, external_file2},
7511 IngestExternalFileOptions()));
7512
7513 // To verify L0 files are sorted by epoch_number in descending order
7514 // instead of largest_seqno
7515 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level0_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7516 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 3);
7517
7518 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[0]->epoch_number, 3);
7519 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[0]->fd.largest_seqno, 0);
7520 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7521 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key3"));
7522
7523 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[1]->epoch_number, 2);
7524 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[1]->fd.largest_seqno, 0);
7525 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[1]->num_entries, 1);
7526 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[1]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key2"));
7527
7528 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[2]->epoch_number, 1);
7529 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[2]->fd.largest_seqno, 2);
7530 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[2]->num_entries, 2);
7531 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[2]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key4"));
7532 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[2]->smallest.user_key() == Slice("key1"));
7533
7534 // To verify compacted file is assigned with the minimum epoch_number
7535 // among input files'
7536 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
7537
7538 level0_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7539 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 1);
7540 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[0]->epoch_number, 1);
7541 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->num_entries, 4);
7542 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key4"));
7543 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->smallest.user_key() == Slice("key1"));
7544}

7546TEST_F(DBTest2, SameEpochNumberAfterCompactRangeChangeLevel) {
7547 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7548 options.num_levels = 7;
7549 options.compaction_style = CompactionStyle::kCompactionStyleLevel;
7550 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
7551 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7552
7553 // Set up the file in L1 to be moved to L0 in later step of CompactRange()
7554 ASSERT_OK(Put("key1", "seq1"));
7555 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7556 MoveFilesToLevel(1, 0);
7557 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level0_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7558 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 0);
7559 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level1_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(1 /* level*/);
7560 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files.size(), 1);
7561 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level2_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(2 /* level*/);
7562 ASSERT_EQ(level2_files.size(), 0);
7563
7564 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files[0]->epoch_number, 1);
7565
7566 // To verify CompactRange() moving file to L0 still keeps the file's
7567 // epoch_number
7568 CompactRangeOptions croptions;
7569 croptions.change_level = true;
7570 croptions.target_level = 0;
7571 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(croptions, nullptr, nullptr));
7572 level0_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7573 level1_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(1 /* level*/);
7574 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 1);
7575 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files.size(), 0);
7576
7577 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[0]->epoch_number, 1);
7578
7579 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7580 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key1"));
7581}

7583TEST_F(DBTest2, RecoverEpochNumber) {
7584 for (bool allow_ingest_behind : {true, false}) {
7585 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7586 options.allow_ingest_behind = allow_ingest_behind;
7587 options.num_levels = 7;
7588 options.compaction_style = kCompactionStyleLevel;
7589 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
7590 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7591 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"cf1"}, options);
7592 VersionSet* versions = dbfull()->GetVersionSet();
7593 assert(versions);
7594 const ColumnFamilyData* default_cf =
7595 versions->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetDefault();
7596 const ColumnFamilyData* cf1 =
7597 versions->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily("cf1");
7598
7599 // Set up files in default CF to recover in later step
7600 ASSERT_OK(Put("key1", "epoch1"));
7601 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7602 MoveFilesToLevel(1 /* level*/, 0 /* cf*/);
7603 ASSERT_OK(Put("key2", "epoch2"));
7604 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7605
7606 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level0_files =
7607 GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7608 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 1);
7609 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->epoch_number,
7610 allow_ingest_behind
7611 ? 2 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7612 : 2);
7613 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7614 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key2"));
7615
7616 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level1_files =
7617 GetLevelFileMetadatas(1 /* level*/);
7618 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files.size(), 1);
7619 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files[0]->epoch_number,
7620 allow_ingest_behind
7621 ? 1 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7622 : 1);
7623 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7624 ASSERT_TRUE(level1_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key1"));
7625
7626 // Set up files in cf1 to recover in later step
7627 ASSERT_OK(Put(1 /* cf */, "cf1_key1", "epoch1"));
7628 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1 /* cf */));
7629
7630 std::vector<FileMetaData*> level0_files_cf1 =
7631 GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/, 1 /* cf*/);
7632 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files_cf1.size(), 1);
7633 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files_cf1[0]->epoch_number,
7634 allow_ingest_behind
7635 ? 1 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7636 : 1);
7637 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files_cf1[0]->num_entries, 1);
7638 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files_cf1[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("cf1_key1"));
7639
7640 ASSERT_EQ(default_cf->GetNextEpochNumber(),
7641 allow_ingest_behind
7642 ? 3 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7643 : 3);
7644 ASSERT_EQ(cf1->GetNextEpochNumber(),
7645 allow_ingest_behind
7646 ? 2 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7647 : 2);
7648
7649 // To verify epoch_number of files of different levels/CFs are
7650 // persisted and recovered correctly
7651 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "cf1"}, options);
7652 versions = dbfull()->GetVersionSet();
7653 assert(versions);
7654 default_cf = versions->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetDefault();
7655 cf1 = versions->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily("cf1");
7656
7657 level0_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/);
7658 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files.size(), 1);
7659 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files[0]->epoch_number,
7660 allow_ingest_behind
7661 ? 2 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7662 : 2);
7663 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7664 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key2"));
7665
7666 level1_files = GetLevelFileMetadatas(1 /* level*/);
7667 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files.size(), 1);
7668 EXPECT_EQ(level1_files[0]->epoch_number,
7669 allow_ingest_behind
7670 ? 1 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7671 : 1);
7672 ASSERT_EQ(level1_files[0]->num_entries, 1);
7673 ASSERT_TRUE(level1_files[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("key1"));
7674
7675 level0_files_cf1 = GetLevelFileMetadatas(0 /* level*/, 1 /* cf*/);
7676 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files_cf1.size(), 1);
7677 EXPECT_EQ(level0_files_cf1[0]->epoch_number,
7678 allow_ingest_behind
7679 ? 1 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7680 : 1);
7681 ASSERT_EQ(level0_files_cf1[0]->num_entries, 1);
7682 ASSERT_TRUE(level0_files_cf1[0]->largest.user_key() == Slice("cf1_key1"));
7683
7684 // To verify next epoch number is recovered correctly
7685 EXPECT_EQ(default_cf->GetNextEpochNumber(),
7686 allow_ingest_behind
7687 ? 3 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7688 : 3);
7689 EXPECT_EQ(cf1->GetNextEpochNumber(),
7690 allow_ingest_behind
7691 ? 2 + kReservedEpochNumberForFileIngestedBehind
7692 : 2);
7693 }
7694}

7713TEST_F(DBTest2, SstUniqueIdVerifyBackwardCompatible) {
7714 const int kNumSst = 3;
7715 const int kLevel0Trigger = 4;
7716 auto options = CurrentOptions();
7717 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = kLevel0Trigger;
7718 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
7719 // Skip for now
7720 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = false;
7721 Reopen(options);
7722
7723 std::atomic_int skipped = 0;
7724 std::atomic_int passed = 0;
7725 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7726 "BlockBasedTable::Open::SkippedVerifyUniqueId",
7727 [&](void* /*arg*/) { skipped++; });
7728 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7729 "BlockBasedTable::Open::PassedVerifyUniqueId",
7730 [&](void* /*arg*/) { passed++; });
7731 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
7732
7733 // generate a few SSTs
7734 for (int i = 0; i < kNumSst; i++) {
7735 for (int j = 0; j < 100; j++) {
7736 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * 10 + j), "value"));
7737 }
7738 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7739 }
7740
7741 // Verification has been skipped on files so far
7742 EXPECT_EQ(skipped, kNumSst);
7743 EXPECT_EQ(passed, 0);
7744
7745 // Reopen with verification
7746 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = true;
7747 skipped = 0;
7748 passed = 0;
7749 Reopen(options);
7750 EXPECT_EQ(skipped, 0);
7751 EXPECT_EQ(passed, kNumSst);
7752
7753 // Now simulate no unique id in manifest for next file
7754 // NOTE: this only works for loading manifest from disk,
7755 // not in-memory manifest, so we need to re-open below.
7756 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7757 "VersionEdit::EncodeTo:UniqueId", [&](void* arg) {
7758 auto unique_id = static_cast<UniqueId64x2*>(arg);
7759 // remove id before writing it to manifest
7760 (*unique_id)[0] = 0;
7761 (*unique_id)[1] = 0;
7762 });
7763
7764 // test compaction generated Sst
7765 for (int i = kNumSst; i < kLevel0Trigger; i++) {
7766 for (int j = 0; j < 100; j++) {
7767 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * 10 + j), "value"));
7768 }
7769 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7770 }
7771 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7772
7773 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
7774
7775 // Reopen (with verification)
7776 ASSERT_TRUE(options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest);
7777 skipped = 0;
7778 passed = 0;
7779 Reopen(options);
7780 EXPECT_EQ(skipped, 1);
7781 EXPECT_EQ(passed, 0);
7782}

7784TEST_F(DBTest2, SstUniqueIdVerify) {
7785 const int kNumSst = 3;
7786 const int kLevel0Trigger = 4;
7787 auto options = CurrentOptions();
7788 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = kLevel0Trigger;
7789 // Allow mismatch for now
7790 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = false;
7791 Reopen(options);
7792
7793 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7794 "PropertyBlockBuilder::AddTableProperty:Start", [&](void* props_vs) {
7795 auto props = static_cast<TableProperties*>(props_vs);
7796 // update table property session_id to a different one, which
7797 // changes unique ID
7798 props->db_session_id = DBImpl::GenerateDbSessionId(nullptr);
7799 });
7800 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
7801
7802 // generate a few SSTs
7803 for (int i = 0; i < kNumSst; i++) {
7804 for (int j = 0; j < 100; j++) {
7805 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * 10 + j), "value"));
7806 }
7807 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7808 }
7809
7810 // Reopen with verification should report corruption
7811 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = true;
7812 auto s = TryReopen(options);
7813 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsCorruption());
7814
7815 // Reopen without verification should be fine
7816 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = false;
7817 Reopen(options);
7818
7819 // test compaction generated Sst
7820 for (int i = kNumSst; i < kLevel0Trigger; i++) {
7821 for (int j = 0; j < 100; j++) {
7822 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * 10 + j), "value"));
7823 }
7824 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7825 }
7826 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->TEST_WaitForCompact());
7827
7828 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
7829
7830 // Reopen with verification should fail
7831 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = true;
7832 s = TryReopen(options);
7833 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsCorruption());
7834}

7877TEST_F(DBTest2, BestEffortsRecoveryWithSstUniqueIdVerification) {
7878 const auto tamper_with_uniq_id = [&](void* arg) {
7879 auto props = static_cast<TableProperties*>(arg);
7880 assert(props);
7881 // update table property session_id to a different one
7882 props->db_session_id = DBImpl::GenerateDbSessionId(nullptr);
7883 };
7884
7885 const auto assert_db = [&](size_t expected_count,
7886 const std::string& expected_v) {
7887 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
7888 size_t cnt = 0;
7889 for (it->SeekToFirst(); it->Valid(); it->Next(), ++cnt) {
7890 ASSERT_EQ(std::to_string(cnt), it->key());
7891 ASSERT_EQ(expected_v, it->value());
7892 }
7893 EXPECT_OK(it->status());
7894 ASSERT_EQ(expected_count, cnt);
7895 };
7896
7897 const int num_l0_compaction_trigger = 8;
7898 const int num_l0 = num_l0_compaction_trigger - 1;
7899 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7900 options.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = num_l0_compaction_trigger;
7901
7902 for (int k = 0; k < num_l0; ++k) {
7903 // Allow mismatch for now
7904 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = false;
7905
7906 DestroyAndReopen(options);
7907
7908 constexpr size_t num_keys_per_file = 10;
7909 for (int i = 0; i < num_l0; ++i) {
7910 for (size_t j = 0; j < num_keys_per_file; ++j) {
7911 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::to_string(j), "v" + std::to_string(i)));
7912 }
7913 if (i == k) {
7914 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
7915 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
7916 "PropertyBlockBuilder::AddTableProperty:Start",
7917 tamper_with_uniq_id);
7918 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
7919 }
7920 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7921 }
7922
7923 options.verify_sst_unique_id_in_manifest = true;
7924 Status s = TryReopen(options);
7925 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsCorruption());
7926
7927 options.best_efforts_recovery = true;
7928 Reopen(options);
7929 assert_db(k == 0 ? 0 : num_keys_per_file, "v" + std::to_string(k - 1));
7930
7931 // Reopen with regular recovery
7932 options.best_efforts_recovery = false;
7933 Reopen(options);
7934 assert_db(k == 0 ? 0 : num_keys_per_file, "v" + std::to_string(k - 1));
7935
7936 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
7937 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
7938
7939 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys_per_file; ++i) {
7940 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::to_string(i), "v"));
7941 }
7942 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7943 Reopen(options);
7944 {
7945 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_keys_per_file; ++i) {
7946 ASSERT_EQ("v", Get(std::to_string(i)));
7947 }
7948 }
7949 }
7950}
7951
7952TEST_F(DBTest2, GetLatestSeqAndTsForKey) {
7953 Destroy(last_options_);
7954
7955 Options options = CurrentOptions();
7956 options.max_write_buffer_size_to_maintain = 64 << 10;
7957 options.create_if_missing = true;
7958 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
7959 options.comparator = test::BytewiseComparatorWithU64TsWrapper();
7960 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
7961
7962 Reopen(options);
7963
7964 constexpr uint64_t kTsU64Value = 12;
7965
7966 for (uint64_t key = 0; key < 100; ++key) {
7967 std::string ts;
7968 PutFixed64(&ts, kTsU64Value);
7969
7970 std::string key_str;
7971 PutFixed64(&key_str, key);
7972 std::reverse(key_str.begin(), key_str.end());
7973 ASSERT_OK(db_->Put(WriteOptions(), key_str, ts, "value"));
7974 }
7975
7976 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
7977
7978 constexpr bool cache_only = true;
7979 constexpr SequenceNumber lower_bound_seq = 0;
7980 auto* cfhi = static_cast_with_check<ColumnFamilyHandleImpl>(
7981 dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily());
7982 assert(cfhi);
7983 assert(cfhi->cfd());
7984 SuperVersion* sv = cfhi->cfd()->GetSuperVersion();
7985 for (uint64_t key = 0; key < 100; ++key) {
7986 std::string key_str;
7987 PutFixed64(&key_str, key);
7988 std::reverse(key_str.begin(), key_str.end());
7989 std::string ts;
7990 SequenceNumber seq = kMaxSequenceNumber;
7991 bool found_record_for_key = false;
7992 bool is_blob_index = false;
7993
7994 const Status s = dbfull()->GetLatestSequenceForKey(
7995 sv, key_str, cache_only, lower_bound_seq, &seq, &ts,
7996 &found_record_for_key, &is_blob_index);
7997 ASSERT_OK(s);
7998 std::string expected_ts;
7999 PutFixed64(&expected_ts, kTsU64Value);
8000 ASSERT_EQ(expected_ts, ts);
8001 ASSERT_TRUE(found_record_for_key);
8002 ASSERT_FALSE(is_blob_index);
8003 }
8004
8005 // Verify that no read to SST files.
8006 ASSERT_EQ(0, options.statistics->getTickerCount(GET_HIT_L0));
8007}

8009#if defined(ZSTD_ADVANCED)
8010TEST_F(DBTest2, ZSTDChecksum) {
8011 // Verify that corruption during decompression is caught.
8012 Options options = CurrentOptions();
8013 options.create_if_missing = true;
8014 options.compression = kZSTD;
8015 options.compression_opts.max_compressed_bytes_per_kb = 1024;
8016 options.compression_opts.checksum = true;
8017 DestroyAndReopen(options);
8018 Random rnd(33);
8019 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(0), rnd.RandomString(4 << 10)));
8020 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
8021 "BlockBasedTableBuilder::WriteBlock:TamperWithCompressedData",
8022 [&](void* arg) {
8023 std::string* output = static_cast<std::string*>(arg);
8024 // https://github.com/facebook/zstd/blob/dev/doc/zstd_compression_format.md#zstandard-frames
8025 // Checksum is the last 4 bytes, corrupting that part in unit test is
8026 // more controllable.
8027 output->data()[output->size() - 1]++;
8028 });
8029 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
8030 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
8031 PinnableSlice val;
8032 Status s = Get(Key(0), &val);
8033 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsCorruption());
8034
8035 // Corruption caught during flush.
8036 options.paranoid_file_checks = true;
8037 DestroyAndReopen(options);
8038 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(0), rnd.RandomString(4 << 10)));
8039 s = Flush();
8040 ASSERT_TRUE(s.IsCorruption());
8041}
8042#endif
8043
8044TEST_F(DBTest2, TableCacheMissDuringReadFromBlockCacheTier) {
8045 Options options = CurrentOptions();
8046 options.statistics = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::CreateDBStatistics();
8047 Reopen(options);
8048
8049 // Give table cache zero capacity to prevent preloading tables. That way,
8050 // `kBlockCacheTier` reads will fail due to table cache misses.
8051 dbfull()->TEST_table_cache()->SetCapacity(0);
8052 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "bar"));
8053 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
8054
8055 uint64_t orig_num_file_opens = TestGetTickerCount(options, NO_FILE_OPENS);
8056
8057 ReadOptions non_blocking_opts;
8058 non_blocking_opts.read_tier = kBlockCacheTier;
8059 std::string value;
8060 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->Get(non_blocking_opts, "foo", &value).IsIncomplete());
8061
8062 ASSERT_EQ(orig_num_file_opens, TestGetTickerCount(options, NO_FILE_OPENS));
8063}
8064
8065TEST_F(DBTest2, GetFileChecksumsFromCurrentManifest_CRC32) {
8066 Options opts = CurrentOptions();
8067 opts.create_if_missing = true;
8068 opts.file_checksum_gen_factory = GetFileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory();
8069 opts.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 10;
8070
8071 // Bootstrap the test database.
8072 DB* db = nullptr;
8073 std::string dbname = test::PerThreadDBPath("file_chksum");
8074 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(opts, dbname, &db));
8075
8076 WriteOptions wopts;
8077 FlushOptions fopts;
8078 fopts.wait = true;
8079 Random rnd(test::RandomSeed());
8080 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
8081 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(wopts, Key(i), rnd.RandomString(100)));
8082 ASSERT_OK(db->Flush(fopts));
8083 }
8084
8085 // Obtain rich files metadata for source of truth.
8086 std::vector<LiveFileMetaData> live_files;
8087 db->GetLiveFilesMetaData(&live_files);
8088
8089 ASSERT_OK(db->Close());
8090 delete db;
8091 db = nullptr;
8092
8093 // Process current MANIFEST file and build internal file checksum mappings.
8094 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumList> checksum_list(NewFileChecksumList());
8095 auto read_only_fs =
8096 std::make_shared<ReadOnlyFileSystem>(env_->GetFileSystem());
8097 ASSERT_OK(experimental::GetFileChecksumsFromCurrentManifest(
8098 read_only_fs.get(), dbname, checksum_list.get()));
8099
8100 ASSERT_TRUE(checksum_list != nullptr);
8101
8102 // Retrieve files, related checksums and checksum functions.
8103 std::vector<uint64_t> file_numbers;
8104 std::vector<std::string> checksums;
8105 std::vector<std::string> checksum_func_names;
8106 ASSERT_OK(checksum_list->GetAllFileChecksums(&file_numbers, &checksums,
8107 &checksum_func_names));
8108
8109 // Compare results.
8110 ASSERT_EQ(live_files.size(), checksum_list->size());
8111 for (size_t i = 0; i < live_files.size(); i++) {
8112 std::string stored_checksum;
8113 std::string stored_func_name;
8114 ASSERT_OK(checksum_list->SearchOneFileChecksum(
8115 live_files[i].file_number, &stored_checksum, &stored_func_name));
8116
8117 ASSERT_EQ(live_files[i].file_checksum, stored_checksum);
8118 ASSERT_EQ(live_files[i].file_checksum_func_name, stored_func_name);
8119 }
8120}
8121
8122} // namespace ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE

8126 ::testing::InitGoogleTest(&argc, argv);
8127 RegisterCustomObjects(argc, argv);
8128 return RUN_ALL_TESTS();
8129}
